78static void httpd_mark_query_answered(httpd_query_t *q);

80static void httpd_trigger_destroy(httpd_trigger_t *cb, unsigned delta)
81{
82 assert (cb->refcnt >= delta);
83
84 cb->refcnt -= delta;
85 if (cb->refcnt == 0) {
86 lstr_wipe(&cb->auth_realm);
87 if (cb->destroy) {
88 cb->destroy(cb);
89 } else {
90 p_delete(&cb);
91 }
92 }
93}
94
95httpd_trigger_t *httpd_trigger_dup(httpd_trigger_t *cb)
96{
97 cb->refcnt += 2;
98 return cb;
99}
100
101void httpd_trigger_delete(httpd_trigger_t **cbp)
102{
103 if (*cbp) {
104 httpd_trigger_destroy(*cbp, 2);
105 *cbp = NULL;
106 }
107}
108
109void httpd_trigger_persist(httpd_trigger_t *cb)
110{
111 cb->refcnt |= 1;
112}
113
114void httpd_trigger_loose(httpd_trigger_t *cb)
115{
116 httpd_trigger_destroy(cb, cb->refcnt & 1);
117}

119/* zlib helpers {{{ */
120
121#define HTTP_ZLIB_BUFSIZ (64 << 10)
122
123static void http_zlib_stream_reset(z_stream *s)
124{
125 s->next_in = s->next_out = NULL;
126 s->avail_in = s->avail_out = 0;
127}
128
129#define http_zlib_inflate_init(w) \
130 ({ typeof(*(w)) *_w = (w); \
131 \
132 if (_w->zs.state == NULL) { \
133 if (inflateInit2(&_w->zs, MAX_WBITS + 32) != Z_OK) \
134 logger_panic(&_G.logger, "zlib error"); \
135 } \
136 http_zlib_stream_reset(&_w->zs); \
137 _w->compressed = true; \
138 })
139
140#define http_zlib_reset(w) \
141 ({ typeof(*(w)) *_w = (w); \
142 \
143 if (_w->compressed) { \
144 http_zlib_stream_reset(&_w->zs); \
145 inflateReset(&_w->zs); \
146 _w->compressed = false; \
147 } \
148 })
149
150#define http_zlib_wipe(w) \
151 ({ typeof(*(w)) *_w = (w); \
152 \
153 if (_w->zs.state) \
154 inflateEnd(&_w->zs); \
155 _w->compressed = false; \
156 })
157
158static int http_zlib_inflate(z_stream *s, int *clen,
159 sb_t *out, pstream_t *in, int flush)
160{
161 int rc;
162
163 s->next_in = (Bytef *)in->s;
164 s->avail_in = ps_len(in);
165
166 for (;;) {
167 size_t sz = MAX(HTTP_ZLIB_BUFSIZ, s->avail_in * 4);
168
169 s->next_out = (Bytef *)sb_grow(out, sz);
170 s->avail_out = sb_avail(out);
171
172 rc = inflate(s, flush ? Z_FINISH : Z_SYNC_FLUSH);
173 switch (rc) {
174 case Z_BUF_ERROR:
175 case Z_OK:
176 case Z_STREAM_END:
177 __sb_fixlen(out, (char *)s->next_out - out->data);
178 if (*clen >= 0) {
179 *clen -= (char *)s->next_in - in->s;
180 }
181 __ps_skip_upto(in, s->next_in);
182 break;
183 default:
184 return rc;
185 }
186
187 if (rc == Z_STREAM_END && ps_len(in)) {
188 return Z_STREAM_ERROR;
189 }
190 if (rc == Z_BUF_ERROR) {
191 if (s->avail_in) {
192 continue;
193 }
194 if (flush) {
195 return Z_STREAM_ERROR;
196 }
197 return 0;
198 }
199 return 0;
200 }
201}

203/* }}} */
204/* RFC 2616 helpers {{{ */
205
206#define PARSE_RETHROW(e) ({ \
207 int __e = (e); \
208 if (unlikely(__e)) { \
209 return __e; \
210 } \
211 })
212
213static inline void http_skipspaces(pstream_t *ps)
214{
215 while (ps->s < ps->s_end && (ps->s[0] == ' ' || ps->s[0] == '\t'))
216 ps->s++;
217}
218
219/* rfc 2616, ยง2.2: Basic rules */
220static inline int http_getline(pstream_t *ps, unsigned max_len,
221 pstream_t *out)
222{
223 const char *p = memmem(ps->s, ps_len(ps), "\r\n", 2);
224
225 if (unlikely(!p)) {
226 *out = ps_initptr(NULL, NULL);
227 if (ps_len(ps) > max_len) {
228 return PARSE_ERROR;
229 }
230 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
231 }
232 *out = ps_initptr(ps->s, p);
233 return __ps_skip_upto(ps, p + 2);
234}
235
236/* rfc 2616, ยง3.3.1: Full Date */
237static char const * const days[7] = {
238 "Sun", "Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri", "Sat",
239};
240static char const * const months[12] = {
241 "Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr", "May", "Jun",
242 "Jul", "Aug", "Sep", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec",
243};
244
245static inline void http_update_date_cache(struct http_date *out, time_t now)
246{
247 if (out->date != now) {
248 struct tm tm;
249
250 gmtime_r(&now, &tm);
251 sprintf(out->buf, "Date: %s, %02d %s %04d %02d:%02d:%02d GMT\r\n",
252 days[tm.tm_wday], tm.tm_mday, months[tm.tm_mon],
253 tm.tm_year + 1900, tm.tm_hour, tm.tm_min, tm.tm_sec);
254 }
255}
256
257void httpd_put_date_hdr(outbuf_t *ob, const char *hdr, time_t now)
258{
259 struct tm tm;
260
261 gmtime_r(&now, &tm);
262 ob_addf(ob, "%s: %s, %02d %s %04d %02d:%02d:%02d GMT\r\n",
263 hdr, days[tm.tm_wday], tm.tm_mday, months[tm.tm_mon],
264 tm.tm_year + 1900, tm.tm_hour, tm.tm_min, tm.tm_sec);
265}

267/* rfc 2616: ยง4.2: Message Headers */
268
269/* FIXME: deal with quotes and similar stuff in 'ps' */
270static ALWAYS_INLINE bool http_hdr_equals(pstream_t ps, const char *v)
271{
272 size_t vlen = strlen(v);
273
274 if (ps_len(&ps) != vlen) {
275 return false;
276 }
277 for (size_t i = 0; i < vlen; i++) {
278 if (tolower(ps.b[i]) != v[i]) {
279 return false;
280 }
281 }
282 return true;
283}
284
285static bool http_hdr_contains(pstream_t ps, const char *v)
286{
287 pstream_t tmp = ps_initptr(NULL, NULL);
288
289 while (ps_get_ps_chr(&ps, ',', &tmp) == 0) {
290 ps_trim(&tmp);
291 __ps_skip(&ps, 1);
292
293 if (http_hdr_equals(tmp, v)) {
294 return true;
295 }
296 }
297 ps_trim(&ps);
298 return http_hdr_equals(ps, v);
299}
300
301/* rfc 2616: ยง5.1: Request Line */
302
303static int t_urldecode(httpd_qinfo_t *rq, pstream_t ps)
304{
305 char *buf = t_new_raw(char, ps_len(&ps) + 1);
306 char *p = buf;
307
308 rq->vars = ps_initptr(NULL, NULL);
309
310 while (!ps_done(&ps)) {
311 int c = __ps_getc(&ps);
312
313 if (c == '+') {
314 c = ' ';
315 } else
316 if (c == '%') {
317 c = RETHROW(ps_hexdecode(&ps));
318 }
319 if (c == '?') {
320 *p++ = '\0';
321 rq->vars = ps;
322 break;
323 }
324 *p++ = c;
325 }
326 *p++ = '\0';
327
328 path_simplify2(buf, true);
329 rq->prefix = ps_initptr(NULL, NULL);
330 rq->query = ps_initstr(buf);
331 return 0;
332}
333
334static int ps_get_ver(pstream_t *ps)
335{
336 int i = ps_geti(ps);
337
338 PS_WANT(i >= 0 && i < 128);
339 return i;
340}
341
342static int t_http_parse_request_line(pstream_t *ps, unsigned max_len,
343 httpd_qinfo_t *req)
344{
345 pstream_t line, method, uri;
346
347 do {
348 PARSE_RETHROW(http_getline(ps, max_len, &line));
349 } while (ps_len(&line) == 0);
350
351 PS_CHECK(ps_get_ps_chr(&line, ' ', &method));
352 __ps_skip(&line, 1);
353
354 switch (http_get_token_ps(method)) {
355#define CASE(c) case HTTP_TK_##c: req->method = HTTP_METHOD_##c; break
356 CASE(CONNECT);
357 CASE(DELETE);
358 CASE(GET);
359 CASE(HEAD);
360 CASE(OPTIONS);
361 CASE(POST);
362 CASE(PUT);
363 CASE(TRACE);
364 default:
365 req->method = HTTP_METHOD_ERROR;
366 return PARSE_ERROR;
367#undef CASE
368 }
369
370 uri = ps_initptr(NULL, NULL);
371 PS_CHECK(ps_get_ps_chr(&line, ' ', &uri));
372 __ps_skip(&line, 1);
373
374 if (ps_skipstr(&uri, "http://") == 0 || ps_skipstr(&uri, "https://") == 0)
375 {
376 PS_CHECK(ps_get_ps_chr(&uri, '/', &req->host));
377 } else {
378 p_clear(&req->host, 1);
379 if (uri.s[0] != '/' && !ps_memequal(&uri, "*", 1)) {
380 return PARSE_ERROR;
381 }
382 }
383 RETHROW(t_urldecode(req, uri));
384 PS_CHECK(ps_skipstr(&line, "HTTP/"));
385 if (ps_len(&line) == 0 || !isdigit(line.b[0])) {
386 return PARSE_ERROR;
387 }
388 req->http_version = RETHROW(ps_get_ver(&line)) << 8;
389 if (ps_getc(&line) != '.' || ps_len(&line) == 0 || !isdigit(line.b[0])) {
390 return PARSE_ERROR;
391 }
392 req->http_version |= RETHROW(ps_get_ver(&line));
393 return ps_len(&line) ? PARSE_ERROR : 0;
394}
395
396/* rfc 2616: ยง6.1: Status Line */
397
398static inline int
399http_parse_status_line(pstream_t *ps, unsigned max_len, httpc_qinfo_t *qi)
400{
401 pstream_t line, code;
402
403 PARSE_RETHROW(http_getline(ps, max_len, &line));
404
405 if (ps_skipstr(&line, "HTTP/")) {
406 return PARSE_ERROR;
407 }
408 if (ps_len(&line) == 0 || !isdigit(line.b[0])) {
409 return PARSE_ERROR;
410 }
411 qi->http_version = RETHROW(ps_get_ver(&line)) << 8;
412 if (ps_getc(&line) != '.' || ps_len(&line) == 0 || !isdigit(line.b[0])) {
413 return PARSE_ERROR;
414 }
415 qi->http_version |= RETHROW(ps_get_ver(&line));
416 __ps_skip(&line, 1);
417
418 if (ps_get_ps_chr(&line, ' ', &code) || ps_len(&code) != 3) {
419 return PARSE_ERROR;
420 }
421 __ps_skip(&line, 1);
422
423 qi->code = ps_geti(&code);
424 if ((int)qi->code < 100 || (int)qi->code >= 600) {
425 return PARSE_ERROR;
426 }
427 qi->reason = line;
428 return PARSE_OK;
429}
430
431#undef PARSE_RETHROW
432
433static void http_chunk_patch(outbuf_t *ob, char *buf, unsigned len)
434{
435 if (len == 0) {
436 sb_shrink(&ob->sb, 12);
437 ob->length -= 12;
438 ob->sb_trailing -= 12;
439 } else {
440 buf[0] = '\r';
441 buf[1] = '\n';
442 buf[2] = __str_digits_lower[(len >> 28) & 0xf];
443 buf[3] = __str_digits_lower[(len >> 24) & 0xf];
444 buf[4] = __str_digits_lower[(len >> 20) & 0xf];
445 buf[5] = __str_digits_lower[(len >> 16) & 0xf];
446 buf[6] = __str_digits_lower[(len >> 12) & 0xf];
447 buf[7] = __str_digits_lower[(len >> 8) & 0xf];
448 buf[8] = __str_digits_lower[(len >> 4) & 0xf];
449 buf[9] = __str_digits_lower[(len >> 0) & 0xf];
450 buf[10] = '\r';
451 buf[11] = '\n';
452 }
453}
454
455#define CLENGTH_RESERVE 12
456
457static void
458http_clength_patch(outbuf_t *ob, char s[static CLENGTH_RESERVE], unsigned len)
459{
460 (sprintf)(s, "%10d\r", len);
461 s[CLENGTH_RESERVE - 1] = '\n';
462}

467ALWAYS_INLINE static int ssl_add_verify_file(SSL_CTX *ctx, lstr_t path)
468{
469 return SSL_CTX_load_verify_locations(ctx, path.s, NULL) == 1 ? 0 : -1;
470}
471
472#if OPENSSL_VERSION_IS(>,1,1,0)
473
474static int ssl_open_keylog_file(void)
475{
476 if (_G.ssl_keylog_fd >= 0) {
477 return 0;
478 }
479
480 /* Give read and write permission for user only. */
481 _G.ssl_keylog_fd = open(_G.ssl_keylog_file_path,
482 O_CREAT | O_WRONLY | O_APPEND,
483 S_IRUSR | S_IWUSR);
484
485 if (_G.ssl_keylog_fd < 0) {
486 return -1;
487 }
488
489 return 0;
490}
491
492static void ssl_keylog_cb(const SSL *ssl, const char *line)
493{
494 /* This callback is called when TLS key is generated or received, so it is
495 * for example called systematically at handshake. It will store the key
496 * for debugging purposes allowing us to decode exchanges. */
497
498 /* If _G.ssl_keylog_file_path is NULL, ssl_keylog_cb is not called. */
499 assert(_G.ssl_keylog_file_path);
500
501 if (ssl_open_keylog_file() < 0) {
502 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 1, "error when trying to open file from "
503 "env var 'SSLKEYLOGFILE' value '%s': %m",
504 _G.ssl_keylog_file_path);
505 return;
506 }
507
508 if (flock(_G.ssl_keylog_fd, LOCK_EX) < 0) {
509 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 1, "error when locking SSL key log file: "
510 " `%m`");
511 return;
512 }
513
514 if ((write(_G.ssl_keylog_fd, line, strlen(line)) < 0) ||
515 (write(_G.ssl_keylog_fd, "\n", 1) < 0))
516 {
517 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 1, "error when writing SSL key: `%m`");
518 }
519
520 flock(_G.ssl_keylog_fd, LOCK_UN);
521}
522
523static void set_ssl_keylog_cb(SSL_CTX *ssl_ctx)
524{
525 if (!_G.ssl_keylog_file_path) {
526 return;
527 }
528
529 if (ssl_open_keylog_file() < 0) {
530 logger_error(&_G.logger, "error when trying to open file from "
531 "env var 'SSLKEYLOGFILE' value '%s': %m",
532 _G.ssl_keylog_file_path);
533 return;
534 }
535
536 SSL_CTX_set_keylog_callback(ssl_ctx, ssl_keylog_cb);
537}
538
539#endif
540
541static void close_ssl_keylog_file(void)
542{
543 if (p_close(&_G.ssl_keylog_fd) < 0) {
544 logger_error(&_G.logger, "error when closing file `%s`: `%m`",
545 _G.ssl_keylog_file_path);
546 }
547}

549/* }}} */
550/* HTTPD Queries {{{ */
551
552/*
553 * HTTPD queries refcounting holds:
554 * - 1 for the fact that it has an owner.
555 * - 1 for the fact it hasn't been answered yet.
556 * - 1 for the fact it hasn't been parsed yet.
557 * Hence it's obj_retained() on creation, always.
558 */
559
560httpd_qinfo_t *httpd_qinfo_dup(const httpd_qinfo_t *info)
561{
562 httpd_qinfo_t *res;
563 size_t len = sizeof(info);
564 void *p;
565 intptr_t offs;
566
567 len += sizeof(info->hdrs[0]) * info->hdrs_len;
568 len += ps_len(&info->host);
569 len += ps_len(&info->prefix);
570 len += ps_len(&info->query);
571 len += ps_len(&info->vars);
572 len += ps_len(&info->hdrs_ps);
573
574 res = p_new_extra(httpd_qinfo_t, len);
575 memcpy(res, info, offsetof(httpd_qinfo_t, host));
576 res->hdrs = (void *)&res[1];
577 p = res->hdrs + res->hdrs_len;
578 res->host.s = p;
579 res->host.s_end = p = mempcpy(p, info->host.s, ps_len(&info->host));
580 res->prefix.s = p;
581 res->prefix.s_end = p = mempcpy(p, info->prefix.s, ps_len(&info->prefix));
582 res->query.s = p;
583 res->query.s_end = p = mempcpy(p, info->query.s, ps_len(&info->query));
584 res->vars.s = p;
585 res->vars.s_end = p = mempcpy(p, info->vars.s, ps_len(&info->vars));
586 res->hdrs_ps.s = p;
587 res->hdrs_ps.s_end = mempcpy(p, info->hdrs_ps.s, ps_len(&info->hdrs_ps));
588
589 offs = res->hdrs_ps.s - info->hdrs_ps.s;
590 for (int i = 0; i < res->hdrs_len; i++) {
591 http_qhdr_t *lhs = &res->hdrs[i];
592 const http_qhdr_t *rhs = &info->hdrs[i];
593
594 lhs->wkhdr = rhs->wkhdr;
595 lhs->key = ps_initptr(rhs->key.s + offs, rhs->key.s_end + offs);
596 lhs->val = ps_initptr(rhs->val.s + offs, rhs->val.s_end + offs);
597 }
598 return res;
599}
600
601static httpd_query_t *httpd_query_create(httpd_t *w, httpd_trigger_t *cb)
602{
603 httpd_query_t *q;
604
605 if (cb) {
606 q = obj_new_of_class(httpd_query, cb->query_cls);
607 } else {
608 q = obj_new(httpd_query);
609 }
610
611 if (w->queries == 0) {
612 q->ob = &w->ob;
613 }
614 /* ensure refcount is 3: owned, unanwsered, unparsed */
615 obj_retain(q);
616 obj_retain(q);
617 q->owner = w;
618 dlist_add_tail(&w->query_list, &q->query_link);
619 if (cb) {
620 q->trig_cb = httpd_trigger_dup(cb);
621 }
622 return q;
623}
624
625static ALWAYS_INLINE void httpd_query_detach(httpd_query_t *q)
626{
627 httpd_t *w = q->owner;
628
629 if (w) {
630 if (!q->own_ob) {
631 q->ob = NULL;
632 }
633 dlist_remove(&q->query_link);
634 if (q->parsed) {
635 w->queries--;
636 }
637 w->queries_done -= q->answered;
638 q->owner = NULL;
639 obj_release(&q);
640 }
641}
642
643static httpd_query_t *httpd_query_init(httpd_query_t *q)
644{
645 sb_init(&q->payload);
646 q->http_version = HTTP_1_1;
647 return q;
648}
649
650static void httpd_query_wipe(httpd_query_t *q)
651{
652 if (q->trig_cb) {
653 if (q->trig_cb->on_query_wipe) {
654 q->trig_cb->on_query_wipe(q);
655 }
656 httpd_trigger_delete(&q->trig_cb);
657 }
658 if (q->own_ob) {
659 ob_delete(&q->ob);
660 }
661 httpd_qinfo_delete(&q->qinfo);
662 sb_wipe(&q->payload);
663 httpd_query_detach(q);
664}
665
666static void httpd_query_on_data_bufferize(httpd_query_t *q, pstream_t ps)
667{
668 size_t plen = ps_len(&ps);
669
670 if (unlikely(plen + q->payload.len > q->payload_max_size)) {
671 httpd_reject(q, REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE,
672 "payload is larger than %d octets",
673 q->payload_max_size);
674 return;
675 }
676 sb_add(&q->payload, ps.s, plen);
677}
678
679void httpd_bufferize(httpd_query_t *q, unsigned maxsize)
680{
681 const httpd_qinfo_t *inf = q->qinfo;
682
683 q->payload_max_size = maxsize;
684 q->on_data = &httpd_query_on_data_bufferize;
685 if (!inf) {
686 return;
687 }
688 for (int i = inf->hdrs_len; i-- > 0; ) {
689 if (inf->hdrs[i].wkhdr == HTTP_WKHDR_CONTENT_LENGTH) {
690 uint64_t len = strtoull(inf->hdrs[i].val.s, NULL, 0);
691
692 if (unlikely(len > maxsize)) {
693 httpd_reject(q, REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE,
694 "payload is larger than %d octets", maxsize);
695 } else {
696 sb_grow(&q->payload, len);
697 }
698 return;
699 }
700 }
701}
702
703OBJ_VTABLE(httpd_query)
704 httpd_query.init = httpd_query_init;
705 httpd_query.wipe = httpd_query_wipe;
706OBJ_VTABLE_END()

708
709/*---- low level httpd_query reply functions ----*/
710
711outbuf_t *httpd_reply_hdrs_start(httpd_query_t *q, int code, bool force_uncacheable)
712{
713 outbuf_t *ob = httpd_get_ob(q);
714
715 http_update_date_cache(&date_cache_g, lp_getsec());
716
717 assert (!q->hdrs_started && !q->hdrs_done);
718
719 q->answer_code = code;
720 ob_addf(ob, "HTTP/1.%d %d %*pM\r\n", HTTP_MINOR(q->http_version),
721 code, LSTR_FMT_ARG(http_code_to_str(code)));
722 ob_add(ob, date_cache_g.buf, sizeof(date_cache_g.buf) - 1);
723 ob_adds(ob, "Accept-Encoding: identity, gzip, deflate\r\n");
724
725 /* XXX: For CORS purposes, allow all origins for now */
726 ob_adds(ob, "Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *\r\n");
727
728 if (q->owner && q->owner->connection_close) {
729 if (!q->conn_close) {
730 ob_adds(ob, "Connection: close\r\n");
731 q->conn_close = true;
732 }
733 }
734 if (force_uncacheable) {
735 ob_adds(ob,
736 "Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate\r\n"
737 "Pragma: no-cache\r\n");
738 }
739 q->hdrs_started = true;
740 return ob;
741}
742
743void httpd_reply_hdrs_done(httpd_query_t *q, int clen, bool chunked)
744{
745 outbuf_t *ob = httpd_get_ob(q);
746
747 assert (!q->hdrs_done);
748 q->hdrs_done = true;
749
750 if (clen >= 0) {
751 ob_addf(ob, "Content-Length: %d\r\n\r\n", clen);
752 return;
753 }
754
755 if (chunked) {
756 if (likely(q->http_version != HTTP_1_0)) {
757 q->chunked = true;
758 ob_adds(ob, "Transfer-Encoding: chunked\r\n");
759 /* XXX: no \r\n because http_chunk_patch adds it */
760 } else {
761 /* FIXME: we aren't allowed to fallback to the non chunked case
762 * here because it would break assumptions from the caller
763 * that it can stream the answer with returns in the event
764 * loop
765 */
766 if (!q->conn_close) {
767 ob_adds(ob, "Connection: close\r\n");
768 q->conn_close = true;
769 }
770 if (q->owner) {
771 q->owner->connection_close = true;
772 }
773 ob_adds(ob, "\r\n");
774 }
775 } else {
776 q->clength_hack = true;
777 ob_adds(ob, "Content-Length: ");
778 q->chunk_hdr_offs = ob_reserve(ob, CLENGTH_RESERVE);
779 ob_adds(ob, "\r\n");
780 q->chunk_prev_length = ob->length;
781 }
782}
783
784void httpd_reply_chunk_done_(httpd_query_t *q, outbuf_t *ob)
785{
786 assert (q->chunk_started);
787 q->chunk_started = false;
788 http_chunk_patch(ob, ob->sb.data + q->chunk_hdr_offs,
789 ob->length - q->chunk_prev_length);
790}
791
792
793__attribute__((format(printf, 4, 0)))
794static void httpd_notify_status(httpd_t *w, httpd_query_t *q, int handler,
795 const char *fmt, va_list va);
796
797static void httpd_trace_query_result(httpd_query_t *q)
798{
799 if (q->qinfo && logger_is_traced(&_G.logger, 1)) {
800 lstr_t answer_code = http_code_to_str(q->answer_code);
801
802 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 1, "query `%*pM` finished (%d - %*pM)",
803 PS_FMT_ARG(&q->qinfo->query), q->answer_code,
804 LSTR_FMT_ARG(answer_code));
805
806 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 2, "query header was:\n%*pM",
807 PS_FMT_ARG(&q->qinfo->hdrs_ps));
808
809 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 3, "query payload was:\n%*pM",
810 SB_FMT_ARG(&q->payload));
811 }
812}
813
814void httpd_reply_done(httpd_query_t *q)
815{
816 va_list va;
817 outbuf_t *ob = httpd_get_ob(q);
818
819 assert (q->hdrs_done && !q->answered && !q->chunk_started);
820 if (q->chunked) {
821 ob_adds(ob, "\r\n0\r\n\r\n");
822 }
823 if (q->clength_hack) {
824 http_clength_patch(ob, ob->sb.data + q->chunk_hdr_offs,
825 ob->length - q->chunk_prev_length);
826 q->clength_hack = false;
827 }
828 httpd_notify_status(q->owner, q, HTTPD_QUERY_STATUS_ANSWERED, "", va);
829 httpd_trace_query_result(q);
830 httpd_mark_query_answered(q);
831}
832
833static void httpd_set_mask(httpd_t *w);
834
835void httpd_signal_write(httpd_query_t *q)
836{
837 httpd_t *w = q->owner;
838
839 if (w) {
840 assert (q->hdrs_done && !q->answered && !q->chunk_started);
841 httpd_set_mask(w);
842 }
843}
844
845/*---- high level httpd_query reply functions ----*/
846
847static ALWAYS_INLINE void httpd_query_reply_100continue_(httpd_query_t *q)
848{
849 if (q->answered || q->hdrs_started) {
850 return;
851 }
852 if (q->expect100cont) {
853 ob_addf(httpd_get_ob(q), "HTTP/1.%d 100 Continue\r\n\r\n",
854 HTTP_MINOR(q->http_version));
855 q->expect100cont = false;
856 }
857}
858
859void httpd_reply_100continue(httpd_query_t *q)
860{
861 httpd_query_reply_100continue_(q);
862}
863
864void httpd_reply_202accepted(httpd_query_t *q)
865{
866 if (q->answered || q->hdrs_started) {
867 return;
868 }
869
870 httpd_reply_hdrs_start(q, HTTP_CODE_ACCEPTED, false);
871 httpd_reply_hdrs_done(q, 0, false);
872 httpd_reply_done(q);
873}
874
875void httpd_reject_(httpd_query_t *q, int code, const char *fmt, ...)
876{
877 va_list ap;
878 outbuf_t *ob;
879
880 if (q->answered || q->hdrs_started) {
881 return;
882 }
883
884 ob = httpd_reply_hdrs_start(q, code, false);
885 ob_adds(ob, "Content-Type: text/html\r\n");
886 httpd_reply_hdrs_done(q, -1, false);
887
888 ob_addf(ob, "<html><body><h1>%d - %*pM</h1><p>",
889 code, LSTR_FMT_ARG(http_code_to_str(code)));
890 va_start(ap, fmt);
891 ob_addvf(ob, fmt, ap);
892 va_end(ap);
893 ob_adds(ob, "</p></body></html>\r\n");
894
895 va_start(ap, fmt);
896 httpd_notify_status(q->owner, q, HTTPD_QUERY_STATUS_ANSWERED, fmt, ap);
897 va_end(ap);
898 httpd_reply_done(q);
899}
900
901void httpd_reject_unauthorized(httpd_query_t *q, lstr_t auth_realm)
902{
903 const lstr_t body = LSTR("<html><body>"
904 "<h1>401 - Authentication required</h1>"
905 "</body></html>\r\n");
906 va_list va;
907 outbuf_t *ob;
908
909 if (q->answered || q->hdrs_started) {
910 return;
911 }
912
913 ob = httpd_reply_hdrs_start(q, HTTP_CODE_UNAUTHORIZED, false);
914 ob_adds(ob, "Content-Type: text/html\r\n");
915 ob_addf(ob, "WWW-Authenticate: Basic realm=\"%*pM\"\r\n",
916 LSTR_FMT_ARG(auth_realm));
917 httpd_reply_hdrs_done(q, body.len, false);
918 ob_add(ob, body.s, body.len);
919
920 httpd_notify_status(q->owner, q, HTTP_CODE_UNAUTHORIZED, "", va);
921 httpd_reply_done(q);
922}
923
924/* }}} */
925/* HTTPD Triggers {{{ */
926
927static httpd_trigger_node_t *
928httpd_trigger_node_new(httpd_trigger_node_t *parent, lstr_t path)
929{
930 httpd_trigger_node_t *node;
931 uint32_t pos;
932
933 pos = qm_put(http_path, &parent->childs, &path, NULL, 0);
934 if (pos & QHASH_COLLISION) {
935 return parent->childs.values[pos & ~QHASH_COLLISION];
936 }
937
938 parent->childs.values[pos] = node =
939 p_new_extra(httpd_trigger_node_t, path.len + 1);
940 qm_init_cached(http_path, &node->childs);
941 memcpy(node->path, path.s, path.len + 1);
942
943 /* Ensure the key point to a valid string since path may be deallocated */
944 parent->childs.keys[pos] = LSTR_INIT_V(node->path, path.len);
945 return node;
946}
947
948static void httpd_trigger_node_wipe(httpd_trigger_node_t *node);
949GENERIC_DELETE(httpd_trigger_node_t, httpd_trigger_node);
950
951static void httpd_trigger_node_wipe(httpd_trigger_node_t *node)
952{
953 httpd_trigger_delete(&node->cb);
954 qm_deep_wipe(http_path, &node->childs, IGNORE, httpd_trigger_node_delete);
955}
956
957bool httpd_trigger_register_flags(httpd_trigger_node_t *n, const char *path,
958 httpd_trigger_t *cb, bool overwrite)
959{
960 while (*path == '/')
961 path++;
962 while (*path) {
963 const char *q = strchrnul(path, '/');
964 lstr_t s = LSTR_INIT(path, q - path);
965
966 n = httpd_trigger_node_new(n, s);
967 while (*q == '/')
968 q++;
969 path = q;
970 }
971 if (!overwrite && n->cb) {
972 return false;
973 }
974 httpd_trigger_delete(&n->cb);
975 n->cb = httpd_trigger_dup(cb);
976 if (unlikely(cb->query_cls == NULL)) {
977 cb->query_cls = obj_class(httpd_query);
978 }
979 return true;
980}
981
982static bool httpd_trigger_unregister__(httpd_trigger_node_t *n, const char *path,
983 httpd_trigger_t *what, bool *res)
984{
985 while (*path == '/')
986 path++;
987
988 if (!*path) {
989 if (!what || n->cb == what) {
990 httpd_trigger_delete(&n->cb);
991 *res = true;
992 } else {
993 *res = false;
994 }
995 } else {
996 const char *q = strchrnul(path, '/');
997 lstr_t s = LSTR_INIT(path, q - path);
998 int pos = qm_find(http_path, &n->childs, &s);
999
1000 if (pos < 0) {
1001 return false;
1002 }
1003 if (httpd_trigger_unregister__(n->childs.values[pos], q, what, res)) {
1004 httpd_trigger_node_delete(&n->childs.values[pos]);
1005 qm_del_at(http_path, &n->childs, pos);
1006 }
1007 }
1008 return qm_len(http_path, &n->childs) == 0;
1009}
1010
1011bool httpd_trigger_unregister_(httpd_trigger_node_t *n, const char *path,
1012 httpd_trigger_t *what)
1013{
1014 bool res = false;
1015
1016 httpd_trigger_unregister__(n, path, what, &res);
1017 return res;
1018}
1019
1020/* XXX: assumes path is canonical wrt '/' and starts with one */
1021static httpd_trigger_t *
1022httpd_trigger_resolve(httpd_trigger_node_t *n, httpd_qinfo_t *req)
1023{
1024 httpd_trigger_t *res = n->cb;
1025 const char *p = req->query.s;
1026 const char *q = req->query.s_end;
1027
1028 req->prefix = ps_initptr(p, p);
1029 while (p++ < q) {
1030 lstr_t s;
1031 int pos;
1032
1033 s.s = p;
1034 p = memchr(p, '/', q - p) ?: q;
1035 s.len = p - s.s;
1036 pos = qm_find(http_path, &n->childs, &s);
1037 if (pos < 0) {
1038 break;
1039 }
1040 n = n->childs.values[pos];
1041 if (n->cb) {
1042 res = n->cb;
1043 req->query.s = req->prefix.s_end = p;
1044 }
1045 }
1046 return res;
1047}
1048
1049/* }}} */
1050/* HTTPD Parser {{{ */
1051
1052static inline void t_ps_get_http_var_parse_elem(pstream_t elem, lstr_t *out)
1053{
1054 if (memchr(elem.p, '%', ps_len(&elem))) {
1055 sb_t sb;
1056
1057 t_sb_init(&sb, ps_len(&elem));
1058 sb_add_lstr_urldecode(&sb, LSTR_PS_V(&elem));
1059 *out = lstr_init_(sb.data, sb.len, MEM_STACK);
1060 } else {
1061 *out = LSTR_PS_V(&elem);
1062 }
1063}
1064
1065int t_ps_get_http_var(pstream_t *ps, lstr_t *key, lstr_t *value)
1066{
1067 pstream_t key_ps, value_ps;
1068
1069 RETHROW(ps_get_ps_chr_and_skip(ps, '=', &key_ps));
1070 THROW_ERR_IF(ps_done(&key_ps));
1071
1072 if (ps_get_ps_chr_and_skip(ps, '&', &value_ps) < 0) {
1073 RETHROW(ps_get_ps(ps, ps_len(ps), &value_ps));
1074 }
1075
1076 t_ps_get_http_var_parse_elem(key_ps, key);
1077 t_ps_get_http_var_parse_elem(value_ps, value);
1078
1079 return 0;
1080}
1081
1082__attribute__((format(printf, 4, 0)))
1083static void httpd_notify_status(httpd_t *w, httpd_query_t *q, int handler,
1084 const char *fmt, va_list va)
1085{
1086 if (!q->status_sent) {
1087 q->status_sent = true;
1088
1089 if (w && w->on_status) {
1090 (*w->on_status)(w, q, handler, fmt, va);
1091 }
1092 }
1093}
1094
1095static void httpd_http2_set_mask(httpd_t *w);
1096
1097static void httpd_set_mask(httpd_t *w)
1098{
1099 int mask;
1100
1101 /* XXX: upstream httpd objects (for http2 server) have no fd (ev). */
1102 if (!w->ev) {
1103 httpd_http2_set_mask(w);
1104 return;
1105 }
1106
1107 if (w->queries >= w->cfg->pipeline_depth
1108 || w->ob.length >= (int)w->cfg->outbuf_max_size
1109 || w->state == HTTP_PARSER_CLOSE)
1110 {
1111 mask = 0;
1112 } else {
1113 mask = POLLIN;
1114 }
1115
1116 if (!ob_is_empty(&w->ob)) {
1117 mask |= POLLOUT;
1118 }
1119
1120 if (w->ssl) {
1121 if (SSL_want_read(w->ssl)) {
1122 mask |= POLLIN;
1123 }
1124 if (SSL_want_write(w->ssl)) {
1125 mask |= POLLOUT;
1126 }
1127 }
1128
1129 el_fd_set_mask(w->ev, mask);
1130}
1131
1132static void httpd_flush_answered(httpd_t *w)
1133{
1134 dlist_for_each_entry(httpd_query_t, q, &w->query_list, query_link) {
1135 if (q->own_ob) {
1136 ob_merge_delete(&w->ob, &q->ob);
1137 q->own_ob = false;
1138 }
1139 if (!q->answered) {
1140 q->ob = &w->ob;
1141 break;
1142 }
1143 if (likely(q->parsed)) {
1144 httpd_query_detach(q);
1145 }
1146 }
1147 httpd_set_mask(w);
1148}
1149
1150static void httpd_query_done(httpd_t *w, httpd_query_t *q)
1151{
1152 struct timeval now;
1153
1154 lp_gettv(&now);
1155 q->query_sec = now.tv_sec;
1156 q->query_usec = now.tv_usec;
1157 q->parsed = true;
1158 w->queries++;
1159 httpd_flush_answered(w);
1160 if (w->connection_close) {
1161 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_CLOSE;
1162 } else {
1163 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_IDLE;
1164 }
1165 w->chunk_length = 0;
1166 obj_release(&q);
1167}
1168
1169static void httpd_mark_query_answered(httpd_query_t *q)
1170{
1171 assert (!q->answered);
1172 q->answered = true;
1173 q->on_data = NULL;
1174 q->on_done = NULL;
1175 q->on_ready = NULL;
1176 if (q->owner) {
1177 httpd_t *w = q->owner;
1178
1179 w->queries_done++;
1180 if (dlist_is_first(&w->query_list, &q->query_link)) {
1181 httpd_flush_answered(w);
1182 }
1183 }
1184 q->expect100cont = false;
1185 obj_release(&q);
1186}
1187
1188qvector_t(qhdr, http_qhdr_t);
1189static void httpd_do_any(httpd_t *w, httpd_query_t *q, httpd_qinfo_t *req);
1190static void httpd_do_trace(httpd_t *w, httpd_query_t *q, httpd_qinfo_t *req);
1191
1192static int httpd_parse_idle(httpd_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
1193{
1194 t_scope;
1195 size_t start = w->chunk_length > 4 ? w->chunk_length - 4 : 0;
1196 httpd_qinfo_t req;
1197 const uint8_t *p;
1198 pstream_t buf;
1199 int clen = -1;
1200 bool chunked = false;
1201 httpd_query_t *q;
1202 qv_t(qhdr) hdrs;
1203 httpd_trigger_t *cb = NULL;
1204 struct timeval now;
1205
1206 if ((p = memmem(ps->s + start, ps_len(ps) - start, "\r\n\r\n", 4)) == NULL) {
1207 if (ps_len(ps) > w->cfg->header_size_max) {
1208 q = httpd_query_create(w, NULL);
1209 httpd_reject(q, FORBIDDEN, "Headers exceed %d octets",
1210 w->cfg->header_size_max);
1211 goto unrecoverable_error;
1212 }
1213 w->chunk_length = ps_len(ps);
1214 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
1215 }
1216
1217 if (--w->max_queries == 0) {
1218 w->connection_close = true;
1219 }
1220
1221 http_zlib_reset(w);
1222 req.hdrs_ps = ps_initptr(ps->s, p + 4);
1223
1224 switch (t_http_parse_request_line(ps, w->cfg->header_line_max, &req)) {
1225 case PARSE_ERROR:
1226 q = httpd_query_create(w, NULL);
1227 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST, "Invalid request line");
1228 goto unrecoverable_error;
1229
1230 case PARSE_MISSING_DATA:
1231 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
1232
1233 default:
1234 break;
1235 }
1236
1237 if ((unsigned)req.method < countof(w->cfg->roots)) {
1238 cb = httpd_trigger_resolve(&w->cfg->roots[req.method], &req);
1239 }
1240 q = httpd_query_create(w, cb);
1241 q->received_hdr_length = ps_len(&req.hdrs_ps);
1242 q->http_version = req.http_version;
1243 q->qinfo = &req;
1244 buf = __ps_get_ps_upto(ps, p + 2);
1245 __ps_skip_upto(ps, p + 4);
1246 switch (req.http_version) {
1247 case HTTP_1_0:
1248 /* TODO: support old-style Keep-Alive ? */
1249 w->connection_close = true;
1250 break;
1251 case HTTP_1_1:
1252 break;
1253 default:
1254 httpd_reject(q, NOT_IMPLEMENTED,
1255 "This server requires an HTTP/1.1 compatible client");
1256 goto unrecoverable_error;
1257 }
1258
1259 lp_gettv(&now);
1260 q->query_sec = now.tv_sec;
1261 q->query_usec = now.tv_usec;
1262 t_qv_init(&hdrs, 64);
1263
1264 while (!ps_done(&buf)) {
1265 http_qhdr_t *qhdr = qv_growlen(&hdrs, 1);
1266
1267 /* TODO: normalize, make "lists" */
1268 qhdr->key = ps_get_cspan(&buf, &http_non_token);
1269 if (ps_len(&qhdr->key) == 0 || __ps_getc(&buf) != ':') {
1270 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST,
1271 "Header name is empty or not followed by a colon");
1272 goto unrecoverable_error;
1273 }
1274 qhdr->val.s = buf.s;
1275 for (;;) {
1276 ps_skip_afterchr(&buf, '\r');
1277 if (__ps_getc(&buf) != '\n') {
1278 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST,
1279 "CR is not followed by a LF in headers");
1280 goto unrecoverable_error;
1281 }
1282 qhdr->val.s_end = buf.s - 2;
1283 if (ps_done(&buf)) {
1284 break;
1285 }
1286 if (buf.s[0] != '\t' && buf.s[0] != ' ') {
1287 break;
1288 }
1289 __ps_skip(&buf, 1);
1290 }
1291 ps_trim(&qhdr->val);
1292
1293 switch ((qhdr->wkhdr = http_wkhdr_from_ps(qhdr->key))) {
1294 case HTTP_WKHDR_HOST:
1295 if (ps_len(&req.host) == 0) {
1296 req.host = qhdr->val;
1297 }
1298 qv_shrink(&hdrs, 1);
1299 break;
1300
1301 case HTTP_WKHDR_EXPECT:
1302 q->expect100cont |= http_hdr_equals(qhdr->key, "100-continue");
1303 break;
1304
1305 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONNECTION:
1306 w->connection_close |= http_hdr_contains(qhdr->val, "close");
1307 break;
1308
1309 case HTTP_WKHDR_TRANSFER_ENCODING:
1310 /* rfc 2616: ยง4.4: != "identity" means chunked encoding */
1311 switch (http_get_token_ps(qhdr->val)) {
1312 case HTTP_TK_IDENTITY:
1313 chunked = false;
1314 break;
1315 case HTTP_TK_CHUNKED:
1316 chunked = true;
1317 break;
1318 default:
1319 httpd_reject(q, NOT_IMPLEMENTED,
1320 "Transfer-Encoding %*pM is unimplemented",
1321 (int)ps_len(&qhdr->val), qhdr->val.s);
1322 break;
1323 }
1324 break;
1325
1326 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONTENT_LENGTH:
1327 clen = memtoip(qhdr->val.b, ps_len(&qhdr->val), &p);
1328 if (p != qhdr->val.b_end) {
1329 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST, "Content-Length is unparseable");
1330 goto unrecoverable_error;
1331 }
1332 break;
1333
1334 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONTENT_ENCODING:
1335 switch (http_get_token_ps(qhdr->val)) {
1336 case HTTP_TK_DEFLATE:
1337 case HTTP_TK_GZIP:
1338 case HTTP_TK_X_GZIP:
1339 http_zlib_inflate_init(w);
1340 qv_shrink(&hdrs, 1);
1341 break;
1342 default:
1343 http_zlib_reset(w);
1344 break;
1345 }
1346 break;
1347
1348 default:
1349 break;
1350 }
1351 }
1352
1353 if (chunked) {
1354 /* rfc 2616: ยง4.4: if chunked, then ignore any Content-Length */
1355 w->chunk_length = clen = 0;
1356 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR;
1357 } else {
1358 w->chunk_length = clen < 0 ? 0 : clen;
1359 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_BODY;
1360 }
1361 req.hdrs = hdrs.tab;
1362 req.hdrs_len = hdrs.len;
1363
1364 switch (req.method) {
1365 case HTTP_METHOD_TRACE:
1366 httpd_do_trace(w, q, &req);
1367 break;
1368 case HTTP_METHOD_POST:
1369 case HTTP_METHOD_PUT:
1370 if (clen < 0) {
1371 httpd_reject(q, LENGTH_REQUIRED, "");
1372 goto unrecoverable_error;
1373 }
1374 /* FALLTHROUGH */
1375 default:
1376 httpd_do_any(w, q, &req);
1377 break;
1378 }
1379 if (q->qinfo == &req) {
1380 q->qinfo = NULL;
1381 }
1382 httpd_query_reply_100continue_(q);
1383 return PARSE_OK;
1384
1385 unrecoverable_error:
1386 if (q->qinfo == &req) {
1387 q->qinfo = NULL;
1388 }
1389 w->connection_close = true;
1390 httpd_query_done(w, q);
1391 return PARSE_ERROR;
1392}
1393
1394static inline int
1395httpd_flush_data(httpd_t *w, httpd_query_t *q, pstream_t *ps, bool done)
1396{
1397 q->received_body_length += ps_len(ps);
1398
1399 if (q->on_data) {
1400 if (w->compressed && !ps_done(ps)) {
1401 t_scope;
1402 sb_t zbuf;
1403
1404 t_sb_init(&zbuf, HTTP_ZLIB_BUFSIZ);
1405 if (http_zlib_inflate(&w->zs, &w->chunk_length, &zbuf, ps, done)) {
1406 goto zlib_error;
1407 }
1408 q->on_data(q, ps_initsb(&zbuf));
1409 return PARSE_OK;
1410 }
1411 q->on_data(q, *ps);
1412 }
1413 w->chunk_length -= ps_len(ps);
1414 ps->b = ps->b_end;
1415 return PARSE_OK;
1416
1417 zlib_error:
1418 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST, "Invalid compressed data");
1419 w->connection_close = true;
1420 httpd_query_done(w, q);
1421 return PARSE_ERROR;
1422}
1423
1424static int httpd_parse_body(httpd_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
1425{
1426 httpd_query_t *q = dlist_last_entry(&w->query_list, httpd_query_t, query_link);
1427 ssize_t plen = ps_len(ps);
1428
1429 q->expect100cont = false;
1430 assert (w->chunk_length >= 0);
1431 if (plen >= w->chunk_length) {
1432 pstream_t tmp = __ps_get_ps(ps, w->chunk_length);
1433
1434 RETHROW(httpd_flush_data(w, q, &tmp, true));
1435 if (q->on_done) {
1436 q->on_done(q);
1437 }
1438 httpd_query_done(w, q);
1439 return PARSE_OK;
1440 }
1441
1442 if (plen >= w->cfg->on_data_threshold) {
1443 RETHROW(httpd_flush_data(w, q, ps, false));
1444 }
1445 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
1446}
1447
1448/*
1449 * rfc 2616: ยง3.6.1: Chunked Transfer Coding
1450 *
1451 * - All chunked extensions are stripped (support is optionnal)
1452 * - trailer headers are ignored, as:
1453 * + Clients must specifically ask for them (we won't)
1454 * + or ignoring them should not modify behaviour (so we do ignore them).
1455 */
1456static int httpd_parse_chunk_hdr(httpd_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
1457{
1458 httpd_query_t *q = dlist_last_entry(&w->query_list, httpd_query_t, query_link);
1459 const char *orig = ps->s;
1460 pstream_t line, hex;
1461 uint64_t len = 0;
1462 int res;
1463
1464 q->expect100cont = false;
1465 res = http_getline(ps, w->cfg->header_line_max, &line);
1466 if (res > 0) {
1467 return res;
1468 }
1469 if (res < 0) {
1470 goto cancel_query;
1471 }
1472 http_skipspaces(&line);
1473 hex = ps_get_span(&line, &ctype_ishexdigit);
1474 http_skipspaces(&line);
1475 if (unlikely(ps_len(&line)) != 0 && unlikely(line.s[0] != ';')) {
1476 goto cancel_query;
1477 }
1478 if (unlikely(ps_len(&hex) == 0) || unlikely(ps_len(&hex) > 16)) {
1479 goto cancel_query;
1480 }
1481 for (const char *s = hex.s; s < hex.s_end; s++)
1482 len = (len << 4) | __str_digit_value[*s + 128];
1483 w->chunk_length = len;
1484 w->state = len ? HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK : HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_TRAILER;
1485 q->received_body_length += ps->s - orig;
1486 return PARSE_OK;
1487
1488 cancel_query:
1489 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST, "Chunked header is unparseable");
1490 w->connection_close = true;
1491 httpd_query_done(w, q);
1492 return PARSE_ERROR;
1493}
1494
1495static int httpd_parse_chunk(httpd_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
1496{
1497 httpd_query_t *q = dlist_last_entry(&w->query_list, httpd_query_t, query_link);
1498 ssize_t plen = ps_len(ps);
1499
1500 assert (w->chunk_length >= 0);
1501 if (plen >= w->chunk_length + 2) {
1502 pstream_t tmp = __ps_get_ps(ps, w->chunk_length);
1503
1504 if (ps_skipstr(ps, "\r\n")) {
1505 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST, "Chunked header is unparseable");
1506 w->connection_close = true;
1507 httpd_query_done(w, q);
1508 return PARSE_ERROR;
1509 }
1510 RETHROW(httpd_flush_data(w, q, &tmp, false));
1511 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR;
1512 return PARSE_OK;
1513 }
1514 if (plen >= w->cfg->on_data_threshold) {
1515 RETHROW(httpd_flush_data(w, q, ps, false));
1516 }
1517 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
1518}
1519
1520static int httpd_parse_chunk_trailer(httpd_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
1521{
1522 httpd_query_t *q = dlist_last_entry(&w->query_list, httpd_query_t, query_link);
1523 const char *orig = ps->s;
1524 pstream_t line;
1525
1526 do {
1527 int res = (http_getline(ps, w->cfg->header_line_max, &line));
1528
1529 if (res < 0) {
1530 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST, "Trailer headers are unparseable");
1531 w->connection_close = true;
1532 httpd_query_done(w, q);
1533 return PARSE_ERROR;
1534 }
1535 if (res > 0) {
1536 return res;
1537 }
1538 } while (ps_len(&line));
1539
1540 q->received_body_length += ps->s - orig;
1541 if (q->on_done) {
1542 q->on_done(q);
1543 }
1544 httpd_query_done(w, q);
1545 return PARSE_OK;
1546}
1547
1548static int httpd_parse_close(httpd_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
1549{
1550 ps->b = ps->b_end;
1551 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
1552}
1553
1554
1555static int (*httpd_parsers[])(httpd_t *w, pstream_t *ps) = {
1556 [HTTP_PARSER_IDLE] = httpd_parse_idle,
1557 [HTTP_PARSER_BODY] = httpd_parse_body,
1558 [HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR] = httpd_parse_chunk_hdr,
1559 [HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK] = httpd_parse_chunk,
1560 [HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_TRAILER] = httpd_parse_chunk_trailer,
1561 [HTTP_PARSER_CLOSE] = httpd_parse_close,
1562};
1563
1564/* }}} */
1565/* HTTPD {{{ */
1566
1567httpd_cfg_t *httpd_cfg_init(httpd_cfg_t *cfg)
1568{
1569 core__httpd_cfg__t iop_cfg;
1570
1571 p_clear(cfg, 1);
1572
1573 dlist_init(&cfg->httpd_list);
1574 dlist_init(&cfg->http2_httpd_list);
1575 cfg->httpd_cls = obj_class(httpd);
1576
1577 iop_init(core__httpd_cfg, &iop_cfg);
1578 /* Default configuration must succeed. */
1579 httpd_cfg_from_iop(cfg, &iop_cfg);
1580
1581 for (int i = 0; i < countof(cfg->roots); i++) {
1582 qm_init_cached(http_path, &cfg->roots[i].childs);
1583 }
1584 return cfg;
1585}
1586
1587static void httpd_cfg_tls_wipe(httpd_cfg_t *cfg)
1588{
1589 if (cfg->ssl_ctx) {
1590 close_ssl_keylog_file();
1591 SSL_CTX_free(cfg->ssl_ctx);
1592 cfg->ssl_ctx = NULL;
1593 }
1594}
1595
1596static int
1597httpd_ssl_alpn_select_protocol_cb(SSL *ssl, const unsigned char **out,
1598 unsigned char *outlen,
1599 const unsigned char *in, unsigned int inlen,
1600 void *arg)
1601{
1602 http_mode_t mode = (intptr_t) arg;
1603 const byte *http2_found = NULL;
1604 const byte *http1_1_found = NULL;
1605 const byte *http1_0_found = NULL;
1606 bool look_for_h2 = mode == HTTP_MODE_USE_HTTP2_ONLY;
1607 pstream_t ps;
1608 const byte *chosen;
1609
1610 /* XXX: This cb is invoked for clients that propose multiple protocols
1611 * (e.g., h2, http/1.1). Currently, we don't support HTTP version
1612 * negotiation so, in HTTP/2 (TLS) mode, we look for h2 only. */
1613
1614 /* XXX: alpn protocol-list is a string of 8-bit length-prefixed byte
1615 * substrings. */
1616 ps = ps_init(in, inlen);
1617 while (!ps_done(&ps)) {
1618 int len = __ps_getc(&ps);
1619
1620 if (!ps_has(&ps, len)) {
1621 break;
1622 }
1623 if (look_for_h2) {
1624 if (len == 2 && ps_startswithstr(&ps, "h2")) {
1625 http2_found = ps.b - 1;
1626 break;
1627 }
1628 } else {
1629 /* look for http/1.x */
1630 if (len == 8 && ps_startswithstr(&ps, "http/1.1")) {
1631 http1_1_found = ps.b - 1;
1632 break;
1633 }
1634 if (len == 8 && ps_startswithstr(&ps, "http/1.0")) {
1635 http1_0_found = ps.b - 1;
1636 break;
1637 }
1638 }
1639 __ps_skip(&ps, len);
1640 }
1641 chosen = http2_found ?: http1_1_found ?: http1_0_found;
1642 if (chosen) {
1643 *out = chosen + 1;
1644 *outlen = *chosen;
1645 return SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_OK;
1646 }
1647 return SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_NOACK;
1648}
1649
1650
1651int httpd_cfg_from_iop(httpd_cfg_t *cfg, const core__httpd_cfg__t *iop_cfg)
1652{
1653 THROW_ERR_UNLESS(expect(!cfg->ssl_ctx));
1654 cfg->outbuf_max_size = iop_cfg->outbuf_max_size;
1655 cfg->pipeline_depth = iop_cfg->pipeline_depth;
1656 cfg->noact_delay = iop_cfg->noact_delay;
1657 cfg->max_queries = iop_cfg->max_queries;
1658 cfg->max_conns = iop_cfg->max_conns_in;
1659 cfg->on_data_threshold = iop_cfg->on_data_threshold;
1660 cfg->header_line_max = iop_cfg->header_line_max;
1661 cfg->header_size_max = iop_cfg->header_size_max;
1662
1663 if (iop_cfg->tls) {
1664 SSL_CTX *ctx;
1665 core__tls_cert_and_key__t *data;
1666 SB_1k(errbuf);
1667 int flags;
1668
1669 data = IOP_UNION_GET(core__tls_cfg, iop_cfg->tls, data);
1670 if (!data) {
1671 /* If a keyname has been provided in the configuration, it
1672 * should have been replaced by the actual TLS data. */
1673 logger_panic(&_G.logger, "TLS data are not provided");
1674 }
1675
1676 flags = iop_cfg->check_client_cert ? SSL_VERIFY_PEER |
1677 SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT: SSL_VERIFY_NONE;
1678
1679 ctx = ssl_ctx_new_tls(TLS_server_method(), data->key, data->cert,
1680 flags, NULL, &errbuf);
1681 httpd_cfg_set_ssl_ctx(cfg, ctx);
1682 if (!cfg->ssl_ctx) {
1683 logger_fatal(&_G.logger, "couldn't initialize SSL_CTX: %*pM",
1684 SB_FMT_ARG(&errbuf));
1685 }
1686
1687 if (iop_cfg->check_client_cert) {
1688 if (iop_cfg->ca_file.s) {
1689 char path[PATH_MAX] = "/tmp/tls-cert-XXXXXX";
1690 int ret;
1691
1692 ret = write_in_tmp_file(path, iop_cfg->ca_file.s,
1693 iop_cfg->ca_file.len, &errbuf);
1694 if (ret < 0) {
1695 httpd_cfg_tls_wipe(cfg);
1696 logger_error(&_G.logger,
1697 "tls: failed to dump certificate: %*pM",
1698 SB_FMT_ARG(&errbuf));
1699 return -1;
1700 }
1701
1702 ret = ssl_add_verify_file(cfg->ssl_ctx, LSTR(path));
1703 unlink(path);
1704
1705 if (ret < 0) {
1706 httpd_cfg_tls_wipe(cfg);
1707 logger_error(&_G.logger,
1708 "tls: failed to load certificate");
1709 return -1;
1710 }
1711 } else {
1712 SSL_CTX_set_default_verify_paths(cfg->ssl_ctx);
1713 }
1714 }
1715
1716#if OPENSSL_VERSION_IS(>,1,1,0)
1717 set_ssl_keylog_cb(cfg->ssl_ctx);
1718#endif
1719
1720 if (OPT_ISSET(iop_cfg->check_cert_depth)) {
1721 SSL_CTX_set_verify_depth(cfg->ssl_ctx,
1722 OPT_VAL(iop_cfg->check_cert_depth));
1723 }
1724 }
1725
1726 return 0;
1727}
1728
1729void httpd_cfg_wipe(httpd_cfg_t *cfg)
1730{
1731 for (int i = 0; i < countof(cfg->roots); i++) {
1732 httpd_trigger_node_wipe(&cfg->roots[i]);
1733 }
1734 httpd_cfg_tls_wipe(cfg);
1735 assert (dlist_is_empty(&cfg->httpd_list));
1736 assert (dlist_is_empty(&cfg->http2_httpd_list));
1737}
1738
1739void httpd_cfg_set_ssl_ctx(httpd_cfg_t *nonnull cfg, SSL_CTX *nullable ctx)
1740{
1741 httpd_cfg_tls_wipe(cfg);
1742
1743 cfg->ssl_ctx = ctx;
1744 if (ctx) {
1745 SSL_CTX_set_alpn_select_cb(cfg->ssl_ctx,
1746 &httpd_ssl_alpn_select_protocol_cb,
1747 (void *)cfg->mode);
1748 }
1749}
1750
1751static httpd_t *httpd_init(httpd_t *w)
1752{
1753 dlist_init(&w->query_list);
1754 dlist_init(&w->httpd_link);
1755 sb_init(&w->ibuf);
1756 ob_init(&w->ob);
1757 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_IDLE;
1758 return w;
1759}
1760
1761static void httpd_wipe(httpd_t *w)
1762{
1763 if (w->on_status) {
1764 va_list va;
1765
1766 dlist_for_each(it, &w->query_list) {
1767 httpd_notify_status(w, dlist_entry(it, httpd_query_t, query_link),
1768 HTTPD_QUERY_STATUS_CANCEL, "Query cancelled", va);
1769 }
1770 }
1771 if (w->on_disconnect) {
1772 (*w->on_disconnect)(w);
1773 }
1774 el_unregister(&w->ev);
1775 sb_wipe(&w->ibuf);
1776 ob_wipe(&w->ob);
1777 http_zlib_wipe(w);
1778 dlist_for_each(it, &w->query_list) {
1779 httpd_query_detach(dlist_entry(it, httpd_query_t, query_link));
1780 }
1781 w->cfg->nb_conns--;
1782 dlist_remove(&w->httpd_link);
1783 httpd_cfg_delete(&w->cfg);
1784 lstr_wipe(&w->peer_address);
1785 SSL_free(w->ssl);
1786 w->ssl = NULL;
1787}
1788
1789OBJ_VTABLE(httpd)
1790 httpd.init = httpd_init;
1791 httpd.wipe = httpd_wipe;
1792OBJ_VTABLE_END()
1793
1794void httpd_close_gently(httpd_t *w)
1795{
1796 w->connection_close = true;
1797 if (w->state == HTTP_PARSER_IDLE) {
1798 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_CLOSE;
1799 /* let the event loop maybe destroy us later, not now */
1800 el_fd_set_mask(w->ev, POLLOUT);
1801 }
1802}
1803
1804int t_httpd_qinfo_get_basic_auth(const httpd_qinfo_t *info,
1805 pstream_t *user, pstream_t *pw)
1806{
1807 for (int i = info->hdrs_len; i-- > 0; ) {
1808 const http_qhdr_t *hdr = info->hdrs + i;
1809 pstream_t v;
1810 char *colon;
1811 sb_t sb;
1812 int len;
1813
1814 if (hdr->wkhdr != HTTP_WKHDR_AUTHORIZATION) {
1815 continue;
1816 }
1817 v = hdr->val;
1818 ps_skipspaces(&v);
1819 PS_CHECK(ps_skipcasestr(&v, "basic"));
1820 ps_trim(&v);
1821
1822 len = ps_len(&v);
1823 t_sb_init(&sb, len + 1);
1824 PS_CHECK(sb_add_unb64(&sb, v.s, len));
1825 colon = strchr(sb.data, ':');
1826 if (!colon) {
1827 return -1;
1828 }
1829 *user = ps_initptr(sb.data, colon);
1830 *colon++ = '\0';
1831 *pw = ps_initptr(colon, sb_end(&sb));
1832 return 0;
1833 }
1834
1835 *pw = *user = ps_initptr(NULL, NULL);
1836 return 0;
1837}
1838
1839static int parse_qvalue(pstream_t *ps)
1840{
1841 int res;
1842
1843 /* is there a ';' ? */
1844 if (ps_skipc(ps, ';') < 0) {
1845 return 1000;
1846 }
1847 ps_skipspaces(ps);
1848
1849 /* parse q= */
1850 RETHROW(ps_skipc(ps, 'q'));
1851 ps_skipspaces(ps);
1852 RETHROW(ps_skipc(ps, '='));
1853 ps_skipspaces(ps);
1854
1855 /* slopily parse 1[.000] || 0[.nnn] */
1856 switch (ps_getc(ps)) {
1857 case '0': res = 0; break;
1858 case '1': res = 1; break;
1859 default:
1860 return -1;
1861 }
1862 if (ps_skipc(ps, '.') == 0) {
1863 for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
1864 if (ps_has(ps, 1) && isdigit(ps->s[0])) {
1865 res = 10 * res + __ps_getc(ps) - '0';
1866 } else {
1867 res *= 10;
1868 }
1869 }
1870 if (res > 1000) {
1871 res = 1000;
1872 }
1873 } else {
1874 res *= 1000;
1875 }
1876 ps_skipspaces(ps);
1877 return res;
1878}
1879
1880static int parse_accept_enc(pstream_t ps)
1881{
1882 int res_valid = 0, res_rej = 0, res_star = 0;
1883 int q;
1884 pstream_t v;
1885
1886 ps_skipspaces(&ps);
1887 while (!ps_done(&ps)) {
1888 bool is_star = false;
1889
1890 if (*ps.s == '*') {
1891 is_star = true;
1892 __ps_skip(&ps, 1);
1893 } else {
1894 v = ps_get_cspan(&ps, &http_non_token);
1895 }
1896 ps_skipspaces(&ps);
1897 q = RETHROW(parse_qvalue(&ps));
1898 switch (ps_getc(&ps)) {
1899 case ',':
1900 ps_skipspaces(&ps);
1901 break;
1902 case -1:
1903 break;
1904 default:
1905 return -1;
1906 }
1907
1908 if (is_star) {
1909 res_star = q ? HTTPD_ACCEPT_ENC_ANY : 0;
1910 } else {
1911 switch (http_get_token_ps(v)) {
1912 case HTTP_TK_X_GZIP:
1913 case HTTP_TK_GZIP:
1914 if (q) {
1915 res_valid |= HTTPD_ACCEPT_ENC_GZIP;
1916 } else {
1917 res_rej |= HTTPD_ACCEPT_ENC_GZIP;
1918 }
1919 break;
1920 case HTTP_TK_X_COMPRESS:
1921 case HTTP_TK_COMPRESS:
1922 if (q) {
1923 res_valid |= HTTPD_ACCEPT_ENC_COMPRESS;
1924 } else {
1925 res_rej |= HTTPD_ACCEPT_ENC_COMPRESS;
1926 }
1927 break;
1928 case HTTP_TK_DEFLATE:
1929 if (q) {
1930 res_valid |= HTTPD_ACCEPT_ENC_DEFLATE;
1931 } else {
1932 res_rej |= HTTPD_ACCEPT_ENC_DEFLATE;
1933 }
1934 break;
1935 default: /* Ignore "identity" or non RFC Accept-Encodings */
1936 break;
1937 }
1938 }
1939 }
1940
1941 return (res_valid | res_star) & ~res_rej;
1942}
1943
1944int httpd_qinfo_accept_enc_get(const httpd_qinfo_t *info)
1945{
1946 int res = 0;
1947
1948 for (int i = info->hdrs_len; i-- > 0; ) {
1949 const http_qhdr_t *hdr = info->hdrs + i;
1950
1951 if (hdr->wkhdr != HTTP_WKHDR_ACCEPT_ENCODING) {
1952 continue;
1953 }
1954
1955 if ((res = parse_accept_enc(hdr->val)) >= 0) {
1956 return res;
1957 }
1958 /* ignore malformed header */
1959 }
1960 return 0;
1961}
1962
1963static void httpd_do_any(httpd_t *w, httpd_query_t *q, httpd_qinfo_t *req)
1964{
1965 httpd_trigger_t *cb = q->trig_cb;
1966 pstream_t user, pw;
1967
1968 if (ps_memequal(&req->query, "*", 1)) {
1969 httpd_reject(q, NOT_FOUND, "'*' not found");
1970 return;
1971 }
1972
1973 if (cb) {
1974 if (cb->auth) {
1975 t_scope;
1976
1977 if (unlikely(t_httpd_qinfo_get_basic_auth(req, &user, &pw) < 0)) {
1978 httpd_reject(q, BAD_REQUEST, "invalid Authentication header");
1979 return;
1980 }
1981 (*cb->auth)(cb, q, user, pw);
1982 }
1983 if (likely(!q->answered)) {
1984 (*cb->cb)(cb, q, req);
1985 }
1986 } else {
1987 int method = req->method;
1988 lstr_t ms = http_method_str[method];
1989 httpd_trigger_node_t *n = &w->cfg->roots[method];
1990
1991 if (n->cb || qm_len(http_path, &n->childs)) {
1992 SB_1k(escaped);
1993
1994 sb_add_lstr_xmlescape(&escaped, LSTR_PS_V(&req->query));
1995 httpd_reject(q, NOT_FOUND,
1996 "%*pM %*pM HTTP/1.%d", LSTR_FMT_ARG(ms),
1997 SB_FMT_ARG(&escaped),
1998 HTTP_MINOR(req->http_version));
1999 } else
2000 if (method == HTTP_METHOD_OPTIONS) {
2001 /* For CORS purposes, handle OPTIONS if not handled above */
2002 outbuf_t *ob = httpd_reply_hdrs_start(q, HTTP_CODE_NO_CONTENT,
2003 false);
2004
2005 ob_adds(ob, "Access-Control-Allow-Methods: "
2006 "POST, GET, OPTIONS\r\n");
2007 ob_adds(ob, "Access-Control-Allow-Headers: "
2008 "Authorization, Content-Type\r\n");
2009
2010 httpd_reply_hdrs_done(q, 0, false);
2011 httpd_reply_done(q);
2012 } else {
2013 httpd_reject(q, NOT_IMPLEMENTED,
2014 "no handler for %*pM", LSTR_FMT_ARG(ms));
2015 }
2016 }
2017}
2018
2019static void httpd_do_trace(httpd_t *w, httpd_query_t *q, httpd_qinfo_t *req)
2020{
2021 httpd_reject(q, METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED, "TRACE method is not allowed");
2022}
2023
2024static void httpd_do_close(httpd_t **wp)
2025{
2026 httpd_t *w = *wp;
2027 if (!dlist_is_empty(&w->query_list)) {
2028 httpd_query_t *q;
2029 q = dlist_last_entry(&w->query_list, httpd_query_t, query_link);
2030 if (!q->parsed) {
2031 obj_release(&q);
2032 if (!q->answered) {
2033 obj_release(&q);
2034 }
2035 }
2036 }
2037 obj_delete(wp);
2038}
2039
2040static int httpd_on_event(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
2041{
2042 httpd_t *w = priv.ptr;
2043 pstream_t ps;
2044
2045 if (events == EL_EVENTS_NOACT) {
2046 goto close;
2047 }
2048
2049 if (events & POLLIN) {
2050 int ret;
2051
2052 ret = w->ssl ?
2053 ssl_sb_read(&w->ibuf, w->ssl, 0):
2054 sb_read(&w->ibuf, fd, 0);
2055 if (ret <= 0) {
2056 if (ret == 0 || !ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
2057 goto close;
2058 }
2059 goto write;
2060 }
2061
2062 ps = ps_initsb(&w->ibuf);
2063 do {
2064 ret = (*httpd_parsers[w->state])(w, &ps);
2065 } while (ret == PARSE_OK);
2066 sb_skip_upto(&w->ibuf, ps.s);
2067 }
2068
2069 write:
2070 {
2071 int oldlen = w->ob.length;
2072 int ret;
2073
2074 ret = w->ssl ?
2075 ob_write_with(&w->ob, fd, ssl_writev, w->ssl) :
2076 ob_write(&w->ob, fd);
2077 if (ret < 0 && !ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
2078 goto close;
2079 }
2080
2081 if (!dlist_is_empty(&w->query_list)) {
2082 httpd_query_t *query = dlist_first_entry(&w->query_list,
2083 httpd_query_t, query_link);
2084 if (!query->answered && query->on_ready != NULL
2085 && oldlen >= query->ready_threshold
2086 && w->ob.length < query->ready_threshold) {
2087 (*query->on_ready)(query);
2088 }
2089 }
2090 }
2091
2092 if (unlikely(w->state == HTTP_PARSER_CLOSE)) {
2093 if (w->queries == 0 && ob_is_empty(&w->ob)) {
2094 /* XXX We call shutdown(โฆ, SHUT_RW) to force TCP to flush our
2095 * writing buffer and protect our responses against a TCP RST
2096 * which could be emitted by close() if there is some pending data
2097 * in the read buffer (think about pipelining). */
2098 shutdown(fd, SHUT_WR);
2099 goto close;
2100 }
2101 } else {
2102 /* w->state == HTTP_PARSER_IDLE:
2103 * queries > 0 means pending answer, client isn't lagging, we are.
2104 *
2105 * w->state != HTTP_PARSER_IDLE:
2106 * queries is always > 0: the query being parsed has been created.
2107 * So for this case, pending requests without answers exist iff
2108 * queries > 1.
2109 */
2110 if (w->queries > (w->state != HTTP_PARSER_IDLE)) {
2111 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, 0);
2112 } else
2113 if (ob_is_empty(&w->ob)) {
2114 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, w->cfg->noact_delay);
2115 }
2116 }
2117 httpd_set_mask(w);
2118 return 0;
2119
2120 close:
2121 httpd_do_close(&w);
2122 return 0;
2123}
2124
2125static int
2126httpd_tls_handshake(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
2127{
2128 httpd_t *w = priv.ptr;
2129
2130 switch (ssl_do_handshake(w->ssl, evh, fd, NULL)) {
2131 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_SUCCESS:
2132 el_fd_set_mask(evh, POLLIN);
2133 el_fd_set_hook(evh, httpd_on_event);
2134 break;
2135 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_PENDING:
2136 break;
2137 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_CLOSED:
2138 obj_delete(&w);
2139 break;
2140 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_ERROR:
2141 obj_delete(&w);
2142 return -1;
2143 }
2144
2145 return 0;
2146}
2147
2148static int
2149httpd_spawn_as_http2(int sockfd, sockunion_t *peer_su, httpd_cfg_t *cfg);
2150
2151static int httpd_on_accept(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
2152{
2153 httpd_cfg_t *cfg = priv.ptr;
2154 int sock;
2155 sockunion_t su;
2156
2157 while ((sock = acceptx_get_addr(fd, O_NONBLOCK, &su)) >= 0) {
2158 if (cfg->nb_conns >= cfg->max_conns) {
2159 close(sock);
2160 } else if (cfg->mode == HTTP_MODE_USE_HTTP2_ONLY) {
2161 return httpd_spawn_as_http2(sock, &su, cfg);
2162 } else {
2163 httpd_spawn(sock, cfg)->peer_su = su;
2164 }
2165 }
2166 return 0;
2167}
2168
2169el_t httpd_listen(sockunion_t *su, httpd_cfg_t *cfg)
2170{
2171 int fd;
2172
2173 fd = listenx(-1, su, 1, SOCK_STREAM, IPPROTO_TCP, O_NONBLOCK);
2174 if (fd < 0) {
2175 return NULL;
2176 }
2177 return el_fd_register(fd, true, POLLIN, httpd_on_accept,
2178 httpd_cfg_retain(cfg));
2179}
2180
2181static void http2_close_servers(httpd_cfg_t *cfg);
2182
2183void httpd_unlisten(el_t *ev)
2184{
2185 if (*ev) {
2186 httpd_cfg_t *cfg = el_unregister(ev).ptr;
2187
2188 dlist_for_each(it, &cfg->httpd_list) {
2189 httpd_close_gently(dlist_entry(it, httpd_t, httpd_link));
2190 }
2191 http2_close_servers(cfg);
2192 httpd_cfg_delete(&cfg);
2193 }
2194}
2195
2196httpd_t *httpd_spawn(int fd, httpd_cfg_t *cfg)
2197{
2198 httpd_t *w = obj_new_of_class(httpd, cfg->httpd_cls);
2199 el_fd_f *el_cb = cfg->ssl_ctx ? &httpd_tls_handshake : &httpd_on_event;
2200
2201 cfg->nb_conns++;
2202 w->cfg = httpd_cfg_retain(cfg);
2203 w->ev = el_fd_register(fd, true, POLLIN, el_cb, w);
2204 w->max_queries = cfg->max_queries;
2205 if (cfg->ssl_ctx) {
2206 w->ssl = SSL_new(cfg->ssl_ctx);
2207 assert (w->ssl);
2208 SSL_set_fd(w->ssl, fd);
2209 SSL_set_accept_state(w->ssl);
2210 }
2211
2212 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, w->cfg->noact_delay);
2213 dlist_add_tail(&cfg->httpd_list, &w->httpd_link);
2214 if (w->on_accept) {
2215 (*w->on_accept)(w);
2216 }
2217 return w;
2218}

2220lstr_t httpd_get_peer_address(httpd_t * w)

2222 if (!w->peer_address.len) {
2223 t_scope;
2224
2225 w->peer_address = lstr_dup(t_addr_fmt_lstr(&w->peer_su));
2226 }
2227
2228 return lstr_dupc(w->peer_address);
2229}

2233
2234static httpc_qinfo_t *httpc_qinfo_dup(const httpc_qinfo_t *info)
2235{
2236 httpc_qinfo_t *res;
2237 size_t len = sizeof(info);
2238 void *p;
2239 intptr_t offs;
2240
2241 len += sizeof(info->hdrs[0]) * info->hdrs_len;
2242 len += ps_len(&info->reason);
2243 len += ps_len(&info->hdrs_ps);
2244
2245 res = p_new_extra(httpc_qinfo_t, len);
2246 memcpy(res, info, offsetof(httpc_qinfo_t, hdrs_ps));
2247 res->hdrs = (void *)&res[1];
2248 p = res->hdrs + res->hdrs_len;
2249 res->reason.s = p;
2250 res->reason.s_end = p = mempcpy(p, info->reason.s, ps_len(&info->reason));
2251 res->hdrs_ps.s = p;
2252 res->hdrs_ps.s_end = mempcpy(p, info->hdrs_ps.s, ps_len(&info->hdrs_ps));
2253
2254 offs = res->hdrs_ps.s - info->hdrs_ps.s;
2255 for (int i = 0; i < res->hdrs_len; i++) {
2256 http_qhdr_t *lhs = &res->hdrs[i];
2257 const http_qhdr_t *rhs = &info->hdrs[i];
2258
2259 lhs->wkhdr = rhs->wkhdr;
2260 lhs->key = ps_initptr(rhs->key.s + offs, rhs->key.s_end + offs);
2261 lhs->val = ps_initptr(rhs->val.s + offs, rhs->val.s_end + offs);
2262 }
2263 return res;
2264}
2265
2266static void httpc_trace_query_on_done(httpc_query_t *q)
2267{
2268 if (!q->qinfo || !logger_is_traced(&_G.logger, 1)) {
2269 return;
2270 }
2271
2272 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 1, "reason of answer on client's side: `%*pM`",
2273 PS_FMT_ARG(&q->qinfo->reason));
2274
2275 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 2, "header of answer on client's side:\n%*pM",
2276 PS_FMT_ARG(&q->qinfo->hdrs_ps));
2277
2278 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 3, "payload on client's side:\n%*pM",
2279 SB_FMT_ARG(&q->payload));
2280}
2281
2282static void httpc_query_on_done(httpc_query_t *q, int status)
2283{
2284 httpc_t *w = q->owner;
2285
2286 if (w) {
2287 if (--w->queries < w->cfg->pipeline_depth && w->max_queries && w->busy) {
2288 obj_vcall(w, set_ready, false);
2289 }
2290 q->owner = NULL;
2291 }
2292 dlist_remove(&q->query_link);
2293 httpc_trace_query_on_done(q);
2294 /* XXX: call the httpc_t's notifier first to ensure qinfo is still set */
2295 if (w && w->on_query_done) {
2296 (*w->on_query_done)(w, q, status);
2297 }
2298 (*q->on_done)(q, status);
2299}
2300#define httpc_query_abort(q) httpc_query_on_done(q, HTTPC_STATUS_ABORT)
2301
2302static int httpc_query_ok(httpc_query_t *q)
2303{
2304 httpc_t *w = q->owner;
2305
2306 httpc_query_on_done(q, HTTPC_STATUS_OK);
2307 if (w) {
2308 w->chunk_length = 0;
2309 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_IDLE;
2310 }
2311 return PARSE_OK;
2312}
2313
2314static inline void httpc_qinfo_delete(httpc_qinfo_t **infop)
2315{
2316 p_delete(infop);
2317}
2318
2319static int httpc_parse_idle(httpc_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
2320{
2321 t_scope;
2322 size_t start = w->chunk_length > 4 ? w->chunk_length - 4 : 0;
2323 httpc_qinfo_t req;
2324 const uint8_t *p;
2325 pstream_t buf;
2326 qv_t(qhdr) hdrs;
2327 httpc_query_t *q;
2328 bool chunked = false, conn_close = false;
2329 int clen = -1, res;
2330
2331 if (ps_len(ps) > 0 && dlist_is_empty(&w->query_list)) {
2332 logger_trace(&_G.logger, 0, "UHOH spurious data from the HTTP "
2333 "server: %*pM", (int)ps_len(ps), ps->s);
2334 return PARSE_ERROR;
2335 }
2336
2337 if ((p = memmem(ps->s + start, ps_len(ps) - start, "\r\n\r\n", 4)) == NULL) {
2338 if (ps_len(ps) > w->cfg->header_size_max) {
2339 return PARSE_ERROR;
2340 }
2341 w->chunk_length = ps_len(ps);
2342 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
2343 }
2344
2345 http_zlib_reset(w);
2346 req.hdrs_ps = ps_initptr(ps->s, p + 4);
2347 res = http_parse_status_line(ps, w->cfg->header_line_max, &req);
2348 if (res) {
2349 return res;
2350 }
2351
2352 buf = __ps_get_ps_upto(ps, p + 2);
2353 __ps_skip_upto(ps, p + 4);
2354 t_qv_init(&hdrs, 64);
2355
2356 while (!ps_done(&buf)) {
2357 http_qhdr_t *qhdr = qv_growlen(&hdrs, 1);
2358
2359 /* TODO: normalize, make "lists" */
2360 qhdr->key = ps_get_cspan(&buf, &http_non_token);
2361 if (ps_len(&qhdr->key) == 0 || __ps_getc(&buf) != ':') {
2362 return PARSE_ERROR;
2363 }
2364 qhdr->val.s = buf.s;
2365 for (;;) {
2366 ps_skip_afterchr(&buf, '\r');
2367 if (__ps_getc(&buf) != '\n') {
2368 return PARSE_ERROR;
2369 }
2370 qhdr->val.s_end = buf.s - 2;
2371 if (ps_done(&buf)) {
2372 break;
2373 }
2374 if (buf.s[0] != '\t' && buf.s[0] != ' ') {
2375 break;
2376 }
2377 __ps_skip(&buf, 1);
2378 }
2379 ps_trim(&qhdr->val);
2380
2381 switch ((qhdr->wkhdr = http_wkhdr_from_ps(qhdr->key))) {
2382 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONNECTION:
2383 conn_close |= http_hdr_contains(qhdr->val, "close");
2384 w->connection_close |= conn_close;
2385 break;
2386
2387 case HTTP_WKHDR_TRANSFER_ENCODING:
2388 /* rfc 2616: ยง4.4: != "identity" means chunked encoding */
2389 switch (http_get_token_ps(qhdr->val)) {
2390 case HTTP_TK_IDENTITY:
2391 chunked = false;
2392 break;
2393 case HTTP_TK_CHUNKED:
2394 chunked = true;
2395 break;
2396 default:
2397 return PARSE_ERROR;
2398 }
2399 break;
2400
2401 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONTENT_LENGTH:
2402 clen = memtoip(qhdr->val.b, ps_len(&qhdr->val), &p);
2403 if (p != qhdr->val.b_end) {
2404 return PARSE_ERROR;
2405 }
2406 break;
2407
2408 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONTENT_ENCODING:
2409 switch (http_get_token_ps(qhdr->val)) {
2410 case HTTP_TK_DEFLATE:
2411 case HTTP_TK_GZIP:
2412 case HTTP_TK_X_GZIP:
2413 http_zlib_inflate_init(w);
2414 qv_shrink(&hdrs, 1);
2415 break;
2416 default:
2417 http_zlib_reset(w);
2418 break;
2419 }
2420 break;
2421
2422 default:
2423 break;
2424 }
2425 }
2426
2427 if (chunked) {
2428 /* rfc 2616: ยง4.4: if chunked, then ignore any Content-Length */
2429 w->chunk_length = 0;
2430 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR;
2431 } else {
2432 /* rfc 2616: ยง4.4: support no Content-Length */
2433 if (clen < 0 && req.code == HTTP_CODE_NO_CONTENT) {
2434 /* due to code 204 (No Content) */
2435 w->chunk_length = 0;
2436 } else {
2437 /* or followed by close */
2438 w->chunk_length = clen;
2439 }
2440 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_BODY;
2441 }
2442 req.hdrs = hdrs.tab;
2443 req.hdrs_len = hdrs.len;
2444
2445 q = dlist_first_entry(&w->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
2446
2447 if (req.code >= 100 && req.code < 200) {
2448 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_IDLE;
2449
2450 /* rfc 2616: ยง10.1: A client MUST be prepared to accept one or more
2451 * 1xx status responses prior to a regular response.
2452 *
2453 * Since HTTP/1.0 did not define any 1xx status codes, servers MUST
2454 * NOT send a 1xx response to an HTTP/1.0 client except under
2455 * experimental conditions
2456 */
2457 if (req.http_version == HTTP_1_0) {
2458 return PARSE_ERROR;
2459 } else
2460 if (req.code != HTTP_CODE_CONTINUE) {
2461 return PARSE_OK;
2462 }
2463
2464 if (q->expect100cont) {
2465 /* Temporary set the qinfo to the 100 Continue header.
2466 */
2467 q->qinfo = &req;
2468 (*q->on_100cont)(q);
2469 q->qinfo = NULL;
2470 }
2471 q->expect100cont = false;
2472
2473 return PARSE_OK;
2474 }
2475
2476 if (q->expect100cont && (req.code >= 200 && req.code < 300)) {
2477 return HTTPC_STATUS_EXP100CONT;
2478 }
2479
2480 q->received_hdr_length = ps_len(&req.hdrs_ps);
2481 q->qinfo = httpc_qinfo_dup(&req);
2482 if (q->on_hdrs) {
2483 RETHROW((*q->on_hdrs)(q));
2484 }
2485 if (conn_close) {
2486 w->max_queries = 0;
2487 if (!w->busy) {
2488 obj_vcall(w, set_busy);
2489 }
2490 dlist_for_each_entry_continue(q, &w->query_list, query_link)
2491 {
2492 httpc_query_abort(q);
2493 }
2494 ob_wipe(&w->ob);
2495 ob_init(&w->ob);
2496 }
2497
2498 return PARSE_OK;
2499}
2500
2501static inline int
2502httpc_flush_data(httpc_t *w, httpc_query_t *q, pstream_t *ps, bool done)
2503{
2504 q->received_body_length += ps_len(ps);
2505
2506 if (w->compressed && !ps_done(ps)) {
2507 t_scope;
2508 sb_t zbuf;
2509
2510 t_sb_init(&zbuf, HTTP_ZLIB_BUFSIZ);
2511 if (http_zlib_inflate(&w->zs, &w->chunk_length, &zbuf, ps, done)) {
2512 return PARSE_ERROR;
2513 }
2514 RETHROW(q->on_data(q, ps_initsb(&zbuf)));
2515 } else {
2516 RETHROW(q->on_data(q, *ps));
2517 if (w->chunk_length >= 0) {
2518 w->chunk_length -= ps_len(ps);
2519 }
2520 ps->b = ps->b_end;
2521 }
2522 return PARSE_OK;
2523}
2524
2525static int httpc_parse_body(httpc_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
2526{
2527 httpc_query_t *q = dlist_first_entry(&w->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
2528 ssize_t plen = ps_len(ps);
2529
2530 if (plen >= w->chunk_length && w->chunk_length >= 0) {
2531 pstream_t tmp = __ps_get_ps(ps, w->chunk_length);
2532
2533 RETHROW(httpc_flush_data(w, q, &tmp, true));
2534 return httpc_query_ok(q);
2535 }
2536 if (plen >= w->cfg->on_data_threshold) {
2537 RETHROW(httpc_flush_data(w, q, ps, false));
2538 }
2539 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
2540}
2541
2542static int httpc_parse_chunk_hdr(httpc_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
2543{
2544 httpc_query_t *q = dlist_first_entry(&w->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
2545 const char *orig = ps->s;
2546 pstream_t line, hex;
2547 uint64_t len = 0;
2548 int res;
2549
2550 res = http_getline(ps, w->cfg->header_line_max, &line);
2551 if (res) {
2552 return res;
2553 }
2554 http_skipspaces(&line);
2555 hex = ps_get_span(&line, &ctype_ishexdigit);
2556 http_skipspaces(&line);
2557 if (unlikely(ps_len(&line)) != 0 && unlikely(line.s[0] != ';')) {
2558 return PARSE_ERROR;
2559 }
2560 if (unlikely(ps_len(&hex) == 0) || unlikely(ps_len(&hex) > 16)) {
2561 return PARSE_ERROR;
2562 }
2563 for (const char *s = hex.s; s < hex.s_end; s++)
2564 len = (len << 4) | __str_digit_value[*s + 128];
2565 w->chunk_length = len;
2566 w->state = len ? HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK : HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_TRAILER;
2567 q->received_body_length += ps->s - orig;
2568 return PARSE_OK;
2569}
2570
2571static int httpc_parse_chunk(httpc_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
2572{
2573 httpc_query_t *q = dlist_first_entry(&w->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
2574 ssize_t plen = ps_len(ps);
2575
2576 assert (w->chunk_length >= 0);
2577 if (plen >= w->chunk_length + 2) {
2578 pstream_t tmp = __ps_get_ps(ps, w->chunk_length);
2579
2580 if (ps_skipstr(ps, "\r\n")) {
2581 return PARSE_ERROR;
2582 }
2583 RETHROW(httpc_flush_data(w, q, &tmp, false));
2584 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR;
2585 return PARSE_OK;
2586 }
2587 if (plen >= w->cfg->on_data_threshold) {
2588 RETHROW(httpc_flush_data(w, q, ps, false));
2589 }
2590 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
2591}
2592
2593static int httpc_parse_chunk_trailer(httpc_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
2594{
2595 httpc_query_t *q = dlist_first_entry(&w->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
2596 const char *orig = ps->s;
2597 pstream_t line;
2598
2599 do {
2600 int res = http_getline(ps, w->cfg->header_line_max, &line);
2601
2602 if (res) {
2603 return res;
2604 }
2605 } while (ps_len(&line));
2606
2607 q->received_body_length += ps->s - orig;
2608 return httpc_query_ok(q);
2609}
2610
2611static int (*httpc_parsers[])(httpc_t *w, pstream_t *ps) = {
2612 [HTTP_PARSER_IDLE] = httpc_parse_idle,
2613 [HTTP_PARSER_BODY] = httpc_parse_body,
2614 [HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR] = httpc_parse_chunk_hdr,
2615 [HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK] = httpc_parse_chunk,
2616 [HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_TRAILER] = httpc_parse_chunk_trailer,
2617};

2622int httpc_cfg_tls_init(httpc_cfg_t *cfg, sb_t *err)
2623{
2624 SSL_CTX *ctx;
2625 int flags;
2626
2627 assert (cfg->ssl_ctx == NULL);
2628
2629 flags = cfg->check_server_cert ? SSL_VERIFY_PEER: SSL_VERIFY_NONE;
2630 ctx = ssl_ctx_new_tls(TLS_client_method(), cfg->client_tls_key,
2631 cfg->client_tls_cert, flags, NULL, err);
2632
2633 httpc_cfg_set_ssl_ctx(cfg, ctx);
2634 return cfg->ssl_ctx ? 0 : -1;
2635}

2637void httpc_cfg_tls_wipe(httpc_cfg_t *cfg)
2638{
2639 if (cfg->ssl_ctx) {
2640 close_ssl_keylog_file();
2641 SSL_CTX_free(cfg->ssl_ctx);
2642 cfg->ssl_ctx = NULL;
2643 }
2644}
