2649}
2650
2651httpc_cfg_t *httpc_cfg_init(httpc_cfg_t *cfg)
2652{
2653 core__httpc_cfg__t iop_cfg;
2654
2655 p_clear(cfg, 1);
2656
2657 cfg->httpc_cls = obj_class(httpc);
2658 iop_init(core__httpc_cfg, &iop_cfg);
2659 /* Default configuration cannot fail */
2660 IGNORE(httpc_cfg_from_iop(cfg, &iop_cfg));
2661
2662 return cfg;
2663}
2664
2665int httpc_cfg_from_iop(httpc_cfg_t *cfg, const core__httpc_cfg__t *iop_cfg)
2666{
2667 cfg->pipeline_depth = iop_cfg->pipeline_depth;
2668 cfg->noact_delay = iop_cfg->noact_delay;
2669 cfg->max_queries = iop_cfg->max_queries;
2670 cfg->on_data_threshold = iop_cfg->on_data_threshold;
2671 cfg->header_line_max = iop_cfg->header_line_max;
2672 cfg->header_size_max = iop_cfg->header_size_max;
2673
2674 /* TODO: remove the http_mode enum and use flag(s) instead. */
2675 if (iop_cfg->use_http2) {
2676 cfg->http_mode = HTTP_MODE_USE_HTTP2_ONLY;
2677 }
2678
2679 if (iop_cfg->tls_on) {
2680 SB_1k(err);
2681 core__tls_cert_and_key__t *data;
2682
2683 if (iop_cfg->tls_client) {
2684 data = IOP_UNION_GET(core__tls_cfg, iop_cfg->tls_client, data);
2685 if (!data) {
2686 /* If a keyname has been provided in the configuration, it
2687 * should have been replaced by the actual TLS data. */
2688 logger_panic(&_G.logger, "mTLS client data are not provided");
2689 }
2690 cfg->client_tls_cert = lstr_dup(data->cert);
2691 cfg->client_tls_key = lstr_dup(data->key);
2692 }
2693
2694 cfg->check_server_cert = iop_cfg->check_server_cert;
2695
2696 if (httpc_cfg_tls_init(cfg, &err) < 0) {
2697 logger_error(&_G.logger, "tls: init: %*pM", SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
2698 return -1;
2699 }
2700
2701 if (cfg->check_server_cert) {
2702 if (iop_cfg->tls_cert.s) {
2703 char path[PATH_MAX] = "/tmp/tls-cert-XXXXXX";
2704 int ret;
2705
2706 ret = write_in_tmp_file(path, iop_cfg->tls_cert.s,
2707 iop_cfg->tls_cert.len, &err);
2708 if (ret < 0) {
2709 httpc_cfg_tls_wipe(cfg);
2710 logger_error(&_G.logger, "tls: failed to dump certificate: "
2711 "%*pM", SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
2712 return -1;
2713 }
2714
2715 ret = ssl_add_verify_file(cfg->ssl_ctx, LSTR(path));
2716 unlink(path);
2717
2718 if (ret < 0) {
2719 httpc_cfg_tls_wipe(cfg);
2720 logger_error(&_G.logger, "tls: failed to load certificate");
2721 return -1;
2722 }
2723 } else {
2724 SSL_CTX_set_default_verify_paths(cfg->ssl_ctx);
2725 }
2726 }
2727
2728#if OPENSSL_VERSION_IS(>,1,1,0)
2729 set_ssl_keylog_cb(cfg->ssl_ctx);
2730#endif
2731
2732 if (OPT_ISSET(iop_cfg->check_cert_depth)) {
2733 SSL_CTX_set_verify_depth(cfg->ssl_ctx,
2734 OPT_VAL(iop_cfg->check_cert_depth));
2735 }
2736 }
2737
2738 return 0;
2739}
2740
2741void httpc_cfg_wipe(httpc_cfg_t *cfg)
2742{
2743 lstr_wipe(&cfg->client_tls_cert);
2744 lstr_wipe(&cfg->client_tls_key);
2745
2746 httpc_close_http2_pool(cfg);
2747 httpc_cfg_tls_wipe(cfg);
2748}
2749
2750void httpc_cfg_set_ssl_ctx(httpc_cfg_t *nonnull cfg, SSL_CTX *nullable ctx)
2751{
2752 httpc_cfg_tls_wipe(cfg);
2753 cfg->ssl_ctx = ctx;
2754 /* XXX: Currently, we only propose h2 protocol in HTTP/2 (TLS) mode */
2755 if (ctx && cfg->http_mode == HTTP_MODE_USE_HTTP2_ONLY) {
2756 const byte alpn[] = "\x02h2";
2757 unsigned int alpnlen = strlen((char *) alpn);
2758
2759 if (SSL_CTX_set_alpn_protos(cfg->ssl_ctx, alpn, alpnlen) != 0) {
2760 logger_error(&_G.logger, "unable to set SSL ALPN protocols");
2761 }
2762 }
2763}
2764
2765httpc_pool_t *httpc_pool_init(httpc_pool_t *pool)
2766{
2767 p_clear(pool, 1);
2768 dlist_init(&pool->ready_list);
2769 dlist_init(&pool->busy_list);
2770 return pool;
2771}
2772
2773void httpc_pool_close_clients(httpc_pool_t *pool)
2774{
2775 dlist_t lst = DLIST_INIT(lst);
2776
2777 dlist_splice(&lst, &pool->busy_list);
2778 dlist_splice(&lst, &pool->ready_list);
2779 dlist_for_each_entry(httpc_t, w, &lst, pool_link) {
2780 obj_release(&w);
2781 }
2782}
2783
2784void httpc_pool_wipe(httpc_pool_t *pool, bool wipe_conns)
2785{
2786 dlist_t l = DLIST_INIT(l);
2787
2788 dlist_splice(&l, &pool->busy_list);
2789 dlist_splice(&l, &pool->ready_list);
2790 dlist_for_each_entry(httpc_t, w, &l, pool_link) {
2791 if (wipe_conns) {
2792 obj_release(&w);
2793 } else {
2794 httpc_pool_detach(w);
2795 }
2796 }
2797 lstr_wipe(&pool->name);
2798 lstr_wipe(&pool->host);
2799 httpc_cfg_delete(&pool->cfg);
2800}
2801
2802void httpc_pool_detach(httpc_t *w)
2803{
2804 if (w->pool) {
2805 w->pool->len--;
2806 if (w->pool->len_global) {
2807 (*w->pool->len_global)--;
2808 }
2809 dlist_remove(&w->pool_link);
2810 w->pool = NULL;
2811 }
2812}
2813
2814void httpc_pool_attach(httpc_t *w, httpc_pool_t *pool)
2815{
2816 httpc_pool_detach(w);
2817 w->pool = pool;
2818 pool->len++;
2819 if (pool->len_global) {
2820 (*pool->len_global)++;
2821 }
2822 if (w->busy) {
2823 dlist_add(&pool->busy_list, &w->pool_link);
2824 if (pool->on_busy) {
2825 (*pool->on_busy)(pool, w);
2826 }
2827 } else {
2828 dlist_add(&pool->ready_list, &w->pool_link);
2829 if (pool->on_ready) {
2830 (*pool->on_ready)(pool, w);
2831 }
2832 }
2833}
2834
2835httpc_t *httpc_pool_launch(httpc_pool_t *pool)
2836{
2837 if (pool->resolve_on_connect) {
2838 SB_1k(err);
2839 const char *what = pool->name.s ?: "httpc pool";
2840
2841 assert(pool->host.s);
2842 if (addr_resolve_with_err(what, pool->host, &pool->su, &err) < 0) {
2843 logger_warning(&_G.logger, "%pL", &err);
2844 return NULL;
2845 }
2846 }
2847
2848 return httpc_connect_as(&pool->su, pool->su_src, pool->cfg, pool);
2849}
2850
2851static inline bool httpc_pool_reach_limit(httpc_pool_t *pool)
2852{
2853 return (pool->len >= pool->max_len ||
2854 (pool->len_global && *pool->len_global >= pool->max_len_global));
2855}
2856
2857httpc_t *httpc_pool_get(httpc_pool_t *pool)
2858{
2859 httpc_t *httpc;
2860
2861 if (!httpc_pool_has_ready(pool)) {
2862 if (httpc_pool_reach_limit(pool)) {
2863 return NULL;
2864 }
2865 httpc = RETHROW_P(httpc_pool_launch(pool));
2866 /* As we are establishing the connection, busy will be true until it
2867 * is connected. Thus, we will always return NULL here unless you
2868 * force this flag to false in the on_busy callback for some specific
2869 * reasons. */
2870 return httpc->busy ? NULL : httpc;
2871 }
2872
2873 httpc = dlist_first_entry(&pool->ready_list, httpc_t, pool_link);
2874 dlist_move_tail(&pool->ready_list, &httpc->pool_link);
2875 return httpc;
2876}
2877
2878bool httpc_pool_has_ready(httpc_pool_t * nonnull pool)
2879{
2880 return !dlist_is_empty(&pool->ready_list);
2881}
2882
2883bool httpc_pool_can_query(httpc_pool_t * nonnull pool)
2884{
2885 return httpc_pool_has_ready(pool) || !httpc_pool_reach_limit(pool);
2886}
2887
2888static httpc_t *httpc_init(httpc_t *w)
2889{
2890 dlist_init(&w->query_list);
2891 sb_init(&w->ibuf);
2892 ob_init(&w->ob);
2893 w->state = HTTP_PARSER_IDLE;
2894 return w;
2895}
2896
2897static void httpc_disconnect_as_http2(httpc_t *w);
2898static void httpc_http2_ctx_delete(httpc_http2_ctx_t **ctx);
2899
2900static void httpc_wipe(httpc_t *w)
2901{
2902 if (w->ev || w->http2_ctx) {
2903 obj_vcall(w, disconnect);
2904 }
2905 httpc_http2_ctx_delete(&w->http2_ctx);
2906 sb_wipe(&w->ibuf);
2907 http_zlib_wipe(w);
2908 ob_wipe(&w->ob);
2909 httpc_cfg_delete(&w->cfg);
2910 SSL_free(w->ssl);
2911}
2912
2913static void httpc_disconnect(httpc_t *w)
2914{
2915 if (w->connected_as_http2) {
2916 httpc_disconnect_as_http2(w);
2917 }
2918 httpc_pool_detach(w);
2919 el_unregister(&w->ev);
2920 dlist_for_each(it, &w->query_list) {
2921 httpc_query_abort(dlist_entry(it, httpc_query_t, query_link));
2922 }
2923}
2924
2925static void httpc_set_ready(httpc_t *w, bool first)
2926{
2927 httpc_pool_t *pool = w->pool;
2928
2929 assert (w->busy);
2930 w->busy = false;
2931 if (pool) {
2932 dlist_move(&pool->ready_list, &w->pool_link);
2933 if (pool->on_ready) {
2934 (*pool->on_ready)(pool, w);
2935 }
2936 }
2937}
2938
2939static void httpc_set_busy(httpc_t *w)
2940{
2941 httpc_pool_t *pool = w->pool;
2942
2943 assert (!w->busy);
2944 w->busy = true;
2945 if (pool) {
2946 dlist_move(&pool->busy_list, &w->pool_link);
2947 if (pool->on_busy) {
2948 (*pool->on_busy)(pool, w);
2949 }
2950 }
2951}
2952
2953OBJ_VTABLE(httpc)
2954 httpc.init = httpc_init;
2955 httpc.disconnect = httpc_disconnect;
2956 httpc.wipe = httpc_wipe;
2957 httpc.set_ready = httpc_set_ready;
2958 httpc.set_busy = httpc_set_busy;
2959OBJ_VTABLE_END()
2960
2961void httpc_close_gently(httpc_t *w)
2962{
2963 w->connection_close = true;
2964 if (!w->busy) {
2965 obj_vcall(w, set_busy);
2966 }
2967 /* let the event loop maybe destroy us later, not now */
2968 el_fd_set_mask(w->ev, POLLOUT);
2969}
2970
2971static void httpc_http2_set_mask(httpc_t *w);
2972
2973static void httpc_set_mask(httpc_t *w)
2974{
2975 int mask = POLLIN;
2976
2977 if (w->connected_as_http2) {
2978 httpc_http2_set_mask(w);
2979 return;
2980 }
2981 if (!ob_is_empty(&w->ob)) {
2982 mask |= POLLOUT;
2983 }
2984 el_fd_set_mask(w->ev, mask);
2985}
2986
2987static int httpc_on_event(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
2988{
2989 httpc_t *w = priv.ptr;
2990 httpc_query_t *q;
2991 pstream_t ps;
2992 int res, st = HTTPC_STATUS_INVALID;
2993
2994 if (events == EL_EVENTS_NOACT) {
2995 if (!dlist_is_empty(&w->query_list)) {
2996 q = dlist_first_entry(&w->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
2997 if (q->expect100cont) {
2998 /* rfc 2616: ยง8.2.3: the client SHOULD NOT wait
2999 * for an indefinite period before sending the request body
3000 */
3001 (*q->on_100cont)(q);
3002 q->expect100cont = false;
3003 el_fd_watch_activity(evh, POLLINOUT, w->cfg->noact_delay);
3004 return 0;
3005 }
3006 }
3007 st = HTTPC_STATUS_TIMEOUT;
3008 goto close;
3009 }
3010
3011 if (events & POLLIN) {
3012 res = w->ssl ? ssl_sb_read(&w->ibuf, w->ssl, 0)
3013 : sb_read(&w->ibuf, fd, 0);
3014 if (res < 0) {
3015 if (!ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
3016 goto close;
3017 }
3018 goto write;
3019 }
3020
3021 ps = ps_initsb(&w->ibuf);
3022 if (res == 0) {
3023 if (w->chunk_length >= 0 || w->state != HTTP_PARSER_BODY) {
3024 goto close;
3025 }
3026 assert (!dlist_is_empty(&w->query_list));
3027 /* rfc 2616: ยง4.4: support no Content-Length followed by close */
3028 w->chunk_length = ps_len(&ps);
3029 }
3030
3031 do {
3032 res = (*httpc_parsers[w->state])(w, &ps);
3033 } while (res == PARSE_OK);
3034 if (res < 0) {
3035 st = res;
3036 goto close;
3037 }
3038 sb_skip_upto(&w->ibuf, ps.s);
3039 }
3040
3041 if (unlikely(w->connection_close)) {
3042 if (dlist_is_empty(&w->query_list) && ob_is_empty(&w->ob)) {
3043 goto close;
3044 }
3045 }
3046 write:
3047 res = w->ssl ? ob_write_with(&w->ob, fd, ssl_writev, w->ssl)
3048 : ob_write(&w->ob, fd);
3049 if (res < 0 && !ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
3050 goto close;
3051 }
3052 httpc_set_mask(w);
3053 return 0;
3054
3055 close:
3056 httpc_pool_detach(w);
3057 if (!dlist_is_empty(&w->query_list)) {
3058 q = dlist_first_entry(&w->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
3059 if (q->qinfo || st == HTTPC_STATUS_TIMEOUT) {
3060 httpc_query_on_done(q, st);
3061 }
3062 }
3063 obj_vcall(w, disconnect);
3064 obj_delete(&w);
3065 return 0;
3066}
3067
3068static void httpc_on_connect_error(httpc_t *w, int errnum)
3069{
3070 if (w->pool && w->pool->on_connect_error) {
3071 (*w->pool->on_connect_error)(w, errnum);
3072 } else
3073 if (w->on_connect_error) {
3074 (*w->on_connect_error)(w, errnum);
3075 }
3076
3077 obj_vcall(w, disconnect);
3078 obj_delete(&w);
3079}
3080
3081static int
3082httpc_tls_handshake(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
3083{
3084 httpc_t *w = priv.ptr;
3085 X509 *cert;
3086
3087 switch (ssl_do_handshake(w->ssl, evh, fd, NULL)) {
3088 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_SUCCESS:
3089 cert = SSL_get_peer_certificate(w->ssl);
3090 if (unlikely(cert == NULL)) {
3091 httpc_on_connect_error(w, ECONNREFUSED);
3092 return -1;
3093 }
3094 X509_free(cert);
3095 httpc_set_mask(w);
3096 el_fd_set_hook(evh, httpc_on_event);
3097 obj_vcall(w, set_ready, true);
3098 break;
3099 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_PENDING:
3100 break;
3101 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_CLOSED:
3102 httpc_on_connect_error(w, errno);
3103 break;
3104 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_ERROR:
3105 httpc_on_connect_error(w, errno);
3106 return -1;
3107 }
3108
3109 return 0;
3110}
3111
3112static int httpc_on_connect(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
3113{
3114 httpc_t *w = priv.ptr;
3115 int res;
3116
3117 if (events == EL_EVENTS_NOACT) {
3118 httpc_on_connect_error(w, ETIMEDOUT);
3119 return -1;
3120 }
3121
3122 res = socket_connect_status(fd);
3123 if (res > 0) {
3124 if (w->cfg->ssl_ctx) {
3125 w->ssl = SSL_new(w->cfg->ssl_ctx);
3126 assert (w->ssl);
3127 SSL_set_tlsext_host_name(w->ssl, w->pool->host.s);
3128 SSL_set_fd(w->ssl, fd);
3129 SSL_set_connect_state(w->ssl);
3130 el_fd_set_hook(evh, &httpc_tls_handshake);
3131 } else {
3132 el_fd_set_hook(evh, httpc_on_event);
3133 httpc_set_mask(w);
3134 obj_vcall(w, set_ready, true);
3135 }
3136 } else
3137 if (res < 0) {
3138 httpc_on_connect_error(w, errno);
3139 }
3140 return res;
3141}
3142
3143httpc_t *httpc_connect(const sockunion_t *su, httpc_cfg_t *cfg,
3144 httpc_pool_t *pool)
3145{
3146 return httpc_connect_as(su, NULL, cfg, pool);
3147}
3148
3149static httpc_t *httpc_connect_as_http2(const sockunion_t *su,
3150 const sockunion_t *nullable su_src,
3151 httpc_cfg_t *cfg, httpc_pool_t *pool);
3152
3153httpc_t *httpc_connect_as(const sockunion_t *su,
3154 const sockunion_t * nullable su_src,
3155 httpc_cfg_t *cfg, httpc_pool_t *pool)
3156{
3157 httpc_t *w;
3158 int fd;
3159
3160 if (cfg->http_mode == HTTP_MODE_USE_HTTP2_ONLY) {
3161 return httpc_connect_as_http2(su, su_src, cfg, pool);
3162 }
3163 fd = RETHROW_NP(connectx_as(-1, su, 1, su_src, SOCK_STREAM, IPPROTO_TCP,
3164 O_NONBLOCK, 0));
3165 w = obj_new_of_class(httpc, cfg->httpc_cls);
3166 w->cfg = httpc_cfg_retain(cfg);
3167 w->ev = el_fd_register(fd, true, POLLOUT, &httpc_on_connect, w);
3168 w->max_queries = cfg->max_queries;
3169 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, w->cfg->noact_delay);
3170 w->busy = true;
3171 if (pool) {
3172 httpc_pool_attach(w, pool);
3173 }
3174 return w;
3175}
3176
3177httpc_t *httpc_spawn(int fd, httpc_cfg_t *cfg, httpc_pool_t *pool)
3178{
3179 httpc_t *w = obj_new_of_class(httpc, cfg->httpc_cls);
3180
3181 w->cfg = httpc_cfg_retain(cfg);
3182 w->ev = el_fd_register(fd, true, POLLIN, &httpc_on_event, w);
3183 w->max_queries = cfg->max_queries;
3184 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, w->cfg->noact_delay);
3185 httpc_set_mask(w);
3186 if (pool) {
3187 httpc_pool_attach(w, pool);
3188 }
3189 return w;
3190}

3192/* }}} */
3193/* HTTPC Queries {{{ */
3194
3195void httpc_query_init(httpc_query_t *q)
3196{
3197 p_clear(q, 1);
3198 dlist_init(&q->query_link);
3199 sb_init(&q->payload);
3200}
3201
3202#define clear_fields_range_(type_t, v, f1, f2) \
3203 ({ type_t *__v = (v); \
3204 size_t off1 = offsetof(type_t, f1); \
3205 size_t off2 = offsetof(type_t, f2); \
3206 memset((uint8_t *)__v + off1, 0, off2 - off1); })
3207#define clear_fields_range(v, f1, f2) \
3208 clear_fields_range_(typeof(*(v)), v, f1, f2)
3209
3210void httpc_query_reset(httpc_query_t *q)
3211{
3212 dlist_remove(&q->query_link);
3213 httpc_qinfo_delete(&q->qinfo);
3214 sb_reset(&q->payload);
3215
3216 clear_fields_range(q, chunk_hdr_offs, on_hdrs);
3217}
3218
3219void httpc_query_wipe(httpc_query_t *q)
3220{
3221 dlist_remove(&q->query_link);
3222 httpc_qinfo_delete(&q->qinfo);
3223 sb_wipe(&q->payload);
3224}
3225
3226void httpc_query_attach(httpc_query_t *q, httpc_t *w)
3227{
3228 assert((w->ev || w->connected_as_http2) && w->max_queries > 0);
3229 assert (!q->hdrs_started && !q->hdrs_done);
3230 q->owner = w;
3231 dlist_add_tail(&w->query_list, &q->query_link);
3232 if (--w->max_queries == 0) {
3233 w->connection_close = true;
3234 if (!w->busy) {
3235 obj_vcall(w, set_busy);
3236 }
3237 }
3238 if (++w->queries >= w->cfg->pipeline_depth && !w->busy) {
3239 obj_vcall(w, set_busy);
3240 }
3241}
3242
3243static int httpc_query_on_data_bufferize(httpc_query_t *q, pstream_t ps)
3244{
3245 size_t plen = ps_len(&ps);
3246
3247 if (unlikely(plen + q->payload.len > q->payload_max_size)) {
3248 return HTTPC_STATUS_TOOLARGE;
3249 }
3250 sb_add(&q->payload, ps.s, plen);
3251 return 0;
3252}
3253
3254void httpc_bufferize(httpc_query_t *q, unsigned maxsize)
3255{
3256 q->payload_max_size = maxsize;
3257 q->on_data = &httpc_query_on_data_bufferize;
3258}
3259
3260void httpc_query_start_flags(httpc_query_t *q, http_method_t m,
3261 lstr_t host, lstr_t uri, bool httpc_encode_url)
3262{
3263 httpc_t *w = q->owner;
3264 outbuf_t *ob = &w->ob;
3265 int encode_at = 0;
3266
3267 assert (!q->hdrs_started && !q->hdrs_done);
3268
3269 ob_add(ob, http_method_str[m].s, http_method_str[m].len);
3270 ob_adds(ob, " ");
3271 if (w->cfg->use_proxy) {
3272 const char *s;
3273
3274 if (lstr_ascii_istartswith(uri, LSTR("http://"))) {
3275 uri.s += 7;
3276 uri.len -= 7;
3277 ob_add(ob, "http://", 7);
3278 s = memchr(uri.s, '/', uri.len);
3279 encode_at = (s) ? s - uri.s : uri.len;
3280 } else
3281 if (lstr_ascii_istartswith(uri, LSTR("https://"))) {
3282 uri.s += 8;
3283 uri.len -= 8;
3284 ob_add(ob, "https://", 8);
3285 s = memchr(uri.s, '/', uri.len);
3286 encode_at = (s) ? s - uri.s : uri.len;
3287 } else {
3288 /* Path must be made absolute for HTTP 1.0 proxies */
3289 ob_addf(ob, "http://%*pM", LSTR_FMT_ARG(host));
3290 if (unlikely(!uri.len || uri.s[0] != '/')) {
3291 ob_adds(ob, "/");
3292 }
3293 }
3294 } else {
3295 assert (!lstr_startswith(uri, LSTR("http://"))
3296 && !lstr_startswith(uri, LSTR("https://")));
3297 }
3298 if (httpc_encode_url) {
3299 ob_add(ob, uri.s, encode_at);
3300 ob_add_urlencode(ob, uri.s + encode_at, uri.len - encode_at);
3301 } else {
3302 ob_add(ob, uri.s, uri.len);
3303 }
3304 ob_addf(ob, " HTTP/1.1\r\n" "Host: %*pM\r\n", LSTR_FMT_ARG(host));
3305 http_update_date_cache(&date_cache_g, lp_getsec());
3306 ob_add(ob, date_cache_g.buf, sizeof(date_cache_g.buf) - 1);
3307 ob_adds(ob, "Accept-Encoding: identity, gzip, deflate\r\n");
3308 if (w->connection_close) {
3309 ob_adds(ob, "Connection: close\r\n");
3310 }
3311 q->hdrs_started = true;
3312}
3313
3314void httpc_query_hdrs_done(httpc_query_t *q, int clen, bool chunked)
3315{
3316 outbuf_t *ob = &q->owner->ob;
3317
3318 assert (!q->hdrs_done);
3319 q->hdrs_done = true;
3320
3321 if (q->expect100cont) {
3322 ob_adds(ob, "Expect: 100-continue\r\n");
3323 }
3324 if (clen >= 0) {
3325 ob_addf(ob, "Content-Length: %d\r\n\r\n", clen);
3326 return;
3327 }
3328 if (chunked) {
3329 q->chunked = true;
3330 ob_adds(ob, "Transfer-Encoding: chunked\r\n");
3331 /* XXX: no \r\n because http_chunk_patch adds it */
3332 } else {
3333 q->clength_hack = true;
3334 ob_adds(ob, "Content-Length: ");
3335 q->chunk_hdr_offs = ob_reserve(ob, CLENGTH_RESERVE);
3336 ob_adds(ob, "\r\n");
3337 q->chunk_prev_length = ob->length;
3338 }
3339}
3340
3341void httpc_query_chunk_done_(httpc_query_t *q, outbuf_t *ob)
3342{
3343 assert (q->chunk_started);
3344 q->chunk_started = false;
3345 http_chunk_patch(ob, ob->sb.data + q->chunk_hdr_offs,
3346 ob->length - q->chunk_prev_length);
3347}
3348
3349void httpc_query_done(httpc_query_t *q)
3350{
3351 outbuf_t *ob = &q->owner->ob;
3352
3353 assert (q->hdrs_done && !q->query_done && !q->chunk_started);
3354 if (q->chunked) {
3355 ob_adds(ob, "\r\n0\r\n\r\n");
3356 }
3357 if (q->clength_hack) {
3358 http_clength_patch(ob, ob->sb.data + q->chunk_hdr_offs,
3359 ob->length - q->chunk_prev_length);
3360 q->clength_hack = false;
3361 }
3362 q->query_done = true;
3363 httpc_set_mask(q->owner);
3364}
3365
3366void httpc_query_hdrs_add_auth(httpc_query_t *q, lstr_t login, lstr_t passwd)
3367{
3368 outbuf_t *ob = &q->owner->ob;
3369 sb_t *sb;
3370 sb_b64_ctx_t ctx;
3371 int oldlen;
3372
3373 assert (q->hdrs_started && !q->hdrs_done);
3374
3375 sb = outbuf_sb_start(ob, &oldlen);
3376
3377 sb_adds(sb, "Authorization: Basic ");
3378 sb_add_b64_start(sb, 0, -1, &ctx);
3379 sb_add_b64_update(sb, login.s, login.len, &ctx);
3380 sb_add_b64_update(sb, ":", 1, &ctx);
3381 sb_add_b64_update(sb, passwd.s, passwd.len, &ctx);
3382 sb_add_b64_finish(sb, &ctx);
3383 sb_adds(sb, "\r\n");
3384
3385 outbuf_sb_end(ob, oldlen);
3386}
3387
3388/* }}} */
3389/* {{{ HTTP2 Framing & Multiplexing Layer */
3390/* {{{ Primary Types */
3391
3392/** Settings of HTTP2 framing layer as per RFC7540/RFC9113 */
3393typedef struct http2_settings_t {
3394 uint32_t header_table_size;
3395 uint32_t enable_push;
3396 opt_u32_t max_concurrent_streams;
3397 uint32_t initial_window_size;
3398 uint32_t max_frame_size;
3399 opt_u32_t max_header_list_size;
3400} http2_settings_t;
3401
3402/* default setting values acc. to RFC7540/RFC9113 */
3403static http2_settings_t http2_default_settings_g = {
3404 .header_table_size = HTTP2_LEN_HDR_TABLE_SIZE_INIT,
3405 .enable_push = 1,
3406 .max_concurrent_streams = OPT_NONE,
3407 .initial_window_size = HTTP2_LEN_WINDOW_SIZE_INIT,
3408 .max_frame_size = HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE_INIT,
3409 .max_header_list_size = OPT_NONE,
3410};
3411
3412typedef struct http2_conn_t http2_conn_t;
3413
3414typedef struct http2_stream_t {
3415 http2_conn_t *conn;
3416 uint32_t remove : 1;
3417 uint32_t id : 31;
3418 dlist_t link;
3419 /* class link: inactive/closed<tracked>/booked streams */
3420 dlist_t class_link;
3421 int32_t recv_window;
3422 int32_t send_window;
3423 sb_t *ibuf;
3424 outbuf_t *ob;
3425 short events;
3426} http2_stream_t;
3427
3428static http2_stream_t *http2_stream_init(http2_stream_t *stream);
3429
3430GENERIC_NEW(http2_stream_t, http2_stream);
3431
3432static void http2_stream_wipe(http2_stream_t *stream);
3433
3434GENERIC_DELETE(http2_stream_t, http2_stream);
3435
3436qm_k32_t(qstream, http2_stream_t *);
3437
3438typedef struct http2_client_t http2_client_t;
3439typedef struct http2_server_t http2_server_t;
3440
3441/** HTTP2 connection object that can be configure as server or client. */
3442typedef struct http2_conn_t {
3443 el_t nonnull ev;
3444 http2_settings_t settings;
3445 http2_settings_t peer_settings;
3446 unsigned refcnt;
3447 unsigned id;
3448 outbuf_t ob;
3449 sb_t ibuf;
3450 SSL * nullable ssl;
3451 /* hpack compression contexts */
3452 hpack_enc_dtbl_t enc;
3453 hpack_dec_dtbl_t dec;
3454 /* tracked streams */
3455 qm_t(qstream) streams;
3456 dlist_t stream_list;
3457 /* inactive streams: either in idle or closed<untracked> state */
3458 dlist_t inactive_stream_list;
3459 /* closed<tracked> streams */
3460 dlist_t closed_stream_list;
3461 dlist_t booked_stream_list;
3462 uint32_t client_streams;
3463 uint32_t server_streams;
3464 int queries_can_send;
3465 int queries_can_recv;
3466 /* backstream contexts */
3467 union {
3468 http2_client_t *nullable client_ctx;
3469 http2_server_t *nullable server_ctx;
3470 };
3471 /* flow control */
3472 int32_t recv_window;
3473 int32_t send_window;
3474 /* socket idle timeout */
3475 unsigned idle_timeout;
3476 /* frame parser */
3477 http2_frame_info_t frame;
3478 unsigned cont_chunk;
3479 unsigned promised_id;
3480 uint8_t state;
3481
3482 /** Connection Flags */
3483
3484 /* True iff is configured as client. */
3485 bool is_client : 1;
3486 /* True once the socket is connected. */
3487 bool connected : 1;
3488 /* True once the peer's preface is received. */
3489 bool preface_recv : 1;
3490 /* True iff the initial SETTINGS been acknowledged. */
3491 bool preface_acked : 1;
3492 /* Closing State Flags */
3493 /* True iff an abortive GOAWAY was received. */
3494 bool abort_recv: 1;
3495 /* True iff the final graceful GOAWAY was received. */
3496 bool goaway_recv: 1;
3497 /* True iff a 'will-close-soon' GOAWAY was received. */
3498 bool will_close_recv: 1;
3499 /* True iff the peer closed its end of the connection. */
3500 bool eof_read : 1;
3501 /* True iff eof condition was processed. */
3502 bool eof_processed : 1;
3503 /* True iff our abortive GOAWAY was sent to the peer. */
3504 bool abort_in_flight: 1;
3505 /* True iff our final graceful GOAWAY was sent to the peer. */
3506 bool goaway_in_flight: 1;
3507 /* True iff an I/O error was encountered. */
3508 bool sock_err : 1;
3509 /* True iff the connection is in the closing fin_time_wait state. */
3510 bool fin_time_wait: 1;
3511 /* True once the closing is done and the socket should be closed. */
3512 bool done : 1;
3513 /* True once we enter the closing state. */
3514 bool closing : 1;
3515
3516 /** Async Inputs & Flags */
3517
3518 /* True once asked to close the connection gracefully. */
3519 bool send_goaway : 1;
3520 /* True iff there is a current async write from the the http1.1 layer. */
3521 bool async_write : 1;
3522} http2_conn_t;
3523
3524/** Get effective HTTP2 settings */
3525static http2_settings_t http2_get_settings(http2_conn_t *w)
3526{
3527 return likely(w->preface_acked) ? w->settings : http2_default_settings_g;
3528}
3529
3530/* }}}*/
3531/* {{{ Logging */
3532
3533/* TODO: add additional conn-related info to the log message */
3534#define http2_conn_log(/* const http_conn_t* */ w, /* int */ level, \
3535 /* const char* */ fmt, ...) \
3536 logger_log(&_G.logger, level, "[h2 %s %u] " fmt, \
3537 (w)->is_client ? "client" : "server", (w)->id, ##__VA_ARGS__)
3538
3539#define http2_conn_trace(w, level, fmt, ...) \
3540 http2_conn_log(w, LOG_TRACE + (level), fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__)
3541
3542/* TODO: add additional stream-related info to the log message */
3543#define http2_stream_log(/* const http_conn_t* */ w, \
3544 /* const stream_t* */ stream, /* int */ level, \
3545 /* const char* */ fmt, ...) \
3546 http2_conn_log(w, level, "[sid %d] " fmt, (stream)->id, ##__VA_ARGS__)
3547
3548#define http2_stream_trace(w, stream, level, fmt, ...) \
3549 http2_stream_log(w, stream, LOG_TRACE + (level), fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__)
3550
3551/* }}} */
3552/* {{{ Connection Management */
3553
3554static http2_conn_t *http2_conn_init(http2_conn_t *w)
3555{
3556 p_clear(w, 1);
3557 w->id = ++_G.http2_conn_count;
3558 sb_init(&w->ibuf);
3559 ob_init(&w->ob);
3560 qm_init(qstream, &w->streams);
3561 dlist_init(&w->stream_list);
3562 dlist_init(&w->inactive_stream_list);
3563 dlist_init(&w->closed_stream_list);
3564 dlist_init(&w->booked_stream_list);
3565 w->peer_settings = http2_default_settings_g;
3566 w->recv_window = HTTP2_LEN_CONN_WINDOW_SIZE_INIT;
3567 w->send_window = HTTP2_LEN_CONN_WINDOW_SIZE_INIT;
3568 hpack_enc_dtbl_init(&w->enc);
3569 hpack_dec_dtbl_init(&w->dec);
3570 hpack_enc_dtbl_init_settings(&w->enc, w->peer_settings.header_table_size);
3571 hpack_dec_dtbl_init_settings(&w->dec,
3572 http2_get_settings(w).header_table_size);
3573 return w;
3574}
3575
3576static void http2_conn_wipe(http2_conn_t *w)
3577{
3578 hpack_dec_dtbl_wipe(&w->dec);
3579 hpack_enc_dtbl_wipe(&w->enc);
3580 ob_wipe(&w->ob);
3581 sb_wipe(&w->ibuf);
3582 assert(dlist_is_empty(&w->stream_list));
3583 qm_wipe(qstream, &w->streams);
3584 assert(dlist_is_empty(&w->inactive_stream_list));
3585 assert(dlist_is_empty(&w->closed_stream_list));
3586 assert(dlist_is_empty(&w->booked_stream_list));
3587 SSL_free(w->ssl);
3588 w->ssl = NULL;
3589 el_unregister(&w->ev);
3590}
3591
3592DO_REFCNT(http2_conn_t, http2_conn)
3593
3594static bool http2_conn_has_pending_streams(http2_conn_t *w)
3595{
3596 return w->queries_can_send > 0 || w->queries_can_recv > 0;
3597}
3598
3599/* {{{ Low I/O Wrappers */
3600
3601static void http2_conn_read(http2_conn_t *w, int fd)
3602{
3603 int rc;
3604
3605 rc = w->ssl ? ssl_sb_read(&w->ibuf, w->ssl, 0) : sb_read(&w->ibuf, fd, 0);
3606
3607 if (unlikely(rc <= 0)) {
3608 if (unlikely(rc < 0)) {
3609 if (!ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
3610 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "read error: %s", strerror(errno));
3611 if (!w->sock_err) {
3612 w->sock_err = true;
3613 w->closing = true;
3614 w->done = true;
3615 }
3616 } else {
3617 /* This may help us see how properly we use el_fd_set_mask. */
3618 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "read temporary error: try again");
3619 }
3620 } else {
3621 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "read eof");
3622 w->eof_read = true;
3623 }
3624 return;
3625 }
3626
3627 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "read %d bytes", rc);
3628}
3629
3630static void http2_conn_write(http2_conn_t *w, int fd)
3631{
3632 int rc;
3633 int oldlen = w->ob.length;
3634
3635 rc = w->ssl ? ob_write_with(&w->ob, fd, ssl_writev, w->ssl)
3636 : ob_write(&w->ob, fd);
3637
3638 if (unlikely(rc < 0)) {
3639 if (!ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
3640 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "write error: %s", strerror(errno));
3641 if (!w->sock_err) {
3642 w->sock_err = true;
3643 w->closing = true;
3644 w->done = true;
3645 }
3646 } else {
3647 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "wrote 0 try again");
3648 }
3649 return;
3650 }
3651 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "wrote %d bytes", oldlen - w->ob.length);
3652}
3653
3654/* }}} */
3655/* {{{ Close Conditions */
3656
3657static void
3658http2_stream_on_reset(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream, bool remote);
3659
3660/** Internally closes streams with ids greater than the respective limits.
3661 *
3662 * Note: Affects only query ids greater than \p query_max and push ids greater
3663 * \p push_max. Passing -1 means no effect so keep all the streams of the
3664 * class (query or push) while passing 0 means close the whole class. */
3665static void http2_conn_close_streams_internal(http2_conn_t *w, int query_max,
3666 int push_max)
3667{
3668 dlist_for_each_entry(http2_stream_t, stream, &w->stream_list, link)
3669 {
3670 bool is_query = stream->id % 2; /* query or push */
3671
3672 if (is_query && (query_max < 0 || stream->id <= query_max)) {
3673 continue;
3674 }
3675 if (!is_query && (push_max < 0 || stream->id <= push_max)) {
3676 continue;
3677 }
3678
3679 http2_stream_on_reset(w, stream, false);
3680 http2_stream_delete(&stream);
3681 }
3682}
3683
3684static void http2_conn_on_close(http2_conn_t *w);
3685
3686static void http2_conn_close(http2_conn_t **w)
3687{
3688 http2_conn_close_streams_internal(*w, 0, 0);
3689 http2_conn_on_close(*w);
3690 http2_conn_release(w);
3691}
3692
3693static void http2_conn_on_connect_error(http2_conn_t *w, int errnum);
3694
3695static int http2_conn_close_connect_timeout(http2_conn_t **w)
3696{
3697 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "socket connect: timeout");
3698 http2_conn_on_connect_error(*w, ETIMEDOUT);
3699 http2_conn_close(w);
3700 return 0;
3701}
3702
3703static int http2_conn_close_connect_error(http2_conn_t **w)
3704{
3705 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "socket connect: error");
3706 http2_conn_on_connect_error(*w, errno);
3707 http2_conn_close(w);
3708 return 0;
3709}

3711static int http2_conn_close_tls_handshake_error(http2_conn_t **w)
3712{
3713 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "tls handshake: error");
3714 http2_conn_on_connect_error(*w, errno);
3715 http2_conn_close(w);
3716 return 0;
3717}
3718
3719static int http2_conn_close_tls_no_peer_certificate_error(http2_conn_t **w)
3720{
3721 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "tls: no peer certificiate error");
3722 http2_conn_on_connect_error(*w, ECONNREFUSED);
3723 http2_conn_close(w);
3724 return 0;
3725}

3727static int http2_conn_close_error_pack_preface(http2_conn_t **w)

3729 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "packing connection preface: error");
3730 http2_conn_close(w);
3731 return 0;

3748static int http2_conn_close_invalid_preface(http2_conn_t **w)

3753}
3754
3755static int http2_conn_close_abort_recv(http2_conn_t **w)
3756{
3757 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "connection error: abortive GOAWAY received");
3758 http2_conn_close(w);
3759 return 0;
3760}
3761
3762static int http2_conn_close_abort_sent(http2_conn_t **w)
3763{
3764 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "connection error: abortive GOAWAY sent");
3765 http2_conn_close(w);
3766 return 0;
3767}
3768
3769static int http2_conn_close_terminated(http2_conn_t **w)
3770{
3771 const char *sent = (**w).goaway_in_flight ? "sent" : "not sent";
3772 const char *recv = (**w).goaway_recv ? "received" : "not received";
3773
3774 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "connection terminated: GOAWAY %s GOAWAY %s",
3775 sent, recv);
3776 http2_conn_close(w);
3777 return 0;
3778}
3779
3780static int http2_conn_close_sock_error(http2_conn_t **w)
3781{
3782 http2_conn_trace(*w, 2, "connection error: socket error: ");
3783 http2_conn_close(w);
3784 return 0;
3785}
3786
3787static int http2_conn_close_done(http2_conn_t **wp)
3788{
3789 http2_conn_t *w = *wp;
3790
3791 if (w->sock_err) {
3792 return http2_conn_close_sock_error(wp);
3793 }
3794 if (w->abort_recv) {
3795 return http2_conn_close_abort_recv(wp);
3796 }
3797 if (w->abort_in_flight) {
3798 return http2_conn_close_abort_sent(wp);
3799 }
3800
3801 return http2_conn_close_terminated(wp);
3802}

3821 * โ โ E1 โ

3823 * โ โโโโโโโโโโโฌโโโผโโโโโโโโโโโโโโ โ
3824 * โ โ CLOSING โ โ โ โ
3825 * โ โโโโโโโโโโโ โผ โ E2: NO_PENDING_STREAMS โ
3826 * โ โ O โ โ
3827 * โ โ โ โ โ
3828 * โ โ โ E2 โ โ
3829 * โ โ โ โ โ
3830 * โ โ โโโโโโโโผโโโโโโโโโ โ โ
3831 * โ โ โ FIN_TIME_WAIT โ โ E3: TIMEOUT โ
3832 * โ โ โโโโโโโโฌโโโโโโโโโ โ EOF_READ โ
3833 * โ โ โ E3 โ โ
3834 * โ โ โ โ โ
3835 * โ โ E* โโโโโผโโโโโ โ โ
3836 * โ โโโโผโโโโโโโโบโ DONE โ โ E*: ABORT_RECV โ
3837 * โ โ โโโโโโโโโโ โ EOF_READ(unclean) โ
3838 * โ โโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโ SOCK_ERR โ
3839 * โ โ
3840 * โโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโโ
3841 *
3842 */
3843
3844static void
3845http2_conn_process_state_change_socket_connected(http2_conn_t *w, int fd)
3846{
3847 assert(!w->connected);
3848 w->connected = true;
3849
3850 if (w->ssl) {
3851 SSL_set_fd(w->ssl, fd);
3852 if (w->is_client) {
3853 SSL_set_connect_state(w->ssl);
3854 } else {
3855 SSL_set_accept_state(w->ssl);
3856 }
3857 }
3858
3859 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, w->idle_timeout);
3860 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "socket connected");
3861}
3862
3863static void http2_conn_process_state_change_preface_received(http2_conn_t *w)
3864{
3865 assert(!w->preface_recv);
3866 w->preface_recv = true;
3867
3868 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "peer connection preface received");
3869}
3870
3871static void http2_conn_process_state_change_preface_sent(http2_conn_t *w)
3872{
3873 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "connection preface sent");
3874}
3875
3876static void http2_conn_process_state_change_settings_sent(http2_conn_t *w)
3877{
3878 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "connection setting sent");
3879 /* FIXME: add timer to receive the the acknowledgement. */
3880}
3881
3882static void
3883http2_conn_process_state_change_goaway_recv(http2_conn_t *w,
3884 uint32_t last_stream_id)
3885{
3886 assert(!w->goaway_recv);
3887 w->goaway_recv = true;
3888 w->closing = true;
3889
3890 if (w->is_client) {
3891 http2_conn_close_streams_internal(w, last_stream_id, -1);
3892 } else {
3893 http2_conn_close_streams_internal(w, -1, last_stream_id);
3894 }
3895 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "closing: goaway recv");
3896}
3897
3898static void
3899http2_conn_process_state_change_will_close_recv(http2_conn_t *w)
3900{
3901 w->will_close_recv = true;
3902 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "'will-close' goaway recv");
3903}
3904
3905static void
3906http2_conn_process_state_change_abort_recv(http2_conn_t *w)
3907{
3908 assert(!w->abort_recv);
3909 w->abort_recv = true;
3910 w->closing = true;
3911 w->done = true;
3912 http2_conn_close_streams_internal(w, 0, 0);
3913 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "closing: abort recv");
3914}
3915
3916static void http2_conn_process_state_change_goaway_in_flight(http2_conn_t *w)
3917{
3918 assert(!w->goaway_in_flight);
3919 w->goaway_in_flight = true;
3920 w->closing = true;
3921 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "closing: goaway sent");
3922}
3923
3924static void http2_conn_process_state_change_abort_in_flight(http2_conn_t *w)
3925{
3926 assert(!w->abort_in_flight);
3927 w->abort_in_flight = true;
3928 w->closing = true;
3929 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "closing: abort sent");
3930 /* XXX: we delay the closing of streams until the end of the parse loop
3931 * since we may be in the process of handling a stream input that led to
3932 * this abort. */
3933}
3934
3935static void
3936http2_conn_process_state_change_fin_time_wait(http2_conn_t *w)
3937{
3938 assert(w->closing);
3939 assert(!w->fin_time_wait);
3940 w->fin_time_wait = true;
3941 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "fin_time_wait: enter");
3942}
3943
3944static void
3945http2_conn_process_state_change_fin_time_wait_idle_timeout(http2_conn_t *w)
3946{
3947 assert(w->fin_time_wait && w->closing);
3948 assert(!w->done);
3949 w->done = true;
3950 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "fin_time_wait: timeout (done)");
3951}
3952
3953static void
3954http2_conn_process_state_change_fin_time_wait_eof_read(http2_conn_t *w)
3955{
3956 assert(w->fin_time_wait && w->closing);
3957 assert(!w->done);
3958 w->done = true;
3959 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "fin_time_wait: eof read (done)");
3960}
3961
3962static void http2_conn_process_state_change_unexpected_eof(http2_conn_t *w)
3963{
3964 assert(!w->done);
3965 w->closing = true;
3966 w->done = true;
3967 http2_conn_close_streams_internal(w, 0, 0);
3968
3969 http2_conn_trace(w, 3, "fin_time_wait: eof read (done)");
3970
3971 if (unlikely(w->ibuf.len || w->cont_chunk)) {
3972 /* parsing leftover or expecting CONTINUATION(s). */
3973 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "read eof: input-buffer/parsing leftover");
3974 }
3975}
3976
3977/* }}} */
3978
3979/** Return the maximum id of the (non-idle) server stream or 0 if none. */
3980static uint32_t http2_conn_max_server_stream_id(const http2_conn_t *w)
3981{
3982 /* Server streams have even ids: 2, 4, 6, and so on. Server streams with
3983 * ids superior than this http2_conn_max_server_stream_id are idle,
3984 * otherwise, they are non idle (either active or closed). So, the next
3985 * available idle server stream is (http2_conn_max_server_stream_id + 2).
3986 * Note, that initiating a stream above this value, i.e., skipping some
3987 * ids is possible and implies closing the streams with the skipped ids.
3988 * So, this threshold is tracked using the number of streams (non-idle)
3989 * sor far. So, 0 server stream => 0 max server stream id (the next idle
3990 * stream is 2), 1 server stream => 2 max server stream id (the next idle
3991 * stream is 4), and so on.
3992 */
3993 return 2 * w->server_streams;
3994}
3995
3996/** Return the maximum id of the (non-idle) client stream or 0 if none. */
3997static uint32_t http2_conn_max_client_stream_id(const http2_conn_t *w)
3998{
3999 /* Client streams have odd ids: 1, 3, 5, and so on. Client streams with
4000 * ids superior than this http2_conn_max_client_stream_id are idle,
4001 * otherwise, they are non idle (either active or closed). So, the next
4002 * available idle client stream is (http2_conn_max_client_stream_id + 2)
4003 * except for client_streams = 0 where the next idle stream is 1. Note,
4004 * that initiating a stream above this value, i.e., skipping some ids is
4005 * possible and implies closing the streams with the skipped ids. So, this
4006 * threshold is tracked using the number of streams (non-idle) sor far.
4007 * So, 0 client stream => max client stream id = 0 (the next idle stream
4008 * is 1), 1 client stream => max client stream id = 1 (the next idle
4009 * stream is 3), 2 client streams => max client stream id = 3 (the next
4010 * idle stream is 5) and so on.
4011 */
4012 return 2 * w->client_streams - !!w->client_streams;
4013}
4014
4015/** Return the maximum id of the (non-idle) peer stream or 0 if none. */
4016static uint32_t http2_conn_max_peer_stream_id(const http2_conn_t *w)
4017{
4018 return w->is_client ? http2_conn_max_server_stream_id(w)
4019 : http2_conn_max_client_stream_id(w);
4020}
4021
4022/* }}}*/
4023/* {{{ Send Buffer Framing */
4024
4025typedef struct http2_frame_hdr_t {
4026 be32_t len : 24;
4027 uint8_t type;
4028 uint8_t flags;
4029 be32_t stream_id;
4030} __attribute__((packed)) http2_frame_hdr_t;
4031
4032static void
4033http2_conn_send_common_hdr(http2_conn_t *w, unsigned len, uint8_t type,
4034 uint8_t flags, uint32_t stream_id)
4035{
4036 http2_frame_hdr_t hdr;
4037
4038 STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(hdr) == HTTP2_LEN_FRAME_HDR);
4039 STATIC_ASSERT(HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE < (1 << 24));
4040 assert(len <= HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE);
4041 put_unaligned_be24(&hdr, len); /* XXX: hdr.len is a bit field */
4042 hdr.type = type;
4043 hdr.flags = flags;
4044 hdr.stream_id = cpu_to_be32(stream_id);
4045 ob_add(&w->ob, &hdr, sizeof(hdr));
4046}
4047
4048static void http2_conn_send_preface(http2_conn_t *w)
4049{
4050 if (w->is_client) {
4051 OB_WRAP(sb_add_lstr, &w->ob, http2_client_preamble_g);
4052 }
4053 http2_conn_process_state_change_preface_sent(w);
4054}
4055
4056typedef struct {
4057 uint16_t id;
4058 uint32_t val;
4059} setting_item_t;
4060
4061qvector_t(qsettings, setting_item_t);
4062
4063static void http2_conn_send_init_settings(http2_conn_t *w)
4064{
4065 t_scope;
4066 http2_settings_t defaults;
4067 http2_settings_t init_settings;
4068 qv_t(qsettings) items;
4069
4070#define STNG_ITEM(id_, val_) \
4071 (setting_item_t) \
4072 { \
4073 .id = HTTP2_ID_##id_, .val = init_settings.val_ \
4074 }
4075
4076#define STNG_ITEM_OPT(id_, val_) \
4077 (setting_item_t){.id = HTTP2_ID_##id_, .val = OPT_VAL(init_settings.val_)}
4078
4079 t_qv_init(&items, HTTP2_LEN_MAX_SETTINGS_ITEMS);
4080 defaults = http2_default_settings_g;
4081 init_settings = w->settings;
4082 if (init_settings.header_table_size != defaults.header_table_size) {
4083 qv_append(&items, STNG_ITEM(HEADER_TABLE_SIZE, header_table_size));
4084 }
4085 if (w->is_client && init_settings.enable_push != defaults.enable_push) {
4086 qv_append(&items, STNG_ITEM(ENABLE_PUSH, enable_push));
4087 }
4088 if (OPT_ISSET(init_settings.max_concurrent_streams) &&
4089 !OPT_EQUAL(init_settings.max_concurrent_streams,
4090 defaults.max_concurrent_streams))
4091 {
4092 qv_append(&items, STNG_ITEM_OPT(MAX_CONCURRENT_STREAMS,
4093 max_concurrent_streams));
4094 }
4095 if (init_settings.initial_window_size != defaults.initial_window_size) {
4096 qv_append(&items,
4097 STNG_ITEM(INITIAL_WINDOW_SIZE, initial_window_size));
4098 }
4099 if (init_settings.max_frame_size != defaults.max_frame_size) {
4100 qv_append(&items, STNG_ITEM(MAX_FRAME_SIZE, max_frame_size));
4101 }
4102 if (OPT_ISSET(init_settings.max_header_list_size) &&
4103 !OPT_EQUAL(init_settings.max_header_list_size,
4104 defaults.max_header_list_size))
4105 {
4106 qv_append(&items, STNG_ITEM_OPT(MAX_HEADER_LIST_SIZE,
4107 max_header_list_size));
4108 }
4109 assert(items.len <= HTTP2_LEN_MAX_SETTINGS_ITEMS);
4110 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(w, HTTP2_LEN_SETTINGS_ITEM * items.len,
4111 HTTP2_TYPE_SETTINGS, HTTP2_FLAG_NONE,
4112 HTTP2_ID_NO_STREAM);
4113 tab_for_each_ptr(item, &items) {
4114 OB_WRAP(sb_add_be16, &w->ob, item->id);
4115 OB_WRAP(sb_add_be32, &w->ob, item->val);
4116 }
4117
4118 http2_conn_process_state_change_settings_sent(w);
4119
4120#undef STNG_ITEM_OPT
4121#undef STNG_ITEM
4122}
4123
4124typedef struct http2_min_goaway_payload_t {
4125 be32_t last_stream_id;
4126 be32_t error_code;
4127} http2_min_goaway_payload_t;
4128
4129static void http2_conn_send_goaway(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t last_stream_id,
4130 uint32_t error_code, lstr_t debug)
4131{
4132 http2_min_goaway_payload_t payload;
4133 int len = sizeof(payload) + debug.len;
4134
4135 STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(payload) == HTTP2_LEN_GOAWAY_PAYLOAD_MIN);
4136 assert(last_stream_id <= HTTP2_ID_MAX_STREAM);
4137 payload.last_stream_id = cpu_to_be32(last_stream_id);
4138 payload.error_code = cpu_to_be32(error_code);
4139 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(w, len, HTTP2_TYPE_GOAWAY, HTTP2_FLAG_NONE,
4140 HTTP2_ID_NO_STREAM);
4141 ob_add(&w->ob, &payload, sizeof(payload));
4142 ob_add(&w->ob, debug.data, debug.len);
4143}
4144
4145/** Send data block as 0 or more data frames. */
4146static void http2_conn_send_data_block(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
4147 pstream_t blk, bool end_stream)
4148{
4149 pstream_t chunk;
4150 uint8_t flags;
4151 unsigned len;
4152
4153 if (ps_done(&blk) && !end_stream) {
4154 /* Empty DATA frames have no effect except those which end streams */
4155 return;
4156 }
4157 /* HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE_INIT is also the minimum possible value so
4158 * peer must always accept frames of this size. */
4159 do {
4160 len = MIN(ps_len(&blk), HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE_INIT);
4161 chunk = __ps_get_ps(&blk, len);
4162 flags = ps_done(&blk) && end_stream ? HTTP2_FLAG_END_STREAM : 0;
4163 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(w, len, HTTP2_TYPE_DATA, flags, stream_id);
4164 OB_WRAP(sb_add_ps, &w->ob, chunk);
4165 } while (!ps_done(&blk));
4166}
4167
4168/** Send header block as 1 header frame plus 0 or more continuation frames. */
4169static void http2_conn_send_headers_block(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
4170 pstream_t blk, bool end_stream)
4171{
4172 pstream_t chunk;
4173 uint8_t type;
4174 uint8_t flags;
4175 unsigned len;
4176
4177 assert(!ps_done(&blk));
4178 /* HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE_INIT is also the minimum possible value so
4179 * peer must always accept frames of this size. */
4180 type = HTTP2_TYPE_HEADERS;
4181 flags = end_stream ? HTTP2_FLAG_END_STREAM : HTTP2_FLAG_NONE;
4182 do {
4183 len = MIN(ps_len(&blk), HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE_INIT);
4184 chunk = __ps_get_ps(&blk, len);
4185 flags |= ps_done(&blk) ? HTTP2_FLAG_END_HEADERS : 0;
4186 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(w, len, type, flags, stream_id);
4187 OB_WRAP(sb_add_ps, &w->ob, chunk);
4188 type = HTTP2_TYPE_CONTINUATION;
4189 flags = HTTP2_FLAG_NONE;
4190 } while (!ps_done(&blk));
4191}
4192
4193static void http2_conn_send_rst_stream(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
4194 uint32_t error_code)
4195{
4196 assert(stream_id);
4197 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(w, HTTP2_LEN_RST_STREAM_PAYLOAD,
4198 HTTP2_TYPE_RST_STREAM, HTTP2_FLAG_NONE,
4199 stream_id);
4200 OB_WRAP(sb_add_be32, &w->ob, error_code);
4201}
4202
4203static void http2_conn_send_window_update(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
4204 uint32_t incr)
4205{
4206 assert(incr > 0 && incr <= 0x7fffffff);
4207 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(w, HTTP2_LEN_WINDOW_UPDATE_PAYLOAD,
4208 HTTP2_TYPE_WINDOW_UPDATE, HTTP2_FLAG_NONE,
4209 stream_id);
4210 OB_WRAP(sb_add_be32, &w->ob, incr);
4211}
4212
4213static void
4214http2_conn_send_shutdown(http2_conn_t *w, lstr_t debug)
4215{
4216 uint32_t stream_id = http2_conn_max_peer_stream_id(w);
4217
4218 http2_conn_send_goaway(w, stream_id, HTTP2_CODE_NO_ERROR, debug);
4219 http2_conn_process_state_change_goaway_in_flight(w);
4220}
4221
4222static int
4223http2_conn_send_error(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t error_code, lstr_t debug)
4224{
4225 uint32_t stream_id = http2_conn_max_peer_stream_id(w);
4226
4227 assert(error_code != HTTP2_CODE_NO_ERROR);
4228 http2_conn_send_goaway(w, stream_id, error_code, debug);
4229 http2_conn_process_state_change_abort_in_flight(w);
4230
4231 return -1;
4232}

4234/* }}} */
4235/* {{{ Stream Management */
4236
4237static http2_stream_t *http2_stream_init(http2_stream_t *stream)
4238{
4239 p_clear(stream, 1);
4240 dlist_init(&stream->link);
4241 dlist_init(&stream->class_link);
4242 return stream;
4243}
4244
4245static void http2_stream_wipe(http2_stream_t *stream)
4246{
4247 if (stream->conn) {
4248 qm_del_key(qstream, &stream->conn->streams, stream->id);
4249 }
4250 dlist_remove(&stream->link);
4251 dlist_remove(&stream->class_link);
4252}
4253
4254static bool http2_stream_id_is_server(uint32_t stream_id)
4255{
4256 assert(stream_id);
4257 assert(stream_id <= (uint32_t)HTTP2_ID_MAX_STREAM);
4258 return stream_id % 2 == 0;
4259}
4260
4261static bool http2_stream_id_is_client(uint32_t stream_id)
4262{
4263 return !http2_stream_id_is_server(stream_id);
4264}
4265
4266static int
4267http2_conn_is_peer_stream_id(const http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id)
4268{
4269 if (w->is_client) {
4270 return http2_stream_id_is_server(stream_id);
4271 } else {
4272 return http2_stream_id_is_client(stream_id);
4273 }
4274 return 0;
4275}
4276
4277
4278/** Check if \p stream_id is a stream that can be initiated by the peer. */
4279static int
4280http2_conn_check_peer_stream_id(const http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id)
4281{
4282 THROW_ERR_UNLESS(http2_conn_is_peer_stream_id(w, stream_id));
4283 return 0;
4284}
4285
4286/** Return true if the \p stream_id is a peer stream that is still in its idle
4287 * state. */
4288static bool
4289http2_conn_peer_stream_id_is_idle(const http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id)
4290{
4291 return stream_id > http2_conn_max_peer_stream_id(w);
4292}
4293
4294/** Return the number of streams (of the same class) upto to \p stream_id. */
4295static uint32_t http2_get_nb_streams_upto(uint32_t stream_id)
4296{
4297 assert(stream_id);
4298 assert(stream_id <= (uint32_t)HTTP2_ID_MAX_STREAM);
4299
4300 return DIV_ROUND_UP(stream_id, 2);
4301}
4302
4303/** Return the stream (info) with id = \p stream_id */
4304static http2_stream_t *http2_stream_get(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id)
4305{
4306 http2_stream_t *stream;
4307 uint32_t nb_streams;
4308
4309 stream = qm_get_def(qstream, &w->streams, stream_id, NULL);
4310 if (stream) {
4311 return stream;
4312 }
4313 stream = http2_stream_new();
4314 stream->conn = w;
4315 stream->id = stream_id;
4316 dlist_add_tail(&w->stream_list, &stream->link);
4317 dlist_add_tail(&w->inactive_stream_list, &stream->class_link);
4318 qm_add(qstream, &w->streams, stream->id, stream);
4319 nb_streams = http2_stream_id_is_client(stream_id) ? w->client_streams
4320 : w->server_streams;
4321 if (http2_get_nb_streams_upto(stream_id) > nb_streams) {
4322 /* stream is idle */
4323 } else {
4324 /* stream is closed<UNTRACKED> */
4325 stream->events = HTTP2_STREAM_EV_CLOSED;
4326 }
4327 return stream;
4328}
4329
4330/** Get the next idle (available) stream id. */
4331static uint32_t http2_stream_get_idle(http2_conn_t *w)
4332{
4333 uint32_t stream_id;
4334
4335 /* XXX: only relevant on the client side since we don't support creating
4336 * server (pushed) streams (yet!). */
4337 assert(w->is_client);
4338 stream_id = 2 * (uint32_t)w->client_streams + 1;
4339 assert(stream_id <= (uint32_t)HTTP2_ID_MAX_STREAM);
4340 return stream_id;
4341}
4342
4343/** Handle Stream States according RFC9113 ยง5.1.
4344 *
4345 * Note :\p events are the new events received or transmitted in *one* HTTP/2
4346 * frame.
4347 */
4348static void
4349http2_stream_handle_events(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
4350 unsigned events)
4351{
4352 unsigned flags = stream->events;
4353
4354 assert(events);
4355 assert(!(flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_CLOSED));
4356 assert(!(flags & events));
4357 if (!flags) {
4358 /* Idle stream */
4359 uint32_t nb_streams;
4360 uint32_t new_nb_streams;
4361
4362 w->queries_can_send++;
4363 w->queries_can_recv++;
4364
4365 nb_streams = http2_stream_id_is_client(stream->id)
4366 ? w->client_streams
4367 : w->server_streams;
4368 new_nb_streams = http2_get_nb_streams_upto(stream->id);
4369 assert(new_nb_streams > nb_streams);
4370 if (events == HTTP2_STREAM_EV_1ST_HDRS) {
4371 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "opened");
4372 } else if (events == (HTTP2_STREAM_EV_1ST_HDRS_EOS_RECV)) {
4373 w->queries_can_recv--;
4374 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "half closed (remote)");
4375 } else if (events == (HTTP2_STREAM_EV_1ST_HDRS_EOS_SENT)) {
4376 w->queries_can_send--;
4377 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "half closed (local)");
4378 } else if (events == HTTP2_STREAM_EV_PSH_RECV) {
4379 assert(w->is_client && !stream->id);
4380 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "reserved (remote)");
4381 } else {
4382 assert(0 && "invalid events on idle stream");
4383 }
4384 /* RFC7541(RFC9113) ยง 5.1.1. Stream Identifiers */
4385 if (http2_stream_id_is_client(stream->id)) {
4386 w->client_streams = new_nb_streams;
4387 } else {
4388 w->server_streams = new_nb_streams;
4389 }
4390 dlist_remove(&stream->class_link) /* from w->inactive_stream_list */;
4391 stream->events = events;
4392 stream->recv_window = http2_get_settings(w).initial_window_size;
4393 stream->send_window = w->peer_settings.initial_window_size;
4394 return;
4395 }
4396 if (events == HTTP2_STREAM_EV_1ST_HDRS) {
4397 assert(flags == HTTP2_STREAM_EV_PSH_RECV);
4398 stream->events |= (events | HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT);
4399 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "half closed (local) [pushed]");
4400 return;
4401 }
4402 if (events == HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_RECV) {
4403 w->queries_can_recv--;
4404 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT) {
4405 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "stream closed [eos recv]");
4406 stream->remove = true;
4407 } else {
4408 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "stream half closed (remote)");
4409 }
4410 } else if (events == HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT) {
4411 w->queries_can_send--;
4412 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_RECV) {
4413 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "stream closed [eos sent]");
4414 dlist_move_tail(&w->closed_stream_list, &stream->class_link);
4415 } else {
4416 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "stream half closed (local)");
4417 }
4418 } else if (events == HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_RECV) {
4419 w->queries_can_recv -= !(flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_RECV);
4420 w->queries_can_send -= !(flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT);
4421 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "stream closed [reset recv]");
4422 stream->remove = true;
4423 } else if (events == HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_SENT) {
4424 w->queries_can_recv -= !(flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_RECV);
4425 w->queries_can_send -= !(flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT);
4426 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "stream closed [reset sent]");
4427 dlist_move_tail(&w->closed_stream_list, &stream->class_link);
4428 } else {
4429 assert(0 && "unexpected stream state transition");
4430 }
4431 stream->events = flags | events;
4432}
4433
4434/* }}}*/
4435/* {{{ Headers Packing/Unpacking (HPACK) */
4436
4437#define PS_NODATA ps_init(NULL, 0)
4438
4439static struct {
4440 lstr_t key;
4441 unsigned flag_seen;
4442 int offset;
4443} http2_pseudo_hdr_descs_g[] = {
4444
4445#define PSEUDO_HDR(key_tok, key_) \
4446 { \
4447 .key = LSTR_IMMED(":" #key_), \
4448 .flag_seen = HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_##key_tok, \
4449 .offset = offsetof(http2_header_info_t, key_), \
4450 }
4451
4452 PSEUDO_HDR(METHOD, method),
4453 PSEUDO_HDR(SCHEME, scheme),
4454 PSEUDO_HDR(PATH, path),
4455 PSEUDO_HDR(AUTHORITY, authority),
4456 PSEUDO_HDR(STATUS, status),
4457
4458#undef PSEUDO_HDR
4459};
4460
4461/** Decode a header block.
4462 *
4463 * \param res: decoded headers info.
4464 * \return 0 if decoding succeed, -1 otherwise.
4465 *
4466 */
4467static int
4468t_http2_conn_decode_header_block(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t in,
4469 http2_header_info_t *res, sb_t *buf)
4470{
4471 hpack_dec_dtbl_t *dec = &w->dec;
4472 http2_header_info_t info = {0};
4473
4474 while (RETHROW(hpack_decoder_read_dts_update(dec, &in))) {
4475 /* read dynamic table size updates. */
4476 }
4477 while (!ps_done(&in)) {
4478 hpack_xhdr_t xhdr;
4479 int len;
4480 int keylen;
4481 byte *out;
4482 lstr_t key;
4483 lstr_t val;
4484
4485 len = RETHROW(hpack_decoder_extract_hdr(dec, &in, &xhdr));
4486 out = (byte *)sb_grow(buf, len);
4487 /* XXX: Decoded header is unpacked into the following format:
4488 * <DECODED_KEY> + ": " + <DECODED_VALUE> + "\r\n".
4489 */
4490 len = RETHROW(hpack_decoder_write_hdr(dec, &xhdr, out, &keylen));
4491 key = LSTR_DATA_V(out, keylen);
4492 val = LSTR_DATA_V(out + keylen + 2, len - keylen - 4);
4493 http2_conn_trace(w, 2, "%*pM: %*pM", LSTR_FMT_ARG(key),
4494 LSTR_FMT_ARG(val));
4495 THROW_ERR_IF(keylen < 1);
4496 if (unlikely(key.s[0] == ':')) {
4497 lstr_t *matched_phdr = NULL;
4498
4499 if (info.flags & HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_REGULAR_HEADERS) {
4500 info.flags |= HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_EXTRA_PSEUDO_HDR;
4501 }
4502 carray_for_each_entry(phdr, http2_pseudo_hdr_descs_g) {
4503 if (lstr_equal(key, phdr.key)) {
4504 if (!(phdr.flag_seen & info.flags)) {
4505 matched_phdr = (lstr_t *)((byte *)(&info) + phdr.offset);
4506
4507 info.flags |= phdr.flag_seen;
4508 *matched_phdr = t_lstr_dup(val);
4509 break;
4510 } else {
4511 info.flags |= HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_EXTRA_PSEUDO_HDR;
4512 }
4513 }
4514 }
4515 if (!matched_phdr) {
4516 /* unknown pseudo-hdr */
4517 info.flags |= HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_EXTRA_PSEUDO_HDR;
4518 }
4519 } else {
4520 info.flags |= HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_REGULAR_HEADERS;
4521 if (lstr_ascii_iequal(key, LSTR_IMMED_V("content-length"))) {
4522 info.flags |= HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_CONTENT_LENGTH;
4523 info.content_length = val;
4524 } else if (lstr_ascii_iequal(key, LSTR_IMMED_V("host"))) {
4525 info.flags |= HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_HOST;
4526 info.host = val;
4527 }
4528 buf->len += len;
4529 }
4530 }
4531 sb_set_trailing0(buf);
4532 /* Basic validation according to RFC9113 ยง8.3. */
4533 *res = info;
4534 return 0;
4535}
4536
4537static void http2_headerlines_get_next_hdr(pstream_t *headerlines,
4538 lstr_t *key, lstr_t *val)
4539{
4540 pstream_t line = PS_NODATA;
4541 pstream_t ps = PS_NODATA;
4542 int rc;
4543
4544 assert(!ps_done(headerlines));
4545 rc = ps_get_ps_upto_str_and_skip(headerlines, "\r\n", &line);
4546 assert(rc >= 0 && !ps_done(&line));
4547 rc = ps_get_ps_chr_and_skip(&line, ':', &ps);
4548 assert(rc >= 0);
4549 ps_trim(&ps);
4550 assert(!ps_done(&ps));
4551 *key = LSTR_PS_V(&ps);
4552 ps_trim(&line);
4553 assert(!ps_done(&line));
4554 *val = LSTR_PS_V(&line);
4555}
4556
4557static void http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(http2_conn_t *w, lstr_t key,
4558 lstr_t val, sb_t *out_)
4559{
4560 hpack_enc_dtbl_t *enc = &w->enc;
4561 int len;
4562 int buflen;
4563 byte *out;
4564
4565 buflen = hpack_buflen_to_write_hdr(key, val, 0);
4566 out = (byte *)sb_grow(out_, buflen);
4567 len = hpack_encoder_write_hdr(enc, key, val, 0, 0, 0, out);
4568 assert(len > 0);
4569 assert(len <= buflen);
4570 __sb_fixlen(out_, out_->len + len);
4571}
