4654
4655static bool
4656http2_is_valid_response_hdr_to_send(lstr_t key_, lstr_t val, int *clen)
4657{
4658 pstream_t key = ps_initlstr(&key_);
4659 int rc;
4660
4661 switch (http_wkhdr_from_ps(key)) {
4662 case HTTP_WKHDR_PRAGMA:
4663 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONNECTION:
4664
4665 return false;
4666 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONTENT_LENGTH:
4667 rc = lstr_to_int(val, clen);
4668 assert(!rc);
4669 break;
4670 default:
4671 break;
4672 }
4673 return true;
4674}
4675
4676static void
4677http2_stream_send_response_headers(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
4678 lstr_t status, pstream_t headerlines,
4679 httpd_http2_ctx_t *httpd_ctx, int *clen)
4680{
4681 t_scope;
4682 t_SB_1k(out);
4683 bool eos;
4684
4685 *clen = -1;
4686 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, LSTR_IMMED_V(":status"), status, &out);
4687 while (!ps_done(&headerlines)) {
4688 lstr_t key;
4689 lstr_t val;
4690
4691 http2_headerlines_get_next_hdr(&headerlines, &key, &val);
4692 if (!http2_is_valid_response_hdr_to_send(key, val, clen)) {
4693 continue;
4694 }
4695 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, key, val, &out);
4696 }
4697 eos = (*clen == 0);
4698 http2_conn_send_headers_block(w, stream->id, ps_initsb(&out), eos);
4699 if (eos) {
4700 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT);
4701 }
4702}
4703
4704static bool
4705http2_is_valid_request_hdr_to_send(lstr_t key_, lstr_t val, int *clen)
4706{
4707 pstream_t key = ps_initlstr(&key_);
4708 int rc;
4709
4710 switch (http_wkhdr_from_ps(key)) {
4711 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONNECTION:
4712 case HTTP_WKHDR_TRANSFER_ENCODING:
4713
4714 return false;
4715 case HTTP_WKHDR_CONTENT_LENGTH:
4716 rc = lstr_to_int(val, clen);
4717 assert(!rc);
4718 break;
4719 default:
4720 break;
4721 }
4722 return true;
4723}
4724
4725static void
4726http2_stream_send_request_headers(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
4727 lstr_t method, lstr_t scheme, lstr_t path,
4728 lstr_t authority, pstream_t headerlines,
4729 int *clen)
4730{
4731 SB_1k(out);
4732 unsigned events;
4733 bool eos;
4734
4735 *clen = -1;
4736 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, LSTR_IMMED_V(":method"), method, &out);
4737 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, LSTR_IMMED_V(":scheme"), scheme, &out);
4738 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, LSTR_IMMED_V(":path"), path, &out);
4739 if (authority.len) {
4740 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, LSTR_IMMED_V(":authority"), authority,
4741 &out);
4742 }
4743 while (!ps_done(&headerlines)) {
4744 lstr_t key;
4745 lstr_t val;
4746
4747 http2_headerlines_get_next_hdr(&headerlines, &key, &val);
4748 if (!http2_is_valid_request_hdr_to_send(key, val, clen)) {
4749 continue;
4750 }
4751 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, key, val, &out);
4752 }
4753 eos = (*clen == 0);
4754 http2_conn_send_headers_block(w, stream->id, ps_initsb(&out), eos);
4755 events = HTTP2_STREAM_EV_1ST_HDRS | (eos ? HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT : 0);
4756 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, events);
4757}
4758
4759static void http2_stream_send_data(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
4760 pstream_t data, bool eos)
4761{
4762 int len = ps_len(&data);
4763
4764 assert(stream->send_window >= len);
4765 stream->send_window -= len;
4766 assert(w->send_window >= (int)len);
4767 w->send_window -= len;
4768 http2_conn_send_data_block(w, stream->id, data, eos);
4769 if (eos) {
4770 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT);
4771 }
4772}
4773
4774#define http2_stream_send_reset(w, stream, fmt, ...) \
4775 do { \
4776 http2_stream_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
4777 } while (0)
4778
4779#define http2_stream_send_reset_cancel(w, stream, fmt, ...) \
4780 do { \
4781 http2_stream_error(w, stream, CANCEL, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
4782 } while (0)
4783
4784/* }}} */
4785/* {{{ Stream-Related Frame Handling */
4786
4787#define http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, error_code, fmt, ...) \
4788 ({ \
4789 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "connection error: " fmt, \
4790 ##__VA_ARGS__); \
4791 http2_stream_conn_error_(w, stream, HTTP2_CODE_##error_code, fmt, \
4792 ##__VA_ARGS__); \
4793 })
4794
4795__attribute__((format(printf, 4, 5)))
4796static int http2_stream_conn_error_(http2_conn_t *w,
4797 const http2_stream_t *stream,
4798 uint32_t error_code,
4799 const char *fmt, ...)
4800{
4801 t_scope;
4802 lstr_t debug;
4803 va_list ap;
4804
4805 va_start(ap, fmt);
4806 debug = t_lstr_vfmt(fmt, ap);
4807 va_end(ap);
4808 return http2_conn_send_error(w, error_code, debug);
4809}
4810
4811#define http2_stream_error(w, stream, error_code, fmt, ...) \
4812 do { \
4813 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "stream error: " fmt, \
4814 ##__VA_ARGS__); \
4815 http2_conn_send_rst_stream(w, (stream)->id, \
4816 HTTP2_CODE_##error_code); \
4817 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_SENT); \
4818 } while (0)
4819
4820static void
4821http2_stream_maintain_recv_window(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream)
4822{
4823 int incr;
4824
4825 incr =
4826 http2_get_settings(w).initial_window_size - stream->recv_window;
4827 if (incr <= 0) {
4828 return;
4829 }
4830 http2_conn_send_window_update(w, stream->id, incr);
4831 stream->recv_window += incr;
4832}
4833
4834static int
4835http2_stream_consume_recv_window(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
4836 unsigned delta)
4837{
4838 assert(delta <= http2_get_settings(w).max_frame_size);
4839
4840 /* maintain the recv window at the initial_window_size settings each time
4841 * the peer sends DATA frame */
4842 stream->recv_window -= delta;
4843 http2_stream_maintain_recv_window(w, stream);
4844 return 0;
4845}
4846
4847static int
4848http2_stream_check_can_recv(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
4849 bool is_headers)
4850{
4851 unsigned flags = stream->events;
4852 const char *type = is_headers ? "HEADERS" : "DATA";
4853
4854 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_CLOSED) {
4855 return http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
4856 "%s on closed stream", type);
4857 }
4858 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_MASK_PEER_CANT_WRITE) {
4859 return http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, STREAM_CLOSED,
4860 "%s on closed stream", type);
4861 }
4862 if (!flags) {
4863 if (!is_headers) {
4864 return http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
4865 "DATA on idle stream");
4866 } else if (w->is_client) {
4867 return http2_stream_conn_error(
4868 w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
4869 "HEADERS on idle stream (at client)");
4870 }
4871 }
4872 return 0;
4873}
4874
4875static int
4876http2_stream_do_recv_data(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id, pstream_t data,
4877 int initial_payload_len, bool eos)
4878{
4879 http2_stream_t *stream = http2_stream_get(w, stream_id);
4880 unsigned flags = stream->events;
4881
4882 RETHROW(http2_stream_check_can_recv(w, stream, false));
4883 if (eos) {
4884 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_RECV);
4885 }
4886 RETHROW(http2_stream_consume_recv_window(w, stream,
4887 initial_payload_len));
4888 if (!(flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_SENT)) {
4889 http2_stream_on_data(w, stream, data, eos);
4890 }
4891 return 0;
4892}
4893
4894static unsigned http2_valid_pseudo_hdr_combination_g[] = {
4895 0,
4896 HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_STATUS,
4897 HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_SCHEME | HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_PATH
4898 | HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_METHOD,
4899 HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_SCHEME | HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_PATH
4900 | HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_METHOD | HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_AUTHORITY,
4901};
4902
4903static bool http2_stream_validate_recv_headrs(http2_header_info_t *info)
4904{
4905 unsigned flags = info->flags;
4906
4907 if (flags & HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_EXTRA_PSEUDO_HDR) {
4908 return false;
4909 }
4910 flags &= ~(HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_CONTENT_LENGTH
4911 | HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_REGULAR_HEADERS);
4912
4913 carray_for_each_entry(e, http2_valid_pseudo_hdr_combination_g) {
4914 if (e == flags) {
4915 return true;
4916 }
4917 }
4918 return false;
4919}
4920
4921static int http2_stream_do_recv_headers(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
4922 http2_header_info_t *info,
4923 pstream_t headerlines, bool eos)
4924{
4925 http2_stream_t *stream = http2_stream_get(w, stream_id);
4926 unsigned flags = stream->events;
4927 unsigned events = 0;
4928
4929 if (http2_stream_id_is_server(stream_id)) {
4930 if (!(flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_PSH_RECV)) {
4931 return http2_stream_conn_error(
4932 w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
4933 "HEADERS on server stream (invalid state)");
4934 }
4935 assert(w->is_client);
4936 /* Discard (responses) headers on server streams. This may happen for
4937 * a short period in the begining of communicaition since we don't
4938 * support them and the server must not send them once it acknowledges
4939 * our initial settings. However, it may start push such streams
4940 * before acknowledging our settings that disables them. */
4941 return 0;
4942 }
4943 RETHROW(http2_stream_check_can_recv(w, stream, true));
4944 if (!http2_stream_validate_recv_headrs(info)) {
4945 if (!flags) {
4946 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, HTTP2_STREAM_EV_1ST_HDRS);
4947 }
4948 http2_stream_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
4949 "HEADERS with invalid HTTP headers");
4950 http2_stream_on_reset(w, stream, false);
4951 return 0;
4952 }
4953 if (!flags) {
4954 events |= HTTP2_STREAM_EV_1ST_HDRS;
4955 }
4956 if (eos) {
4957 events |= HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_RECV;
4958 }
4959 if (events) {
4960 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, events);
4961 } else {
4962 assert(flags);
4963 }
4964 if (!flags && w->goaway_recv) {
4965 http2_stream_error(
4966 w, stream, REFUSED_STREAM,
4967 "server is finalizing, no more stream is accepted");
4968 http2_stream_on_reset(w, stream, false);
4969 }
4970 if (!(flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_SENT)) {
4971 if (!flags) {
4972 /* new stream */
4973 http2_stream_on_accept(w, stream);
4974 }
4975 http2_stream_on_headers(w, stream, info, headerlines, eos);
4976 }
4977 return 0;
4978}
4979
4980static int http2_stream_do_recv_priority(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
4981 uint32_t stream_dependency)
4982{
4983 http2_stream_t *stream = http2_stream_get(w, stream_id);
4984
4985 /* Priority frames can be received in any stream state */
4986 /* XXX: we don't support stream prioritization. However, a minimal
4987 * processing is to check against self-dependency error. */
4988 if (stream_dependency == stream_id) {
4989 return http2_stream_conn_error(
4990 w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
4991 "frame error: PRIORITY with self-dependency [%d]",
4992 stream_dependency);
4993 }
4994 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2, "PRIORITY [dependency on %d]",
4995 stream_dependency);
4996 return 0;
4997}
4998
4999static int
5000http2_stream_do_recv_rst_stream(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5001 uint32_t error_code)
5002{
5003 http2_stream_t *stream = http2_stream_get(w, stream_id);
5004 unsigned flags = stream->events;
5005
5006 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_CLOSED) {
5007 return http2_stream_conn_error(
5008 w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5009 "RST_STREAM on closed stream [code %u]", error_code);
5010 }
5011 if (!flags) {
5012 return http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5013 "RST_STREAM on idle stream [code %u]",
5014 error_code);
5015 }
5016 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_SENT) {
5017 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2,
5018 "RST_STREAM ingored (rst sent already) [code %u]",
5019 error_code);
5020 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_RECV);
5021 return 0;
5022 }
5023 http2_stream_handle_events(w, stream, HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_RECV);
5024 return 0;
5025}
5026
5027static int
5028http2_stream_do_recv_push_promise(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5029 http2_header_info_t *info,
5030 pstream_t headerlines, uint32_t promised_id)
5031{
5032 http2_stream_t *stream = http2_stream_get(w, stream_id);
5033 http2_stream_t *promised = http2_stream_get(w, promised_id);
5034 unsigned flags = stream->events;
5035
5036 assert(w->is_client);
5037 assert(!promised->events);
5038 if (http2_stream_id_is_server(stream_id)) {
5039 return http2_stream_conn_error(
5040 w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5041 "cannot accept promised stream %d on a server stream",
5042 promised_id);
5043 }
5044 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_CLOSED) {
5045 return http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5046 "PUSH_STREAM on closed stream");
5047 }
5048 if (!flags) {
5049 return http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5050 "PUSH_STREAM on idle stream");
5051 }
5052 /* RFC 9113 ยง6.6. PUSH_PROMISE:
5053 * `PUSH_PROMISE frames MUST only be sent on a peer-initiated stream that
5054 * is in either the "open" or "half-closed (remote)" state. is in either
5055 * the "open" or "half-closed (remote)" state.`*/
5056 /* So, w.r.t the client, this means that push promise can be received only
5057 * on a stream that is either open or half-closed (local) [or closing by
5058 * RST_SENT]. */
5059 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_RECV) {
5060 return http2_stream_conn_error(
5061 w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5062 "PUSH_STREAM on half-closed (remote) stream");
5063 }
5064 /* Refuse the pushed stream: not supported (yet). */
5065 http2_stream_handle_events(w, promised, HTTP2_STREAM_EV_PSH_RECV);
5066 http2_stream_error(w, promised, REFUSED_STREAM,
5067 "refuse push promise (not supported)");
5068 return 0;
5069}
5070
5071static int
5072http2_stream_do_recv_window_update(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5073 int32_t incr)
5074{
5075 http2_stream_t *stream = http2_stream_get(w, stream_id);
5076 unsigned flags = stream->events;
5077 int64_t new_size = (int64_t)stream->send_window + incr;
5078
5079 assert(incr >= 0);
5080 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_CLOSED) {
5081 return http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5082 "WINDOW_UPDATE on closed stream");
5083 }
5084 if (!flags) {
5085 return http2_stream_conn_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5086 "WINDOW_UPDATE on idle stream");
5087 }
5088 if (!incr) {
5089 http2_stream_error(w, stream, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5090 "frame error: WINDOW_UPDATE with 0 increment");
5091 return 0;
5092 }
5093 if (new_size > HTTP2_LEN_WINDOW_SIZE_LIMIT) {
5094 if (flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_SENT) {
5095 http2_stream_trace(
5096 w, stream, 2,
5097 "flow control: ignored WINDOW_UPDATE (already RST_SENT)");
5098 return 0;
5099 }
5100 http2_stream_error(
5101 w, stream, FLOW_CONTROL_ERROR,
5102 "flow control: WINDOW_UPDATE cannot increment send-window beyond "
5103 "limit [cur %d, incr %d, new %jd]",
5104 stream->send_window, incr, new_size);
5105 return 0;
5106 }
5107 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2,
5108 "send-window incremented [new size %lld, incr %d]",
5109 (long long)new_size, incr);
5110 stream->send_window += incr;
5111 return 0;
5112}
5113
5114/* }}} */
5115/* {{{ Stream-Related Frame Parsing */
5116
5117#define HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, error_code, fmt, ...) \
5118 do { \
5119 return http2_conn_error(w, error_code, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
5120 } while (0)
5121
5122#define http2_conn_error(w, error_code, fmt, ...) \
5123 ({ \
5124 http2_conn_trace(w, 2, "connection error: " fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
5125 http2_conn_error_(w, HTTP2_CODE_##error_code, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
5126 })
5127
5128__attribute__((format(printf, 3, 4)))
5129static int http2_conn_error_(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t error_code,
5130 const char *fmt, ...)
5131{
5132 t_scope;
5133 lstr_t debug;
5134 va_list ap;
5135
5136 va_start(ap, fmt);
5137 debug = t_lstr_vfmt(fmt, ap);
5138 va_end(ap);
5139 return http2_conn_send_error(w, error_code, debug);
5140}
5141
5142int http2_parse_frame_hdr(pstream_t *ps, http2_frame_info_t *frame)
5143{
5144 const http2_frame_hdr_t *hdr;
5145
5146 hdr = RETHROW_PN(ps_get_data(ps, sizeof(http2_frame_hdr_t)));
5147
5148 /* XXX: hdr->len is a bitfield. */
5149 frame->len = get_unaligned_be24(hdr);
5150 frame->type = hdr->type;
5151 frame->flags = hdr->flags;
5152 frame->stream_id = HTTP2_STREAM_ID_MASK & cpu_to_be32(hdr->stream_id);
5153
5154 return 0;
5155}
5156
5157static void http2_conn_maintain_recv_window(http2_conn_t *w)
5158{
5159 int incr = HTTP2_LEN_WINDOW_SIZE_LIMIT - w->recv_window;
5160
5161 if (incr <= 0) {
5162 return;
5163 }
5164 http2_conn_send_window_update(w, 0, incr);
5165 w->recv_window += incr;
5166}
5167
5168static void
5169http2_conn_consume_recv_window(http2_conn_t *w, int len)
5170{
5171 /* Maintain the recv window at a specific level each time the peer
5172 * sends DATA frame. This effectively disables the flow control. */
5173 w->recv_window -= len;
5174 http2_conn_maintain_recv_window(w);
5175}
5176
5177int http2_payload_get_trimmed_chunk(pstream_t payload, int frame_flags,
5178 pstream_t *chunk)
5179{
5180 if (frame_flags & HTTP2_FLAG_PADDED) {
5181 int padding_sz;
5182
5183 padding_sz = RETHROW(ps_getc(&payload));
5184 RETHROW(ps_shrink(&payload, padding_sz));
5185 }
5186 *chunk = payload;
5187 return 0;
5188}
5189
5190static int http2_conn_parse_data(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5191 pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5192{
5193 bool end_stream;
5194 int initial_payload_len;
5195 pstream_t chunk;
5196
5197 initial_payload_len = ps_len(&payload);
5198 if (http2_payload_get_trimmed_chunk(payload, flags, &chunk) < 0) {
5199 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5200 "frame error: invalid padding on stream %d",
5201 stream_id);
5202 }
5203
5204 http2_conn_consume_recv_window(w, initial_payload_len);
5205 end_stream = flags & HTTP2_FLAG_END_STREAM;
5206 return http2_stream_do_recv_data(w, stream_id, chunk, initial_payload_len,
5207 end_stream);
5208}
5209
5210/** Consolidate a header block from an already-validated multiframe.
5211 *
5212 * Note: \p multiframe is composed of either a HEADERS or PUSH_PROMISE frame
5213 * (followed by 0 or more CONTINUATION frame(s)). The multiframe components
5214 * are already parsed (and verified) but is kept in the connection buffer
5215 * until the coming of the END_OF_HEADERS flag where the embeded header block
5216 * is reconstructed before decoded by the HPACK decoder. The type of initial
5217 * frame is conveyed by \p promised_id.
5218 */
5219/* TODO: Bench performance against a version of the function that uses the
5220 * safe counterparts of __ps_* .*/
5221static void
5222http2_conn_construct_hdr_blk(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t multiframe,
5223 size_t initial_len, uint8_t flags,
5224 uint32_t promised_id, sb_t *blk)
5225{
5226 pstream_t chunk;
5227 int chunk_len;
5228
5229 chunk_len = initial_len;
5230 chunk = __ps_get_ps(&multiframe, chunk_len);
5231 if (flags & HTTP2_FLAG_PADDED) {
5232 uint8_t padding = __ps_getc(&chunk);
5233
5234 __ps_shrink(&chunk, padding);
5235 }
5236 if (!promised_id) {
5237 /* block in HEADERS + 0 or more CONTINUATION(s). */
5238 if (flags & HTTP2_FLAG_PRIORITY) {
5239 __ps_skip(&chunk, 4 + 1); /* stream dependency (4) + weight (1) */
5240 }
5241 } else {
5242 /* block in PUSH_PROMISE + 0 or more CONTINUATION(s). */
5243 __ps_skip(&chunk, 4); /* promised_id (4) */
5244 }
5245 sb_add_ps(blk, chunk);
5246 while (!ps_done(&multiframe)) {
5247 chunk_len = __ps_get_be24(&multiframe);
5248 __ps_skip(&multiframe, HTTP2_LEN_FRAME_HDR - 3);
5249 chunk = __ps_get_ps(&multiframe, chunk_len);
5250 sb_add_ps(blk, chunk);
5251 }
5252}
5253
5254static int http2_conn_do_on_end_headers(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5255 pstream_t ps, size_t initial_len,
5256 uint32_t flags, uint32_t promised_id)
5257{
5258 t_scope;
5259 http2_header_info_t info;
5260 bool end_stream;
5261 SB_8k(blk);
5262 SB_8k(headerlines);
5263 int rc;
5264
5265 http2_conn_construct_hdr_blk(w, ps, initial_len, flags, promised_id,
5266 &blk);
5267 rc = t_http2_conn_decode_header_block(w, ps_initsb(&blk), &info,
5268 &headerlines);
5269 if (rc < 0) {
5270 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, COMPRESSION_ERROR,
5271 "compression error: "
5272 "invalid header block on stream %d",
5273 stream_id);
5274 }
5275 if (promised_id) {
5276 /* We have block as PUSH + 0 or more CONTINUATION(s). */
5277 return http2_stream_do_recv_push_promise(
5278 w, stream_id, &info, ps_initsb(&headerlines), promised_id);
5279 }
5280 /* We have block as HEADERS + 0 or more CONTINUATION(s). */
5281 end_stream = flags & HTTP2_FLAG_END_STREAM;
5282 return http2_stream_do_recv_headers(w, stream_id, &info,
5283 ps_initsb(&headerlines), end_stream);
5284}
5285
5286static bool http2_conn_is_server_push_enabled(http2_conn_t *w)
5287{
5288 return http2_get_settings(w).enable_push && w->peer_settings.enable_push;
5289}
5290
5291static int http2_conn_parse_headers(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5292 pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5293{
5294 pstream_t chunk;
5295
5296 if (http2_payload_get_trimmed_chunk(payload, flags, &chunk) < 0) {
5297 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5298 "frame error: HEADERS with invalid padding");
5299 }
5300
5301 if (flags & HTTP2_FLAG_PRIORITY) {
5302 uint32_t stream_dependency;
5303
5304 if (ps_get_be32(&chunk, &stream_dependency) < 0) {
5305 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR,
5306 "frame error: "
5307 "HEADERS is too short to read stream dependency");
5308 }
5309 stream_dependency &= HTTP2_STREAM_ID_MASK;
5310
5311 /* XXX: we ignore stream (re)-prioritization scheme. However, a
5312 * minimal processing is to check against self-dependency error */
5313 if (stream_dependency == stream_id) {
5314 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(
5315 w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5316 "frame error: self-dependency in HEADERS on stream %d",
5317 stream_id);
5318 }
5319 }
5320 if (flags & HTTP2_FLAG_END_HEADERS) {
5321 return http2_conn_do_on_end_headers(w, stream_id, payload,
5322 ps_len(&payload), flags, 0);
5323 }
5324 return PARSE_OK;
5325}
5326
5327static int http2_conn_parse_push_promise(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5328 pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5329{
5330 pstream_t chunk;
5331 uint32_t promised_id;
5332
5333 assert(w->is_client);
5334 if (http2_payload_get_trimmed_chunk(payload, flags, &chunk) < 0) {
5335 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(
5336 w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5337 "frame error: PUSH_PROMISE with invalid padding");
5338 }
5339
5340 if (ps_get_be32(&chunk, &promised_id) < 0) {
5341 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(
5342 w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR,
5343 "frame error: PUSH_PROMISE too short to read promised id");
5344 }
5345 promised_id &= HTTP2_STREAM_ID_MASK;
5346
5347 if (http2_conn_check_peer_stream_id(w, promised_id)) {
5348 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5349 "frame error: promised_id is PUSH_PROMISE is "
5350 "not server stream %d",
5351 promised_id);
5352 }
5353
5354 if (!http2_conn_peer_stream_id_is_idle(w, promised_id)) {
5355 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5356 "frame error: invalid promised stream %d "
5357 "in PUSH_PROMISE on stream %d",
5358 promised_id, stream_id);
5359 }
5360 if (!http2_conn_is_server_push_enabled(w)) {
5361 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5362 "settings error: unexpected PUSH_PROMISE on "
5363 "stream %d (server push disabled)",
5364 stream_id);
5365 }
5366 w->promised_id = promised_id;
5367 if (flags & HTTP2_FLAG_END_HEADERS) {
5368 return http2_conn_do_on_end_headers(
5369 w, stream_id, payload, ps_len(&payload), flags, promised_id);
5370 }
5371 return PARSE_OK;
5372}
5373
5374static int http2_conn_parse_priority(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5375 pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5376{
5377 int len = ps_len(&payload);
5378 uint32_t stream_dependency;
5379 int weight;
5380
5381 if (ps_get_be32(&payload, &stream_dependency) < 0) {
5382 goto size_error;
5383 }
5384 stream_dependency &= HTTP2_STREAM_ID_MASK;
5385
5386 weight = ps_getc(&payload);
5387 if (weight < 0) {
5388 goto size_error;
5389 }
5390
5391 if (!ps_done(&payload)) {
5392 goto size_error;
5393 }
5394
5395 RETHROW(http2_stream_do_recv_priority(w, stream_id, stream_dependency));
5396 return PARSE_OK;
5397
5398size_error:
5399 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR,
5400 "frame error: PRIORITY with invalid size %d", len);
5401}
5402
5403static int http2_conn_parse_rst_stream(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5404 pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5405{
5406 uint32_t error_code;
5407
5408 if (ps_get_be32(&payload, &error_code) < 0) {
5409 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR,
5410 "frame error: RST_STREAM with invalid size %jd",
5411 ps_len(&payload));
5412 }
5413 RETHROW(http2_stream_do_recv_rst_stream(w, stream_id, error_code));
5414 return PARSE_OK;
5415}
5416
5417/* }}} */
5418/* {{{ Connection-Related Frame Handling */
5419
5420static int
5421http2_conn_on_peer_initial_window_size_changed(http2_conn_t *w, int32_t delta)
5422{
5423 int64_t new_size;
5424
5425 if (!delta) {
5426 return PARSE_OK;
5427 }
5428 qm_for_each_value(qstream, stream, &w->streams) {
5429 unsigned flags = stream->events;
5430
5431 if (!flags || flags & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_CLOSED) {
5432 continue;
5433 }
5434 new_size = (int64_t)stream->send_window + delta;
5435 if (new_size > HTTP2_LEN_WINDOW_SIZE_LIMIT) {
5436 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(
5437 w, FLOW_CONTROL_ERROR,
5438 "settings error: INITIAL_WINDOW_SIZE causes stream %d "
5439 "send-window to overflow (%jd out of range)",
5440 stream->id, new_size);
5441 }
5442 stream->send_window += delta;
5443 http2_stream_trace(
5444 w, stream, 2,
5445 "send-window updated by SETTINGS [new size %d, delta %d]",
5446 stream->send_window, delta);
5447 }
5448 return PARSE_OK;
5449}
5450
5451static int
5452http2_conn_process_peer_settings(http2_conn_t *w, uint16_t id, uint32_t val)
5453{
5454 int32_t delta;
5455
5456 switch (id) {
5457 case HTTP2_ID_HEADER_TABLE_SIZE:
5458 if (val != w->peer_settings.header_table_size) {
5459 w->enc.tbl_size_max = val;
5460 }
5461 w->peer_settings.header_table_size = val;
5462 break;
5463
5464 case HTTP2_ID_ENABLE_PUSH:
5465 if (val > 1) {
5466 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5467 "settings error: invalid ENABLE_PUSH (%u)", val);
5468 }
5469 w->peer_settings.enable_push = val;
5470 break;
5471
5472 case HTTP2_ID_MAX_CONCURRENT_STREAMS:
5473 OPT_SET(w->peer_settings.max_concurrent_streams, val);
5474 break;
5475
5476 case HTTP2_ID_MAX_FRAME_SIZE:
5477 if (val < HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE_INIT ||
5478 val > HTTP2_LEN_MAX_FRAME_SIZE)
5479 {
5480 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(
5481 w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5482 "settings error: invalid FRAME_SIZE (%u out of range)", val);
5483 }
5484 w->peer_settings.max_frame_size = val;
5485 break;
5486
5487 case HTTP2_ID_MAX_HEADER_LIST_SIZE:
5488 OPT_SET(w->peer_settings.max_header_list_size, val);
5489 break;
5490
5491 case HTTP2_ID_INITIAL_WINDOW_SIZE:
5492 if (val > HTTP2_LEN_WINDOW_SIZE_LIMIT) {
5493 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FLOW_CONTROL_ERROR,
5494 "settings error: invalid "
5495 "INITIAL_WINDOW_SIZE (%u out of range)",
5496 val);
5497 }
5498
5499 /* XXX Make sure that the cast '(int32_t)val' is legitimate. */
5500 STATIC_ASSERT(HTTP2_LEN_WINDOW_SIZE_LIMIT == INT32_MAX);
5501
5502 delta = (int32_t)val - w->peer_settings.initial_window_size;
5503 w->peer_settings.initial_window_size = val;
5504 RETHROW(http2_conn_on_peer_initial_window_size_changed(w, delta));
5505 break;
5506
5507 default:
5508 http2_conn_trace(w, 2,
5509 "ignored unknown setting from peer [id %d, val %u]",
5510 id, val);
5511 }
5512 return PARSE_OK;
5513}
5514
5515static int
5516http2_conn_parse_settings(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5517{
5518 size_t len = ps_len(&payload);
5519 int nb_items;
5520
5521 if ((flags & HTTP2_FLAG_ACK) && len) {
5522 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(
5523 w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR,
5524 "frame error: invalid SETTINGS (ACK_FLAG with non-zero payload)");
5525 }
5526 if (flags & HTTP2_FLAG_ACK) {
5527 if (w->preface_acked) {
5528 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5529 "frame error: invalid SETTINGS (ACK with "
5530 "no previously sent SETTINGS)");
5531 }
5532 w->preface_acked = true;
5533 return PARSE_OK;
5534 }
5535 if (len % HTTP2_LEN_SETTINGS_ITEM != 0) {
5536 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5537 "frame error: invalid SETTINGS (payload size "
5538 "not a multiple of 6)");
5539 }
5540 /* new peer settings */
5541 nb_items = len / HTTP2_LEN_SETTINGS_ITEM;
5542 for (int i = 0; i != nb_items; i++) {
5543 uint16_t id = __ps_get_be16(&payload);
5544 uint32_t val = __ps_get_be32(&payload);
5545
5546 RETHROW(http2_conn_process_peer_settings(w, id, val));
5547 }
5548 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(w, HTTP2_LEN_NO_PAYLOAD, HTTP2_TYPE_SETTINGS,
5549 HTTP2_FLAG_ACK, HTTP2_ID_NO_STREAM);
5550 return PARSE_OK;
5551}
5552
5553static int
5554http2_conn_parse_ping(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5555{
5556 size_t len = ps_len(&payload);
5557
5558 STATIC_ASSERT(HTTP2_LEN_PING_PAYLOAD == 8);
5559 if (len != HTTP2_LEN_PING_PAYLOAD) {
5560 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR,
5561 "frame error: invalid PING size");
5562 }
5563 if (w->frame.flags & HTTP2_FLAG_ACK) {
5564 /* TODO: correlate the acked frame with a sent one and estimate the
5565 * ping rtt. */
5566 } else {
5567 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(w, HTTP2_LEN_PING_PAYLOAD, HTTP2_TYPE_PING,
5568 HTTP2_FLAG_ACK, HTTP2_ID_NO_STREAM);
5569 ob_add(&w->ob, payload.p, HTTP2_LEN_PING_PAYLOAD);
5570 }
5571 return PARSE_OK;
5572}
5573
5574static int
5575http2_conn_parse_goaway(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5576{
5577 size_t len = w->frame.len;
5578 uint32_t last_stream_id;
5579 uint32_t error_code;
5580 pstream_t debug;
5581
5582 STATIC_ASSERT(HTTP2_LEN_GOAWAY_PAYLOAD_MIN
5583 == sizeof last_stream_id + sizeof error_code);
5584 if (len < HTTP2_LEN_GOAWAY_PAYLOAD_MIN
5585 || ps_get_be32(&payload, &last_stream_id) < 0)
5586 {
5587 goto size_error;
5588 }
5589 last_stream_id &= HTTP2_STREAM_ID_MASK;
5590
5591 if (ps_get_be32(&payload, &error_code)) {
5592 goto size_error;
5593 }
5594 debug = payload;
5595 http2_conn_trace(w, 2, "received GOAWAY "
5596 "[last stream %d, error code %d, debug <%*pM>]",
5597 last_stream_id, error_code, PS_FMT_ARG(&debug));
5598
5599 if (error_code == HTTP2_CODE_NO_ERROR) {
5600 if (last_stream_id != HTTP2_ID_MAX_STREAM) {
5601 if (w->goaway_recv) {
5602 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5603 "frame error: second shutdown GOAWAY");
5604 }
5605
5606 http2_conn_process_state_change_goaway_recv(w, last_stream_id);
5607 } else {
5608 http2_conn_process_state_change_will_close_recv(w);
5609 }
5610 } else {
5611 http2_conn_process_state_change_abort_recv(w);
5612 }
5613 return PARSE_OK;
5614
5615size_error:
5616 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR, "frame error: invalid GOAWAY size");
5617}
5618
5619static int http2_conn_parse_window_update(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id,
5620 pstream_t payload, uint8_t flags)
5621{
5622 uint32_t incr;
5623 int64_t new_size;
5624
5625 if (ps_get_be32(&payload, &incr) < 0 || !ps_done(&payload)) {
5626 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR,
5627 "frame error: invalid WINDOW_UPDATE size");
5628 }
5629 incr &= HTTP2_LEN_MAX_WINDOW_UPDATE_INCR;
5630
5631 if (stream_id) {
5632 /* incr conn send-window */
5633 return http2_stream_do_recv_window_update(w, stream_id, incr);
5634 }
5635 if (!incr) {
5636 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5637 "frame error: 0 increment in WINDOW_UPDATE");
5638 }
5639 new_size = (int64_t)w->send_window + incr;
5640 if (new_size > HTTP2_LEN_WINDOW_SIZE_LIMIT) {
5641 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FLOW_CONTROL_ERROR,
5642 "flow control: "
5643 "tried to increment send-window beyond limit "
5644 "[cur %d, incr %d, new %jd]",
5645 w->send_window, incr, new_size);
5646 }
5647 http2_conn_trace(w, 2, "send-window increment [new size %jd, incr %d]",
5648 new_size, incr);
5649 w->send_window = new_size;
5650 return PARSE_OK;
5651}
5652
5653/* }}} */
5654/* {{{ Receive Buffer Framing */
5655
5656static bool http2_is_known_frame_type(uint8_t type)
5657{
5658 return type <= HTTP2_TYPE_CONTINUATION;
5659}
5660
5661static int http2_conn_check_frame_type_role(http2_conn_t *w)
5662{
5663 if (!w->is_client && w->frame.type == HTTP2_TYPE_PUSH_PROMISE) {
5664 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5665 "PUSH_PROMISE received from client");
5666 }
5667 return PARSE_OK;
5668}
5669
5670/** Check if current frame type is compatible with the level `stream_id`.
5671 * Note: 0 => Connection-level frame, > 0 => Stream-level frame */
5672static int http2_conn_check_frame_type_level(http2_conn_t *w)
5673{
5674 uint8_t type = w->frame.type;
5675 uint32_t stream_id = w->frame.stream_id;
5676
5677 switch (type) {
5678 case HTTP2_TYPE_DATA:
5679 case HTTP2_TYPE_HEADERS:
5680 case HTTP2_TYPE_PRIORITY:
5681 case HTTP2_TYPE_RST_STREAM:
5682 case HTTP2_TYPE_PUSH_PROMISE:
5683 case HTTP2_TYPE_CONTINUATION:
5684 if (likely(stream_id)) {
5685 return PARSE_OK;
5686 }
5687 break;
5688
5689 case HTTP2_TYPE_SETTINGS:
5690 case HTTP2_TYPE_PING:
5691 case HTTP2_TYPE_GOAWAY:
5692 if (likely(!stream_id)) {
5693 return PARSE_OK;
5694 }
5695 break;
5696
5697 case HTTP2_TYPE_WINDOW_UPDATE:
5698 return PARSE_OK;
5699
5700 default:
5701 assert(false && "unexpected frame type");
5702 }
5703 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5704 "frame error: type %x incompatible with stream id %u",
5705 type, stream_id);
5706}
5707
5708static int http2_conn_check_frame_size(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t len)
5709{
5710 uint32_t lim = http2_get_settings(w).max_frame_size;
5711
5712 if (len > lim) {
5713 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, FRAME_SIZE_ERROR,
5714 "frame error: size %u > setting limit %u", len, lim);
5715 }
5716 return PARSE_OK;
5717}
5718
5719
5720static int http2_conn_parse_preface(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
5721{
5722 /* XXX: the client preamble consists of the magic preface + the initial
5723 * settings frame. For the server, the preamble consists of the initial
5724 * settings frame, IoW, the server preface is empty. So, both client and
5725 * server send the connection PREAMBLE in reaction to parsing the other's
5726 * PREFACE!
5727 */
5728 if (!w->is_client) {
5729 size_t len = http2_client_preamble_g.len;
5730 pstream_t preface_recv;
5731
5732 if (ps_get_ps(ps, len, &preface_recv) < 0) {
5733 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
5734 }
5735 if (!lstr_equal(LSTR_PS_V(&preface_recv), http2_client_preamble_g)) {
5736 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5737 "parse error: invalid preface");
5738 }
5739 }
5740 http2_conn_send_preface(w);
5741 http2_conn_send_init_settings(w);
5742 return PARSE_OK;
5743}
5744
5745static int http2_conn_parse_init_settings_hdr(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
5746{
5747 if (http2_parse_frame_hdr(ps, &w->frame) < 0) {
5748 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
5749 }
5750 if (w->frame.len > http2_get_settings(w).max_frame_size ||
5751 w->frame.type != HTTP2_TYPE_SETTINGS ||
5752 w->frame.flags & HTTP2_FLAG_ACK ||
5753 w->frame.len % HTTP2_LEN_SETTINGS_ITEM != 0)
5754 {
5755 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5756 "invalid preamble (not a setting frame)");
5757 }
5758
5759 return PARSE_OK;
5760}
5761
5762static int http2_conn_parse_common_hdr(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
5763{
5764 if (http2_parse_frame_hdr(ps, &w->frame) < 0) {
5765 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
5766 }
5767
5768 RETHROW(http2_conn_check_frame_size(w, w->frame.len));
5769 if (http2_is_known_frame_type(w->frame.type)) {
5770 RETHROW(http2_conn_check_frame_type_level(w));
5771 RETHROW(http2_conn_check_frame_type_role(w));
5772 }
5773
5774 return PARSE_OK;
5775}
5776
5777static int http2_conn_parse_payload(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
5778{
5779 pstream_t payload;
5780 size_t len = w->frame.len;
5781 uint32_t stream_id = w->frame.stream_id;
5782 uint8_t flags = w->frame.flags;
5783
5784 if (ps_get_ps(ps, len, &payload) < 0) {
5785 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
5786 }
5787
5788 switch (w->frame.type) {
5789 case HTTP2_TYPE_DATA:
5790 return http2_conn_parse_data(w, stream_id, payload, flags);
5791
5792 case HTTP2_TYPE_HEADERS:
5793 return http2_conn_parse_headers(w, stream_id, payload, flags);
5794
5795 case HTTP2_TYPE_PRIORITY:
5796 return http2_conn_parse_priority(w, stream_id, payload, flags);
5797
5798 case HTTP2_TYPE_RST_STREAM:
5799 return http2_conn_parse_rst_stream(w, stream_id, payload, flags);
5800
5801 case HTTP2_TYPE_SETTINGS:
5802 return http2_conn_parse_settings(w, payload, flags);
5803
5804 case HTTP2_TYPE_PUSH_PROMISE:
5805 return http2_conn_parse_push_promise(w, stream_id, payload, flags);
5806
5807 case HTTP2_TYPE_PING:
5808 return http2_conn_parse_ping(w, payload, flags);
5809
5810 case HTTP2_TYPE_GOAWAY:
5811 return http2_conn_parse_goaway(w, payload, flags);
5812
5813 case HTTP2_TYPE_WINDOW_UPDATE:
5814 return http2_conn_parse_window_update(w, stream_id, payload, flags);
5815
5816 case HTTP2_TYPE_CONTINUATION:
5817 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5818 "frame error: CONTINUATION with no previous "
5819 "HEADERS or PUSH_PROMISE");
5820
5821 default:
5822 break;
5823 }
5824 http2_conn_trace(w, 2, "discarded received frame with unknown type %d",
5825 w->frame.type);
5826 return PARSE_OK;
5827}
5828
5829/* TODO use some box drawing to explain the mechanics */
5830static int http2_conn_parse_cont_hdr(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t ps)
5831{
5832 http2_frame_info_t frame;
5833
5834 if (ps_skip(&ps, w->frame.len + w->cont_chunk) < 0 ||
5835 http2_parse_frame_hdr(&ps, &frame) < 0)
5836 {
5837 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
5838 }
5839
5840 RETHROW(http2_conn_check_frame_size(w, frame.len));
5841 assert(w->frame.stream_id);
5842 if (frame.type != HTTP2_TYPE_CONTINUATION ||
5843 frame.stream_id != w->frame.stream_id)
5844 {
5845 HTTP2_THROW_ERR(w, PROTOCOL_ERROR,
5846 "frame error: missing CONTINUATION");
5847 }
5848 w->frame.flags |= (frame.flags & HTTP2_FLAG_END_HEADERS);
5849 w->cont_chunk += HTTP2_LEN_FRAME_HDR + frame.len;
5850 return PARSE_OK;
5851}
5852
5853static int http2_conn_parse_cont_fragment(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
5854{
5855 size_t initial_len = w->frame.len;
5856 size_t len = w->frame.len + w->cont_chunk;
5857 uint32_t stream_id = w->frame.stream_id;
5858 uint8_t flags = w->frame.flags;
5859 uint32_t promised_id = w->promised_id;
5860
5861 assert(w->cont_chunk);
5862 if (ps_len(ps) < len) {
5863 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
5864 }
5865 if (flags & HTTP2_FLAG_END_HEADERS) {
5866 pstream_t payload;
5867
5868 payload = __ps_get_ps(ps, len);
5869 assert((!!promised_id) ^ (w->frame.type == HTTP2_TYPE_HEADERS));
5870 return http2_conn_do_on_end_headers(w, stream_id, payload,
5871 initial_len, flags, promised_id);
5872 }
5873 /* XXX: No END_HEADERS yet: continue to keep the chunks in place to be
5874 * reassembled later in http2_conn_do_on_end_headers() when END_HEADERS
5875 * arrives. */
5876 return PARSE_OK;
5877}
5878
5879static int http2_conn_parse_shutdown_sent(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
5880{
5881 __ps_skip(ps, ps_len(ps));
5882 return PARSE_MISSING_DATA;
5883}
5884
5885/* }}} */
5886/* {{{ Connection IO Event Handlers */
5887
5888/* parser state(s) */
5889typedef enum {
5890 HTTP2_PARSE_PREAMBLE = 0,
5891 HTTP2_PARSE_INIT_SETTINGS_HDR = 1,
5892 HTTP2_PARSE_COMMON_HDR = 2,
5893 HTTP2_PARSE_PAYLOAD = 3,
5894 HTTP2_PARSE_CONT_HDR = 4,
5895 HTTP2_PARSE_CONT_FRAGMENT = 5,
5896 HTTP2_PARSE_GOAWAY_SENT = 6,
5897} parse_state_t;
5898
5899static void http2_conn_process_eof_read(http2_conn_t *w, pstream_t *ps)
5900{
5901 bool pending = http2_conn_has_pending_streams(w);
5902
5903 assert(w->eof_read && !w->eof_processed);
5904 w->eof_processed = true;
5905
5906 if (w->closing && !pending) {
5907 /* we are already in, or about to transition to fin_time_wait. */
5908 return;
5909 }
5910 http2_conn_process_state_change_unexpected_eof(w);
5911}
5912
5913static void http2_conn_process_input_buffer(http2_conn_t *w)
5914{
5915 int rc;
5916 pstream_t ps;
5917 pstream_t ps_tmp;
5918
5919 assert(!w->abort_recv);
5920 ps = ps_initsb(&w->ibuf);
5921 do {
5922 parse_state_t state = w->state;
5923
5924 switch (state) {
5925 case HTTP2_PARSE_PREAMBLE:
5926 rc = http2_conn_parse_preface(w, &ps);
5927 if (rc == PARSE_OK) {
5928 state = HTTP2_PARSE_INIT_SETTINGS_HDR;
5929 }
5930 break;
5931 case HTTP2_PARSE_INIT_SETTINGS_HDR:
5932 rc = http2_conn_parse_init_settings_hdr(w, &ps);
5933 if (rc == PARSE_OK) {
5934 state = HTTP2_PARSE_PAYLOAD;
5935 }
5936 break;
5937 case HTTP2_PARSE_COMMON_HDR:
5938 rc = http2_conn_parse_common_hdr(w, &ps);
5939 if (rc == PARSE_OK) {
5940 state = HTTP2_PARSE_PAYLOAD;
5941 }
5942 break;
5943 case HTTP2_PARSE_PAYLOAD:
5944 ps_tmp = ps;
5945 rc = http2_conn_parse_payload(w, &ps);
5946 if (rc == PARSE_OK) {
5947 uint8_t t = w->frame.type;
5948
5949 if (t == HTTP2_TYPE_HEADERS || t == HTTP2_TYPE_PUSH_PROMISE) {
5950 if (w->frame.flags & HTTP2_FLAG_END_HEADERS) {
5951 state = HTTP2_PARSE_COMMON_HDR;
5952 } else {
5953 /* reset to a new *multi-frame* in ibuf: composed of
5954 * the initial payload (of the current HEADERS or
5955 * PUSH_PROMISE) and a chunk that spans one ore
5956 * CONTINUATION frame(s) */
5957 w->cont_chunk = 0;
5958 w->promised_id = 0;
5959 ps = ps_tmp;
5960 state = HTTP2_PARSE_CONT_HDR;
5961 }
5962 } else {
5963 state = HTTP2_PARSE_COMMON_HDR;
5964 }
5965 }
5966 break;
5967 case HTTP2_PARSE_CONT_HDR:
5968 rc = http2_conn_parse_cont_hdr(w, ps);
5969 if (rc == PARSE_OK) {
5970 state = HTTP2_PARSE_CONT_FRAGMENT;
5971 }
5972 break;
5973 case HTTP2_PARSE_CONT_FRAGMENT:
5974 rc = http2_conn_parse_cont_fragment(w, &ps);
5975 if (rc == PARSE_OK) {
5976 assert(w->frame.type == HTTP2_TYPE_HEADERS
5977 || w->frame.type == HTTP2_TYPE_PUSH_PROMISE);
5978 if (w->frame.flags & HTTP2_FLAG_END_HEADERS) {
5979 state = HTTP2_PARSE_COMMON_HDR;
5980 } else {
5981 /* continue the *multi-frame* */
5982 state = HTTP2_PARSE_CONT_HDR;
5983 }
5984 }
5985 break;
5986 case HTTP2_PARSE_GOAWAY_SENT:
5987 rc = http2_conn_parse_shutdown_sent(w, &ps);
5988 break;
5989 }
5990 if (rc == PARSE_ERROR) {
5991 assert(w->abort_in_flight);
5992 state = HTTP2_PARSE_GOAWAY_SENT;
5993 rc = PARSE_OK;
5994 }
5995 w->state = state;
5996 } while (rc == PARSE_OK);
5997 sb_skip_upto(&w->ibuf, ps.s);
5998
5999 /* prune useless stream objects created during parsing */
6000 dlist_for_each_entry(http2_stream_t, stream, &w->inactive_stream_list,
6001 class_link)
6002 {
6003 http2_stream_delete(&stream);
6004 }
6005
6006 if (w->abort_in_flight) {
6007 http2_conn_close_streams_internal(w, 0, 0);
6008 }
6009
6010 if (w->eof_read && !w->eof_processed) {
6011 http2_conn_process_eof_read(w, &ps);
6012 }
6013}
6014
6015static void http2_conn_set_mask(http2_conn_t *w)
6016{
6017 int mask = POLLIN;
6018
6019 if (w->eof_read) {
6020 mask = 0;
6021 }
6022
6023 if (!ob_is_empty(&w->ob) || w->async_write) {
6024 mask |= POLLOUT;
6025 w->async_write = false;
6026 }
6027
6028 if (w->ssl) {
6029 if (SSL_want_read(w->ssl)) {
6030 mask |= POLLIN;
6031 }
6032 if (SSL_want_write(w->ssl)) {
6033 mask |= POLLOUT;
6034 }
6035 }
6036
6037 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "set mask %d", mask);
6038 el_fd_set_mask(w->ev, mask);
6039}
6040
6041static void http2_conn_process_idle_socket(http2_conn_t *w)
6042{
6043 if (w->fin_time_wait) {
6044 http2_conn_process_state_change_fin_time_wait_idle_timeout(w);
6045 return;
6046 }
6047
6048 /* FIXME: handle the "unlikely" case of being blocked because of the
6049 * peer's flow-control algorithm and react accordingly. */
6050 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "idle socket timeout");
6051 if (w->goaway_in_flight) {
6052 w->done = true;
6053 } else {
6054 http2_conn_send_shutdown(w, LSTR("IDLE_TIMEOUT"));
6055 }
6056}
6057
6058static int http2_conn_process_streams_output(http2_conn_t *w)
6059{
6060 if (w->state > HTTP2_PARSE_INIT_SETTINGS_HDR) {
6061 http2_conn_on_streams_can_write(w);
6062 }
6063 return 0;
6064}
6065
6066static void http2_conn_process_async_inputs(http2_conn_t *w)
6067{
6068 if (unlikely(w->send_goaway && !w->closing)) {
6069 /* TODO: Possible Enhancements: (1) In client, stop sending requests
6070 * and delay the GOAWAY until no pending streams. (2) In server, send
6071 * a "will-close" GOAWAY first and then send the final GOAWAY after a
6072 * timeout as recommended by the standard. */
6073 http2_conn_send_shutdown(w, LSTR("UPPER_LAYER_REQUEST"));
6074 }
6075}
6076
6077static void http2_conn_process_no_pending_streams(http2_conn_t *w)
6078{
6079 bool pending = http2_conn_has_pending_streams(w);
6080
6081 if (unlikely(w->done)) {
6082 return;
6083 }
6084 if (unlikely(w->closing && !pending && !w->fin_time_wait)) {
6085 http2_conn_process_state_change_fin_time_wait(w);
6086 }
6087}
6088
6089static void http2_conn_process_send_last_goaway_if_needed(http2_conn_t *w)
6090{
6091 if (likely(!w->fin_time_wait || w->done)) {
6092 return;
6093 }
6094
6095 if (likely(w->goaway_in_flight || w->abort_in_flight)) {
6096 /* final goaway is no longer possible or needed. */
6097 return;
6098 }
6099
6100 http2_conn_send_shutdown(w, LSTR_EMPTY_V);
6101}
6102
6103static int http2_conn_process_before_return_ev_loop(http2_conn_t **wp, int fd)
6104{
6105 http2_conn_t *w = *wp;
6106
6107 if (ob_is_empty(&w->ob)) {
6108 if (!w->done) {
6109 int timeout = w->idle_timeout;
6110
6111 if (unlikely(w->fin_time_wait)) {
6112 timeout = 1000; /* TODO: configurable goaway timeout */
6113 shutdown(fd, SHUT_WR);
6114 }
6115 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "watch activity timeout %d", timeout);
6116 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, timeout);
6117 }
6118 } else {
6119 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "unregister watch activity timer");
6120 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, 0);
6121 }
6122
6123 if (unlikely(w->fin_time_wait && w->eof_read && !w->done)) {
6124 http2_conn_process_state_change_fin_time_wait_eof_read(w);
6125 }
6126
6127 if (unlikely(w->done)) {
6128 return http2_conn_close_done(wp);
6129 }
6130
6131 http2_conn_set_mask(w);
6132 return 0;
6133}
6134
6135static int http2_conn_on_event(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
6136{
6137 http2_conn_t *w = priv.ptr;
6138
6139 http2_conn_trace(w, 4, "events 0x%x", events);
6140
6141 if (unlikely(events == EL_EVENTS_NOACT)) {
6142 http2_conn_process_idle_socket(w);
6143 } else if (unlikely(events & POLLERR)) {
6144 w->sock_err = true;
6145 w->closing = true;
6146 w->done = true;
6147 } else if (events & POLLIN) {
6148 http2_conn_read(w, fd);
6149 http2_conn_process_input_buffer(w);
6150 }
6151
6152 http2_conn_process_streams_output(w);
6153 http2_conn_process_async_inputs(w);
6154 http2_conn_process_no_pending_streams(w);
6155 http2_conn_process_send_last_goaway_if_needed(w);
6156 http2_conn_write(w, fd);
6157 http2_conn_process_before_return_ev_loop(&w, fd);
6158 return 0;
6159}
6160
6161/* {{{ Initial Phase I/O Handlers */
6162
6163/** Check the received connection preface.
6164 *
6165 * \return: -1 if preface is not valid, 0 if preface is not fully read, or 1
6166 * to indicate that validation is done. */
6167static int http2_conn_check_preface(http2_conn_t *w)
6168{
6169 pstream_t ps = ps_initsb(&w->ibuf);
6170 const unsigned hdrlen = 9;
6171
6172 /* Early check of a partially received client preamble. Strictly speaking,
6173 * this is not needed save for conformance testing. */
6174 if (!w->is_client && ps_len(&ps) < http2_client_preamble_g.len + hdrlen) {
6175 int n = MIN((unsigned)http2_client_preamble_g.len, ps_len(&ps));
6176 pstream_t tmp = ps_init(ps.p, n);
6177
6178 THROW_ERR_IF(!ps_memequal(&tmp, http2_client_preamble_g.data, n));
6179 }
6180
6181 if (!ps_has(&ps, w->is_client ? hdrlen : http2_client_preamble_g.len +
6182 hdrlen))
6183 {
6184 return w->eof_read || w->sock_err ? -1 : 0;
6185 }
6186
6187 /* TODO: rework the main parser to exclude the initial phase parsing. */
6188 if (w->state == HTTP2_PARSE_PREAMBLE) {
6189 THROW_ERR_IF(http2_conn_parse_preface(w, &ps) != 0);
6190 w->state = HTTP2_PARSE_INIT_SETTINGS_HDR;
6191 }
6192 THROW_ERR_IF(http2_conn_parse_init_settings_hdr(w, &ps) != 0);
6193 w->state = HTTP2_PARSE_PAYLOAD;
6194 sb_skip_upto(&w->ibuf, ps.p);
6195 return 1;
6196}
6197
6198static int
6199http2_conn_on_preface_wait(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
6200{
6201 http2_conn_t *w = priv.ptr;
6202 int rc;
6203
6204 if (events == EL_EVENTS_NOACT) {
6205 return http2_conn_close_preface_wait_timeout(&w);
6206 }
6207
6208 if (events & POLLIN) {
6209 http2_conn_read(w, fd);
6210 }
6211
6212 /* Write our preface to the socket (if still in buffer). */
6213 /* XXX: Not all servers send their preface right after they accept the
6214 * connection. Some wait to receive from the client to send their preface.
6215 */
6216 http2_conn_write(w, fd);
6217
6218 if (w->sock_err) {
6219 return http2_conn_close_preface_wait_socket_error(&w);
6220 }
6221
6222 rc = http2_conn_check_preface(w);
6223
6224 if (rc < 0) {
6225 return http2_conn_close_invalid_preface(&w);
6226 }
6227
6228 if (rc == 0) { /* In progress (wait for the connection preface). */
6229 int mask = POLLIN;
6230
6231 if (!ob_is_empty(&w->ob) || (w->ssl && SSL_want_write(w->ssl))) {
6232 mask |= POLLOUT;
6233 }
6234 el_fd_set_mask(evh, mask);
6235 return 0;
6236 }
6237
6238 http2_conn_process_state_change_preface_received(w);
6239 http2_conn_process_input_buffer(w);
6240
6241 el_fd_set_hook(evh, &http2_conn_on_event);
6242 return http2_conn_on_event(evh, fd, events & ~POLLIN, priv);
6243}
6244
6245static int http2_conn_tls_handshake(http2_conn_t *w, el_t evh, int fd)
6246{
6247 switch (ssl_do_handshake(w->ssl, evh, fd, NULL)) {
6248 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_SUCCESS:
6249 return 1;
6250 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_PENDING:
6251 return 0;
6252 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_CLOSED:
6253 case SSL_HANDSHAKE_ERROR:
6254 break;
6255 }
6256 return -1;
6257}
6258
6259/* RFC9113 ยง3.4. HTTP/2 Connection Preface */
6260static int http2_conn_pack_preface(http2_conn_t *w)
6261{
6262 /* TODO: To rework. */
6263 /* As client: this writes the connection preface to w->ob. */
6264 http2_conn_process_input_buffer(w);
6265 RETHROW(w->state != HTTP2_PARSE_PREAMBLE);
6266 return 0;
6267}
6268
6269static int http2_conn_on_connect(el_t evh, int fd, short events, data_t priv)
6270{
6271 http2_conn_t *w = priv.ptr;
6272
6273 if (events == EL_EVENTS_NOACT) {
6274 return http2_conn_close_connect_timeout(&w);
6275 }
6276
6277 if (w->is_client && !w->connected) {
6278 int rc = socket_connect_status(fd);
6279
6280 if (rc < 0) {
6281 return http2_conn_close_connect_error(&w);
6282 }
6283 if (rc == 0) { /* In progress (wait for the socket to be connected) */
6284 return 0;
6285 }
6286 }
6287
6288 if (!w->connected) {
6289 http2_conn_process_state_change_socket_connected(w, fd);
6290 }
6291
6292 if (w->ssl) {
6293 int rc = http2_conn_tls_handshake(w, evh, fd);
6294
6295 if (rc < 0) {
6296 return http2_conn_close_tls_handshake_error(&w);
6297 }
6298 if (rc == 0) { /* In progress (wait for the tls handshake) */
6299 return 0;
6300 }
6301
6302 if (w->is_client) {
6303 /* ???: Couldn't this verification be replaced by adding the ssl
6304 * flag SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT in httpc_cfg_tls_init to
6305 * the verify_mode option.
6306 */
6307 X509 *cert = SSL_get_peer_certificate(w->ssl);
6308
6309 if (unlikely(!cert)) {
6310 return http2_conn_close_tls_no_peer_certificate_error(&w);
6311 }
6312 X509_free(cert);
6313 }
6314 }
6315
6316 if (http2_conn_pack_preface(w) < 0) {
6317 return http2_conn_close_error_pack_preface(&w);
6318 }
6319
6320 el_fd_set_hook(evh, &http2_conn_on_preface_wait);
6321 return http2_conn_on_preface_wait(evh, fd, events, priv);
6322}
6323
6324/* }}} */
6325/* }}} */
6326/* {{{ HTTP2 Server Adaptation */
6327
6328typedef struct http2_server_t {
6329 http2_conn_t * conn;
6330 httpd_cfg_t * httpd_cfg;
6331 dlist_t active_httpds;
6332 dlist_t idle_httpds;
6333 dlist_t http2_link;
6334} http2_server_t;
6335
6336static http2_server_t *http2_server_init(http2_server_t *w)
6337{
6338 p_clear(w, 1);
6339 dlist_init(&w->active_httpds);
6340 dlist_init(&w->idle_httpds);
6341 dlist_init(&w->http2_link);
6342 return w;
6343}
6344
6345static void http2_server_wipe(http2_server_t *w)
6346{
6347 dlist_remove(&w->http2_link);
6348 httpd_cfg_delete(&w->httpd_cfg);
6349}
6350
6351GENERIC_NEW(http2_server_t, http2_server);
6352GENERIC_DELETE(http2_server_t, http2_server);
6353
6354typedef struct httpd_http2_ctx_t {
6355 httpd_t *httpd;
6356 http2_server_t *server;
6357 dlist_t http2_link;
6358
6359 /* offset into httpd's ob */
6360 int http2_sync_mark;
6361 /* request converted to chunked encoding: payload with no Content-Length
6362 * header */
6363 uint32_t http2_chunked : 1;
6364 uint32_t http2_stream_id : 31;
6365} httpd_http2_ctx_t;
6366
6367static httpd_http2_ctx_t *httpd_http2_ctx_init(httpd_http2_ctx_t *ctx)
6368{
6369 p_clear(ctx, 1);
6370 dlist_init(&ctx->http2_link);
6371 return ctx;
6372}
6373
6374static void httpd_http2_ctx_wipe(httpd_http2_ctx_t *ctx)
6375{
6376 dlist_remove(&ctx->http2_link);
6377}
6378
6379GENERIC_NEW(httpd_http2_ctx_t, httpd_http2_ctx);
6380GENERIC_DELETE(httpd_http2_ctx_t, httpd_http2_ctx);
6381
6382static int
6383httpd_spawn_as_http2(int fd, sockunion_t *peer_su, httpd_cfg_t *cfg)
6384{
6385 http2_server_t *w;
6386 http2_conn_t *conn;
6387
6388 conn = http2_conn_new();
6389 if (cfg->ssl_ctx) {
6390 conn->ssl = SSL_new(cfg->ssl_ctx);
6391 }
6392 conn->settings = http2_default_settings_g;
6393 cfg->nb_conns++;
6394 fd_set_features(fd, FD_FEAT_TCP_NODELAY);
6395 conn->ev = el_fd_register(fd, true, POLLIN, http2_conn_on_connect, conn);
6396 conn->idle_timeout = cfg->noact_delay;
6397 el_fd_watch_activity(conn->ev, POLLIN, conn->idle_timeout);
6398 w = http2_server_new();
6399 w->conn = conn;
6400 w->httpd_cfg = httpd_cfg_retain(cfg);
6401 dlist_add_tail(&cfg->http2_httpd_list, &w->http2_link);
6402 conn->server_ctx = w;
6403 return 0;
6404}
6405
6406static httpd_t *
6407httpd_spawn_as_http2_stream(http2_server_t *server, uint32_t stream_id)
6408{
6409 httpd_t *w;
6410 httpd_cfg_t *cfg = server->httpd_cfg;
6411 httpd_http2_ctx_t *http2_ctx;
6412
6413 w = obj_new_of_class(httpd, cfg->httpd_cls);
6414 w->cfg = httpd_cfg_retain(cfg);
6415 cfg->nb_conns++;
6416 w->max_queries = 1;
6417 dlist_init(&w->httpd_link);
6418 w->http2_ctx = http2_ctx = httpd_http2_ctx_new();
6419 http2_ctx->httpd = w;
6420 http2_ctx->server = server;
6421 http2_ctx->http2_stream_id = stream_id;
6422 dlist_add_tail(&server->idle_httpds, &http2_ctx->http2_link);
6423 return w;
6424}

6426/** Streaming Layer Handlers */
6427
6428static void http2_stream_close_httpd(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream)
6429{
6430 httpd_t *httpd;
6431
6432 if (!stream->ibuf) {
6433 return;
6434 }
6435 httpd = container_of(stream->ibuf, httpd_t, ibuf);
6436 stream->ibuf = NULL;
6437 stream->ob = NULL;
6438 httpd_http2_ctx_delete(&httpd->http2_ctx);
6439 obj_release(&httpd);
6440 httpd_do_close(&httpd);
6441}
6442
6443static int httpd_unpack_http2_headers(httpd_t *w, http2_header_info_t *info,
6444 pstream_t headerlines, bool eos)
6445{
6446 sb_t *ibuf = &w->ibuf;
6447 enum http_parser_state state = w->state;
6448
6449 switch (state) {
6450 case HTTP_PARSER_IDLE:
6451 if (!info->method.s) {
6452 return -1;
6453 }
6454 sb_addf(ibuf, "%*pM %*pM HTTP/1.1\r\n", LSTR_FMT_ARG(info->method),
6455 LSTR_FMT_ARG(info->path));
6456 if (!(info->flags & HTTP2_HDR_FLAG_HAS_HOST)) {
6457 /* Host: is missing, copy it from :authority. */
6458 sb_addf(ibuf, "Host: %pL\r\n", &info->authority);
6459 } else {
6460 /* Host: is in headers: RFC9113 must equal to :authority. */
6461 /* TODO: check for equality with normalization */
6462 }
6463 sb_add_ps(ibuf, headerlines);
6464 switch (http_get_token_ps(ps_initlstr(&info->method))) {
6465 case HTTP_TK_POST:
6466 case HTTP_TK_PUT:
6467 if (!info->content_length.s) {
6468 lstr_t zero_clen_hdr = LSTR("Content-Length: 0\r\n");
6469 lstr_t chunked_te_hdr = LSTR("Transfer-Encoding: chunked\r\n");
6470
6471 sb_add_lstr(ibuf, eos ? zero_clen_hdr : chunked_te_hdr);
6472 }
6473 break;
6474 default:
6475 break;
6476 }
6477 sb_adds(ibuf, "\r\n");
6478 break;
6479 case HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_TRAILER:
6480 if (!eos) {
6481 return -1;
6482 }
6483 sb_add_ps(ibuf, headerlines);
6484 break;
6485 default:
6486 return -1;
6487 }
6488 return 0;
6489}
6490
6491static void
6492http2_stream_on_accept(http2_conn_t *conn, http2_stream_t *stream)
6493{
6494 httpd_t *httpd;
6495
6496 http2_server_t *server = conn->server_ctx;
6497
6498 assert(!stream->ibuf && !stream->ob);
6499 httpd = httpd_spawn_as_http2_stream(server, stream->id);
6500 stream->ibuf = &httpd->ibuf;
6501 stream->ob = &httpd->ob;
6502
6503 obj_retain(httpd);
6504}
6505
6506static void
6507http2_stream_on_headers_server(http2_conn_t *conn, http2_stream_t *stream,
6508 http2_header_info_t *info,
6509 pstream_t headerlines, bool eos)
6510{
6511 httpd_t *httpd = container_of(stream->ibuf, httpd_t, ibuf);
6512 sb_t *ibuf;
6513 pstream_t ps;
6514 int res;
6515
6516 if (httpd_unpack_http2_headers(httpd, info, headerlines, eos) < 0) {
6517 goto malformed_err;
6518 }
6519 ps = ps_initsb(ibuf = &httpd->ibuf);
6520 do {
6521 res = (*httpd_parsers[httpd->state])(httpd, &ps);
6522 } while (res == PARSE_OK);
6523 sb_skip_upto(ibuf, ps.p);
6524 if (res < 0 || (eos && httpd->state != HTTP_PARSER_CLOSE)) {
6525 goto malformed_err;
6526 }
6527 return;
6528malformed_err:
6529 http2_stream_send_reset(conn, stream,
6530 "malformed request [invalid headers]");
6531 http2_stream_close_httpd(conn, stream);
6532}
6533
6534static void
6535http2_stream_on_data_server(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
6536 pstream_t data, bool eos)
6537{
6538 httpd_t *httpd = container_of(stream->ibuf, httpd_t, ibuf);
6539 pstream_t ps;
6540 int len;
6541 int res;
6542
6543 assert(httpd->state == HTTP_PARSER_BODY
6544 || httpd->state == HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR);
6545 if (ps_done(&data) && !eos) {
6546 return;
6547 }
6548 switch(httpd->state) {
6549 case HTTP_PARSER_BODY:
6550 sb_add_ps(&httpd->ibuf, data);
6551 ps = ps_initsb(&httpd->ibuf);
6552 len = ps_len(&ps);
6553 if (httpd->chunk_length == len) {
6554 /* XXX: ensure that the last call to httpd_parse_body happens only
6555 * when eos arrives, possibly later in a 0-payload DATA frame. */
6556 if (!eos) {
6557 if (len <= 1) {
6558 return;
6559 }
6560 __ps_clip(&ps, --len);
6561 }
6562 } else if (httpd->chunk_length < len) {
6563 /* mismatch: DATA frames > content-length */
6564 if (!eos) {
6565 http2_stream_send_reset(
6566 w, stream, "malformed response [DATA > Content-Length]");
6567 }
6568 http2_stream_close_httpd(w, stream);
6569 return;
6570 }
6571 res = httpd_parse_body(httpd, &ps);
6572 switch (res) {
6573 case PARSE_MISSING_DATA:
6574 assert(httpd->state == HTTP_PARSER_BODY);
6575 sb_skip_upto(&httpd->ibuf, ps.p);
6576 if (eos) {
6577 /* mismatch: content-length > DATA frames.*/
6578 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2,
6579 "malformed response [unexpected eos]");
6580 http2_stream_close_httpd(w, stream);
6581 return;
6582 }
6583 break;
6584 case PARSE_OK:
6585 assert(httpd->state == HTTP_PARSER_CLOSE);
6586 assert(ps_done(&ps));
6587 assert(eos);
6588 sb_skip_upto(&httpd->ibuf, ps.p);
6589 return;
6590 case PARSE_ERROR:
6591 if (!eos) {
6592 http2_stream_send_reset(w, stream,
6593 "malformed response [invalid payload "
6594 "format or compression]");
6595 }
6596 http2_stream_close_httpd(w, stream);
6597 return;
6598 default:
6599 assert(0 && "unexpected result from httpd_parse_body");
6600 }
6601 break;
6602 case HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR:
6603 res = PARSE_OK;
6604 if (!ps_done(&data)) {
6605 char hdr[12];
6606
6607 http_chunk_patch(NULL, hdr, ps_len(&data));
6608 sb_add(&httpd->ibuf, hdr + 2, 10);
6609 sb_add_ps(&httpd->ibuf, data);
6610 sb_adds(&httpd->ibuf, "\r\n");
6611 ps = ps_initsb(&httpd->ibuf);
6612 len = ps_len(&ps);
6613 res = httpd_parse_chunk_hdr(httpd, &ps);
6614 if (res == PARSE_OK) {
6615 res = httpd_parse_chunk(httpd, &ps);
6616 }
6617 }
6618 if (eos && res == PARSE_OK) {
6619 sb_adds(&httpd->ibuf, "0\r\n\r\n");
6620 ps = ps_initsb(&httpd->ibuf);
6621 len = ps_len(&ps);
6622 res = httpd_parse_chunk_hdr(httpd, &ps);
6623 if (res == PARSE_OK) {
6624 res = httpd_parse_chunk(httpd, &ps);
6625 }
6626 }
6627 break;
6628 default:
6629 assert(0 && "invalid parser state");
6630 }
6631}
6632
6633static void http2_stream_on_reset_server(http2_conn_t *w,
6634 http2_stream_t *stream, bool remote)
6635{
6636 http2_stream_close_httpd(w, stream);
6637}
6638
6639/** Extract code/headerline from an upstream server (httpd) response in \p
6640 * chunk.
6641 *
6642 * Note: non-defensive parsing due to hypotheses about the way our HTTP/1.x
6643 * code works (see above). These hypotheses are guarded by assertions for now.
6644 *
6645 * FIXME: add unit tests to verify our hypotheses OR use defensive parsing.
6646 */
6647static void http_get_http2_response_hdrs(pstream_t *chunk, lstr_t *code,
6648 pstream_t *headerlines)
6649{
6650 byte *p;
6651 pstream_t line;
6652 pstream_t control;
6653
6654 p = memmem(chunk->p, ps_len(chunk), "\r\n\r\n", 4);
6655 assert(p);
6656 control = __ps_get_ps_upto(chunk, p + 2);
6657 __ps_skip(chunk, 2);
6658 p = memmem(control.p, ps_len(&control), "\r\n", 2);
6659 assert(p);
6660 line = __ps_get_ps_upto(&control, p);
6661 __ps_skip(&control, 2);
6662 __ps_skip(&line, sizeof("HTTP/1.x ") - 1);
6663 *code = LSTR_INIT_V(line.s, 3);
6664 __ps_skip(&line, 3);
6665 *headerlines = control;
6666}
6667
6668static void
6669http2_conn_assert_idle_httpd_invariants(httpd_t *nonnull httpd)
6670{
6671#ifndef NDEBUG
6672 assert(httpd->http2_ctx->http2_stream_id);
6673 /* don't support chunked httpd ob (yet) */
6674 assert(htlist_is_empty(&httpd->ob.chunks_list));
6675 /* one unique (non-answered) query or none if already answered. */
6676 assert(dlist_is_empty_or_singular(&httpd->query_list));
6677 if (ob_is_empty(&httpd->ob)) {
6678 /* no response was written yet */
6679 httpd_query_t *q;
6680
6681 assert(dlist_is_singular(&httpd->query_list));
6682 q = dlist_first_entry(&httpd->query_list, httpd_query_t, query_link);
6683 assert(!q->hdrs_done);
6684 }
6685#endif
6686}
6687
6688/* Stream the response of idle httpd (headers are not sent yet) */
6689static void http2_conn_stream_idle_httpd(http2_conn_t *w, httpd_t *httpd)
6690{
6691 http2_server_t *ctx = w->server_ctx;
6692 http2_stream_t *stream;
6693 pstream_t chunk;
6694 lstr_t code;
6695 pstream_t headerlines;
6696 int clen;
6697 httpd_http2_ctx_t *http2_ctx = httpd->http2_ctx;
6698
6699 http2_conn_assert_idle_httpd_invariants(httpd);
6700
6701 if (ob_is_empty(&httpd->ob)) {
6702 /* httpd ob is empty: the current query is not answered yet. */
6703 return;
6704 }
6705
6706 stream = http2_stream_get(w, http2_ctx->http2_stream_id);
6707 chunk = ps_initsb(&httpd->ob.sb);
6708 http_get_http2_response_hdrs(&chunk, &code, &headerlines);
6709 http2_stream_send_response_headers(w, stream, code, headerlines,
6710 http2_ctx, &clen);
6711 /* TODO: support 1xx informational responses (100-continue) */
6712 assert(clen >= 0 && "TODO: support chunked respones");
6713 http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark = clen;
6714 OB_WRAP(sb_skip_upto, &httpd->ob, chunk.p);
6715 if (!clen) {
6716 /* headers-only response (no-payload). */
6717 assert(ob_is_empty(&httpd->ob));
6718 assert(stream->events & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT);
6719 http2_stream_close_httpd(w, stream);
6720 return;
6721 }
6722 /* httpd becomes active: payload streaming phase (DATA). */
6723 dlist_move_tail(&ctx->active_httpds, &http2_ctx->http2_link);
6724}
6725
6726static void
6727http2_conn_assert_active_httpd_invariants(httpd_t *nonnull httpd)
6728{
6729#ifndef NDEBUG
6730 assert(httpd->http2_ctx->http2_stream_id);
6731 /* We don't support chunked httpd ob (yet) */
6732 assert(htlist_is_empty(&httpd->ob.chunks_list));
6733 /* We don't support chunked upstream responses yet */
6734 assert(httpd->http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark == httpd->ob.length);
6735#endif
6736}
6737
6738/** Stream the response of active httpd (payload sending).
6739 * \param max_sz: max size of data to send in this sending opportunity.
6740 */
6741static void
6742http2_conn_stream_active_httpd(http2_conn_t *w, httpd_t *httpd, int max_sz)
6743{
6744 httpd_http2_ctx_t *http2_ctx = httpd->http2_ctx;
6745 uint32_t stream_id = http2_ctx->http2_stream_id;
6746 http2_stream_t *stream;
6747 pstream_t chunk;
6748 int len;
6749 bool eos;
6750
6751 /* Calling code: max_sz must not exceed connection send window. */
6752 assert(max_sz <= w->send_window);
6753 http2_conn_assert_active_httpd_invariants(httpd);
6754
6755 stream = http2_stream_get(w, stream_id);
6756 len = MIN3(http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark, stream->send_window, max_sz);
6757 if (len <= 0) {
6758 return;
6759 }
6760 chunk = ps_initsb(&httpd->ob.sb);
6761 __ps_clip(&chunk, len);
6762 http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark -= len;
6763 eos = http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark == 0;
6764 http2_stream_send_data(w, stream, chunk, eos);
6765 OB_WRAP(sb_skip, &httpd->ob, len);
6766 if (eos) {
6767 /* No more data to send and stream was ended from our side. */
6768 assert(ob_is_empty(&httpd->ob));
6769 assert(stream->events & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_SENT);
6770 if (stream->events & HTTP2_STREAM_EV_EOS_RECV) {
6771 http2_stream_close_httpd(w, stream);
6772 } else {
6773 /* Early response case: (usually an error response) */
6774 }
6775 }
6776}
6777
6778static void http2_conn_on_streams_can_write_server(http2_conn_t *w)
6779{
6780 http2_server_t *ctx = w->server_ctx;
6781 dlist_t *httpds;
6782 bool can_progress;
6783
6784 httpds = &ctx->idle_httpds;
6785 dlist_for_each_entry(httpd_http2_ctx_t, httpd, httpds, http2_link) {
6786 http2_conn_stream_idle_httpd(w, httpd->httpd);
6787 }
6788 httpds = &ctx->active_httpds;
6789 do {
6790#define OB_SEND_ALLOC (8 << 10)
6791#define OB_HIGH_MARK (1 << 20)
6792 /* A simple DATA send "scheduling" algorithm for active streams as we
6793 * don't have a sophisticated frame-aware scheduler:
6794 * - To be fair, we allow each stream to send (i.e., output) up to
6795 * OB_SEND_ALLOC per each opportunity.
6796 * - We iterate over streams and continue this as long as one of
6797 * them can progress.
6798 * - However, we stop this once we have exceeded the OB_HIGH_MARK in
6799 * the conn buffer.
6800 * - This done because we don't want to delay too much the writing of
6801 * generated responses to the underlying socket (e.g., acks to
6802 * PING or SETTINGS in subsequent event callbacks to
6803 * http2_conn_on_event().
6804 */
6805 can_progress = false;
6806
6807 dlist_for_each_entry(httpd_http2_ctx_t, httpd, httpds, http2_link) {
6808 int ob_len = w->ob.length;
6809 int len;
6810
6811 if (ob_len >= OB_HIGH_MARK || w->send_window <= 0) {
6812 can_progress = false;
6813 break;
6814 }
6815 len = MIN(w->send_window, OB_SEND_ALLOC);
6816 http2_conn_stream_active_httpd(w, httpd->httpd, len);
6817 if (w->ob.length - ob_len >= len) {
6818 can_progress = true;
6819 }
6820 }
6821#undef OB_HIGH_MARK
6822#undef OB_SEND_ALLOC
6823 } while (can_progress);
6824}
6825
6826static void http2_conn_on_close_server(http2_conn_t *w)
6827{
6828 http2_server_delete(&w->server_ctx);
6829}
6830
6831static void http2_close_servers(httpd_cfg_t *cfg)
6832{
6833 dlist_t *servers = &cfg->http2_httpd_list;
6834
6835 dlist_for_each_entry(http2_server_t, server, servers, http2_link) {
6836 http2_conn_t *w = server->conn;
6837
6838 if (!w || !w->ev) {
6839 continue;
6840 }
6841 w->send_goaway = true;
6842 el_fd_set_mask(w->ev, POLLINOUT);
6843 }
6844}

6852 HTTP2_CTX_STATE_RESETTING,

6877}

6918static void http2_pool_remove_client(http2_client_t *client)
6919{
6920 http2_pool_t *pool = client->pool;
6921
6922 qm_del_key(qhttp2_clients, &pool->qclients, &client->peer_su);
6923 client->pool = NULL;
6924}

6926static void http2_pool_wipe(http2_pool_t *pool)
6927{
6928 qm_for_each_value(qhttp2_clients, client, &pool->qclients) {
6929 if (client->pool) {
6930 http2_pool_remove_client(client);
6931 }
6932 }
6933 qm_wipe(qhttp2_clients, &pool->qclients);
6934}

6950static void http2_client_wipe(http2_client_t *ctx)
6951{
6952 assert(dlist_is_empty(&ctx->active_httpcs));
6953 assert(dlist_is_empty(&ctx->idle_httpcs));
6954
6955 if (ctx->pool) {
6956 http2_pool_remove_client(ctx);
6957 }
