6964static http2_pool_t *http2_pool_get(httpc_cfg_t *cfg)
6965{
6966 if (!cfg->http2_pool) {
6967 cfg->http2_pool = http2_pool_new();
6968 }
6969 return cfg->http2_pool;
6970}
6971
6972static void httpc_http2_ctx_on_connect_error(dlist_t *httpcs, int errnum)
6973{
6974 dlist_for_each_entry(httpc_http2_ctx_t, httpc_http2, httpcs, http2_link) {
6975 httpc_t *httpc = httpc_http2->httpc;
6976
6977 if (httpc->pool && httpc->pool->on_connect_error) {
6978 (*httpc->pool->on_connect_error)(httpc, errnum);
6979 } else if (httpc->on_connect_error) {
6980 (*httpc->on_connect_error)(httpc, errnum);
6981 }
6982 }
6983}
6984
6985static void http2_conn_on_connect_error(http2_conn_t *w, int errnum)
6986{
6987 if (w->is_client) {
6988 http2_client_t *ctx = w->client_ctx;
6989
6990 if (ctx) {
6991 httpc_http2_ctx_on_connect_error(&ctx->idle_httpcs, errnum);
6992 httpc_http2_ctx_on_connect_error(&ctx->active_httpcs, errnum);
6993 }
6994 }
6995}
6996
6997static http2_conn_t *
6998http2_conn_connect_client_as(const sockunion_t *su, httpc_cfg_t *cfg)
6999{
7000 http2_conn_t *w;
7001 int flags = O_NONBLOCK | FD_FEAT_TCP_NODELAY;
7002 int fd;
7003
7004 fd = RETHROW_NP(
7005 connectx_as(-1, su, 1, NULL, SOCK_STREAM, IPPROTO_TCP, flags, 0));
7006 w = http2_conn_new();
7007 if (cfg->ssl_ctx) {
7008 w->ssl = SSL_new(cfg->ssl_ctx);
7009 }
7010 w->is_client = true;
7011 w->settings = http2_default_settings_g;
7012 w->idle_timeout = cfg->noact_delay;
7013 w->ev = el_fd_register(fd, true, POLLOUT, &http2_conn_on_connect, w);
7014 el_fd_watch_activity(w->ev, POLLINOUT, w->idle_timeout);
7015 return w;
7016}
7017
7018static http2_client_t *
7019http2_pool_get_client(httpc_cfg_t *cfg, const sockunion_t *peer_su)
7020{
7021 http2_client_t *client;
7022 http2_pool_t *pool = http2_pool_get(cfg);
7023 http2_conn_t *w;
7024 unsigned pos;
7025
7026 pos = qm_reserve(qhttp2_clients, &pool->qclients, peer_su, 0);
7027 if (pos & QHASH_COLLISION) {
7028 /* We already have a client for this address. */
7029 pos &= ~QHASH_COLLISION;
7030 return pool->qclients.values[pos];
7031 }
7032
7033 w = http2_conn_connect_client_as(peer_su, cfg);
7034 if (unlikely(!w)) {
7035 qm_del_at(qhttp2_clients, &pool->qclients, pos);
7036 return NULL;
7037 }
7038
7039 client = http2_client_new();
7040 client->pool = pool;
7041 client->peer_su = *peer_su;
7042 client->conn = w;
7043 w->client_ctx = client;
7044
7045 pool->qclients.values[pos] = client;
7046
7047 return client;
7048}
7049
7050static httpc_t *httpc_connect_as_http2(const sockunion_t *su,
7051 const sockunion_t *nullable su_src,
7052 httpc_cfg_t *cfg, httpc_pool_t *pool)
7053{
7054 httpc_t *w;
7055 http2_client_t *client;
7056
7057 client = RETHROW_P(http2_pool_get_client(cfg, su));
7058
7059 w = obj_new_of_class(httpc, cfg->httpc_cls);
7060 w->http2_ctx = httpc_http2_ctx_new();
7061 w->http2_ctx->httpc = w;
7062 w->http2_ctx->conn = client->conn;
7063 dlist_add_tail(&client->idle_httpcs, &w->http2_ctx->http2_link);
7064 w->connected_as_http2 = true;
7065 w->cfg = httpc_cfg_retain(cfg);
7066 w->max_queries = cfg->max_queries;
7067 w->busy = true;
7068 if (pool) {
7069 httpc_pool_attach(w, pool);
7070 }
7071 el_fd_set_mask(client->conn->ev, POLLINOUT);
7072 return w;
7073}
7074
7075/** Streaming Layer Handlers */
7076
7077/** Extract headerlines and special values from a downstream client (httpc)
7078 * request in \p chunk.
7079 *
7080 * Note: non-defensive parsing due to hypotheses about the way our HTTP/1.x
7081 * code works (see above). These hypotheses are guarded by assertions for now.
7082 *
7083 * FIXME: add unit tests to verify our hypotheses OR use defensive parsing.
7084 */
7085static void
7086http_get_http2_request_hdrs(pstream_t *chunk, lstr_t *method, lstr_t *scheme,
7087 lstr_t *path, lstr_t *authority,
7088 pstream_t *headerlines)
7089{
7090 byte *p;
7091 pstream_t line;
7092 pstream_t control;
7093 pstream_t ps;
7094
7095 p = memmem(chunk->p, ps_len(chunk), "\r\n\r\n", 4);
7096 assert(p);
7097 control = __ps_get_ps_upto(chunk, p + 2);
7098 __ps_skip(chunk, 2);
7099 p = memmem(control.p, ps_len(&control), "\r\n", 2);
7100 assert(p);
7101 line = __ps_get_ps_upto(&control, p);
7102 __ps_skip(&control, 2);
7103 __ps_shrink(&line, sizeof(" HTTP/1.1") - 1);
7104 p = memchr(line.p, ' ', ps_len(&line));
7105 assert(p);
7106 ps = __ps_get_ps_upto(&line, p);
7107 __ps_skip(&line, 1);
7108 *method = LSTR_PS_V(&ps);
7109 if (line.b[0] == '/' || line.b[0] == '*') {
7110 *scheme = LSTR_NULL_V;
7111 *authority = LSTR_NULL_V;
7112 } else {
7113 assert(line.b[0] == 'h');
7114 if (line.b[4] == ':') {
7115 *scheme = LSTR_INIT_V(line.s, 4); /* http */
7116 __ps_skip(&line, sizeof("http://") - 1);
7117 } else {
7118 assert(line.b[5] == ':');
7119 *scheme = LSTR_INIT_V(line.s, 5); /* https */
7120 __ps_skip(&line, sizeof("https://") - 1);
7121 }
7122 p = memchr(line.p, '/', ps_len(&line));
7123 assert(p);
7124 ps = __ps_get_ps_upto(&line, p);
7125 *authority = LSTR_PS_V(&ps);
7126 }
7127 *path = LSTR_PS_V(&line);
7128 if (!authority->len) {
7129 /* Get the host line "Host: the-host-value\r\n" */
7130 p = memmem(control.p, ps_len(&control), "\r\n", 2);
7131 line = __ps_get_ps_upto(&control, p + 2);
7132 __ps_skip(&line, strlen("Host: "));
7133 __ps_shrink(&line, 2);
7134 *authority = LSTR_PS_V(&line);
7135 }
7136 *headerlines = control;
7137}
7138
7139static void
7140http2_conn_assert_attachable_httpc_invariants(httpc_t *nonnull httpc)
7141{
7142#ifndef NDEBUG
7143 httpc_query_t *q;
7144
7145 /* At least one query is attached, */
7146 assert(!dlist_is_empty(&httpc->query_list));
7147 /* for which, at least, the request headers are written to the buffer, */
7148 q = dlist_first_entry(&httpc->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
7149 assert(q->hdrs_done);
7150 /* so, the output buffer is not empty, */
7151 assert(!ob_is_empty(&httpc->ob));
7152 /* however, not yet streamed to HTTP/2, so, no response is received
7153 * (parsed) yet. */
7154 assert(httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_IDLE);
7155#endif
7156}
7157
7158/* Attach an idle httpc (headers are not sent yet) to a HTTP/2 stream */
7159static void http2_stream_attach_httpc(http2_conn_t *w, httpc_t *httpc)
7160{
7161 http2_client_t *ctx = w->client_ctx;
7162 httpc_http2_ctx_t *http2_ctx = httpc->http2_ctx;
7163 http2_stream_t *stream;
7164 pstream_t chunk;
7165 lstr_t method;
7166 lstr_t scheme;
7167 lstr_t authority;
7168 lstr_t path;
7169 pstream_t headerlines;
7170 int clen;
7171
7172 http2_conn_assert_attachable_httpc_invariants(httpc);
7173
7174 http2_ctx->http2_stream_id = http2_stream_get_idle(w);
7175 stream = http2_stream_get(w, http2_ctx->http2_stream_id);
7176 chunk = ps_initsb(&httpc->ob.sb);
7177 http_get_http2_request_hdrs(&chunk, &method, &scheme, &path, &authority,
7178 &headerlines);
7179 if (!scheme.len) {
7180 scheme = w->ssl ? LSTR_IMMED_V("https") : LSTR_IMMED_V("http");
7181 }
7182 http2_stream_send_request_headers(w, stream, method, scheme, path,
7183 authority, headerlines, &clen);
7184 stream->ibuf = &httpc->ibuf;
7185 stream->ob = &httpc->ob;
7186 assert(clen >= 0 && "TODO: support chunked requests");
7187 http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark = clen;
7188 OB_WRAP(sb_skip_upto, &httpc->ob, chunk.p);
7189 /* httpc becomes active: payload streaming phase (DATA). */
7190 dlist_move_tail(&ctx->active_httpcs, &http2_ctx->http2_link);
7191}
7192
7193static void http2_conn_stream_idle_httpc(http2_conn_t *w, httpc_t *httpc)
7194{
7195 httpc_query_t *q;
7196
7197 if (!httpc->http2_ctx->first_set_ready_called) {
7198 obj_vcall(httpc, set_ready, true);
7199 httpc->http2_ctx->first_set_ready_called = true;
7200 }
7201
7202 if (dlist_is_empty(&httpc->query_list)) {
7203 if (httpc->connection_close) {
7204 obj_delete(&httpc);
7205 }
7206 return;
7207 }
7208 q = dlist_first_entry(&httpc->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
7209 if (!q->hdrs_done) {
7210 return;
7211 }
7212 http2_stream_attach_httpc(w, httpc);
7213}
7214
7215static void
7216http2_conn_stream_active_httpc(http2_conn_t *w, httpc_t *httpc, int max_sz)
7217{
7218 httpc_http2_ctx_t *http2_ctx = httpc->http2_ctx;
7219 uint32_t stream_id = http2_ctx->http2_stream_id;
7220 http2_stream_t *stream;
7221 pstream_t chunk;
7222 int len;
7223 bool eos;
7224
7225 assert(stream_id);
7226 if (http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark == 0) {
7227 return;
7228 }
7229 assert(http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark <= httpc->ob.length);
7230 stream = http2_stream_get(w, stream_id);
7231 if (stream->events
7232 & (HTTP2_STREAM_EV_CLOSED | HTTP2_STREAM_EV_RST_SENT)) {
7233 /* XXX: stream was already reset or closed and we still have some
7234 * payload to remove from the httpc output buffer. */
7235 assert(0 && "TODO");
7236 }
7237 assert(max_sz <= w->send_window);
7238 len = MIN3(http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark, stream->send_window, max_sz);
7239 if (len <= 0) {
7240 return;
7241 }
7242 assert(htlist_is_empty(&httpc->ob.chunks_list)
7243 && "TODO: support chunked requests");
7244 chunk = ps_initsb(&httpc->ob.sb);
7245 __ps_clip(&chunk, len);
7246 http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark -= len;
7247 eos = http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark == 0;
7248 http2_stream_send_data(w, stream, chunk, eos);
7249 OB_WRAP(sb_skip, &httpc->ob, len);
7250}
7251
7252static void
7253http2_stream_reset_httpc_ob(http2_conn_t *w, httpc_t *httpc)
7254{
7255 httpc_http2_ctx_t *http2_ctx = httpc->http2_ctx;
7256
7257 assert(!http2_ctx->http2_chunked && "TODO: support chunked requests");
7258 assert(htlist_is_empty(&httpc->ob.chunks_list));
7259 OB_WRAP(sb_skip, &httpc->ob, http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark);
7260}
7261
7262/** Reset a steam-attached (active) httpc to the idle state to serve the next
7263 * query if any. */
7264static void http2_stream_reset_httpc(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
7265 bool query_error)
7266{
7267 http2_client_t *ctx;
7268 httpc_t *httpc;
7269 httpc_http2_ctx_t *http2_ctx;
7270
7271 if (!stream->ibuf) {
7272 return;
7273 }
7274
7275 ctx = w->client_ctx;
7276 httpc = container_of(stream->ibuf, httpc_t, ibuf);
7277 http2_ctx = httpc->http2_ctx;
7278
7279 assert(http2_ctx->http2_stream_id);
7280 stream->ibuf = NULL;
7281 stream->ob = NULL;
7282 if (query_error) {
7283 httpc_query_t *q;
7284
7285 http2_stream_reset_httpc_ob(w, httpc);
7286 q = dlist_first_entry(&httpc->query_list, httpc_query_t, query_link);
7287 httpc_query_on_done(q, HTTPC_STATUS_INVALID);
7288 httpc->chunk_length = 0;
7289 httpc->state = HTTP_PARSER_IDLE;
7290 } else {
7291 assert(httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_IDLE);
7292 assert(!http2_ctx->http2_sync_mark);
7293 }
7294 http2_ctx->http2_stream_id = 0;
7295 sb_reset(&httpc->ibuf);
7296 dlist_move_tail(&ctx->idle_httpcs, &http2_ctx->http2_link);
7297 if (httpc->connection_close) {
7298 obj_delete(&httpc);
7299 } else if (httpc->http2_ctx->disconnect_cmd) {
7300 httpc_http2_ctx_delete(&httpc->http2_ctx);
7301 }
7302 return;
7303}
7304
7305static void
7306http2_stream_on_headers_client(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
7307 http2_header_info_t *info,
7308 pstream_t headerlines, bool eos)
7309{
7310 httpc_t *httpc = container_of(stream->ibuf, httpc_t, ibuf);
7311 httpc_http2_ctx_t *httpc_ctx = httpc->http2_ctx;
7312 enum http_parser_state state = httpc->state;
7313 pstream_t ps;
7314
7315 httpc_ctx->substate = HTTP2_CTX_STATE_PARSING;
7316
7317 if (state == HTTP_PARSER_BODY) {
7318 /* XXX: we don't expect trailer headers since we don't ask for them so
7319 * we don't validate if they are really trailer headers or if they end
7320 * the stream, IoW, receiving headers here is an error anyway. */
7321 http2_stream_send_reset(w, stream,
7322 "malformed response [headers while "
7323 "expecting body]");
7324 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, true);
7325 return;
7326 }
7327
7328 /* TODO: dependency on the above HTTP/1.x code: add a test or convert it
7329 * to an expect. */
7330 assert(state == HTTP_PARSER_IDLE &&
7331 "unexpected http2-forwarded httpc state");
7332
7333 sb_addf(&httpc->ibuf, "HTTP/1.1 %pL Nothing But Code\r\n",
7334 &info->status);
7335 sb_add_ps(&httpc->ibuf, headerlines);
7336 sb_add(&httpc->ibuf, "\r\n", 2);
7337 ps = ps_initsb(&httpc->ibuf);
7338 if (httpc_parse_idle(httpc, &ps) != PARSE_OK ||
7339 httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_CHUNK_HDR)
7340 {
7341 if (eos) {
7342 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2,
7343 "malformed response [invalid headers]");
7344 } else {
7345 http2_stream_send_reset(
7346 w, stream, "malformed response [invalid headers]");
7347 }
7348 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, true);
7349 return;
7350 }
7351 sb_skip_upto(&httpc->ibuf, ps.p);
7352 assert(ps_done(&ps));
7353 assert(httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_IDLE ||
7354 httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_BODY);
7355 if (eos) {
7356 bool query_error = false;
7357
7358 if (httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_IDLE) {
7359 http2_stream_trace(
7360 w, stream, 2,
7361 "malformed response [1xx headers with eos]");
7362 query_error = true;
7363 } else {
7364 assert(httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_BODY);
7365 if (httpc_parse_body(httpc, &ps) != PARSE_OK) {
7366 query_error = true;
7367 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2,
7368 "malformed response [no-content]");
7369 }
7370 }
7371 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, query_error);
7372 return;
7373 }
7374
7375 if (httpc->http2_ctx->disconnect_cmd) {
7376 http2_stream_send_reset_cancel(w, stream, "client disconnect");
7377 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, true);
7378 return;
7379 }
7380 httpc_ctx->substate = HTTP2_CTX_STATE_WAITING;
7381}
7382
7383static void
7384http2_stream_on_data_client(http2_conn_t *w, http2_stream_t *stream,
7385 pstream_t data, bool eos)
7386{
7387 httpc_t *httpc = container_of(stream->ibuf, httpc_t, ibuf);
7388 httpc_http2_ctx_t *httpc_ctx = httpc->http2_ctx;
7389 pstream_t ps;
7390 int len;
7391 int res;
7392
7393 assert(httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_BODY);
7394 if (ps_done(&data) && !eos) {
7395 return;
7396 }
7397 sb_add_ps(&httpc->ibuf, data);
7398 ps = ps_initsb(&httpc->ibuf);
7399 len = ps_len(&ps);
7400 if (httpc->chunk_length < 0) {
7401 /* no Content-Length: responses */
7402 if (eos) {
7403 httpc->chunk_length = len;
7404 }
7405 } else {
7406 if (httpc->chunk_length == len) {
7407 /* XXX: ensure that the last call to httpc_parse_body happens only
7408 * when eos arrives, possibly later in a 0-payload DATA frame. */
7409 if (!eos) {
7410 if (len <= 1) {
7411 return;
7412 }
7413 __ps_clip(&ps, --len);
7414 }
7415 } else if (httpc->chunk_length < len) {
7416 /* mismatch: DATA frames > content-length */
7417 if (!eos) {
7418 http2_stream_send_reset(
7419 w, stream, "malformed response [DATA > Content-Length]");
7420 }
7421 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, true);
7422 return;
7423 }
7424 }
7425 httpc_ctx->substate = HTTP2_CTX_STATE_PARSING;
7426 res = httpc_parse_body(httpc, &ps);
7427 switch (res) {
7428 case PARSE_MISSING_DATA:
7429 assert(httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_BODY);
7430 sb_skip_upto(&httpc->ibuf, ps.p);
7431 if (eos) {
7432 /* mismatch: content-length > DATA frames.*/
7433 http2_stream_trace(w, stream, 2,
7434 "malformed response [unexpected eos]");
7435 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, false);
7436 return;
7437 }
7438 break;
7439 case PARSE_OK:
7440 assert(httpc->state == HTTP_PARSER_IDLE);
7441 assert(ps_done(&ps));
7442 assert(eos);
7443 sb_skip_upto(&httpc->ibuf, ps.p);
7444 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, false);
7445 return;
7446 case PARSE_ERROR:
7447 case HTTPC_STATUS_TOOLARGE:
7448 if (!eos) {
7449 http2_stream_send_reset(
7450 w, stream,
7451 "malformed response [invalid payload format or compression]");
7452 }
7453 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, true);
7454 return;
7455 default:
7456 assert(0 && "unexpected result from httpc_parse_body");
7457 }
7458 if (httpc->http2_ctx->disconnect_cmd) {
7459 http2_stream_send_reset_cancel(w, stream, "client disconnect");
7460 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, true);
7461 return;
7462 }
7463 httpc_ctx->substate = HTTP2_CTX_STATE_WAITING;
7464}
7465
7466static void http2_stream_on_reset_client(http2_conn_t *w,
7467 http2_stream_t *stream, bool remote)
7468{
7469 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, true);
7470}
7471
7472static void http2_conn_on_streams_can_write_client(http2_conn_t *w)
7473{
7474 http2_client_t *ctx = w->client_ctx;
7475 dlist_t *httpcs;
7476 bool can_progress;
7477
7478 httpcs = &ctx->idle_httpcs;
7479 dlist_for_each_entry(httpc_http2_ctx_t, httpc, httpcs, http2_link) {
7480 http2_conn_stream_idle_httpc(w, httpc->httpc);
7481 }
7482 httpcs = &ctx->active_httpcs;
7483 do {
7484#define OB_SEND_ALLOC (8 << 10)
7485#define OB_HIGH_MARK (1 << 20)
7486 /* XXX: see http2_conn_on_streams_can_write_server() */
7487 can_progress = false;
7488
7489 dlist_for_each_entry(httpc_http2_ctx_t, httpc, httpcs, http2_link) {
7490 int ob_len = w->ob.length;
7491 int len;
7492
7493 if (ob_len >= OB_HIGH_MARK || w->send_window <= 0) {
7494 can_progress = false;
7495 break;
7496 }
7497 len = MIN(w->send_window, OB_SEND_ALLOC);
7498 http2_conn_stream_active_httpc(w, httpc->httpc, len);
7499 if (w->ob.length - ob_len >= len) {
7500 can_progress = true;
7501 }
7502 }
7503#undef OB_HIGH_MARK
7504#undef OB_SEND_ALLOC
7505 } while (can_progress);
7506}
7507
7508static void httpc_disconnect_as_http2(httpc_t *httpc)
7509{
7510 httpc_http2_ctx_t *http2_ctx = httpc->http2_ctx;
7511 http2_conn_t *w = http2_ctx->conn;
7512
7513 if (http2_ctx->http2_stream_id) {
7514 http2_stream_t *stream =
7515 http2_stream_get(w, http2_ctx->http2_stream_id);
7516
7517 http2_ctx->disconnect_cmd = true;
7518 if (http2_ctx->substate == HTTP2_CTX_STATE_WAITING) {
7519 http2_stream_send_reset_cancel(w, stream, "client disconnect");
7520 http2_stream_reset_httpc(w, stream, true);
7521 }
7522 return;
7523 }
7524 httpc_http2_ctx_delete(&httpc->http2_ctx);
7525}
7526
7527static void http2_conn_close_httpcs(http2_client_t *ctx)
7528{
7529 dlist_t *httpcs;
7530
7531 assert(dlist_is_empty(&ctx->active_httpcs));
7532 httpcs = &ctx->idle_httpcs;
7533 dlist_for_each_entry(httpc_http2_ctx_t, httpc, httpcs, http2_link) {
7534 httpc_t *w1 = httpc->httpc;
7535
7536 obj_vcall(w1, disconnect);
7537 obj_delete(&w1);
7538 }
7539}
7540
7541static void http2_conn_on_close_client(http2_conn_t *w)
7542{
7543 if (w->client_ctx) {
7544 http2_conn_close_httpcs(w->client_ctx);
7545 http2_client_delete(&w->client_ctx);
7546 }
7547}
7548
7549void httpc_close_http2_pool(httpc_cfg_t *cfg)
7550{
7551 if (!cfg->http2_pool) {
7552 return;
7553 }
7554 qm_for_each_value(qhttp2_clients, client, &cfg->http2_pool->qclients) {
7555 client->pool = NULL;
7556 client->conn->send_goaway = true;
7557 client->conn->async_write = true;
7558 http2_conn_trace(client->conn, 4, "send goaway");
7559 el_fd_set_mask(client->conn->ev, POLLINOUT);
7560 }
7561 http2_pool_delete(&cfg->http2_pool);
7562}
7563
7564static void httpc_http2_set_mask(httpc_t *w)
7565{
7566 if (!w->http2_ctx || !w->http2_ctx->conn) {
7567 return;
7568 }
7569 if (!ob_is_empty(&w->ob)) {
7570 w->http2_ctx->conn->async_write = true;
7571 }
7572 el_fd_set_mask(w->http2_ctx->conn->ev, POLLINOUT);
7573}
7574
7575static void httpd_http2_set_mask(httpd_t *w)
7576{
7577 http2_conn_t *conn;
7578
7579 if (!w->http2_ctx || !w->http2_ctx->server) {
7580 return;
7581 }
7582 conn = w->http2_ctx->server->conn;
7583
7584 if (!ob_is_empty(&w->ob)) {
7585 conn->async_write = true;
7586 }
7587 el_fd_set_mask(conn->ev, POLLINOUT);
7588}

7602 return 0;
7603}

7610}

7619#include <lib-common/z.h>

7621static bool has_reply_g;
7622static http_code_t code_g;
7623static sb_t body_g;
7624static httpc_query_t zquery_g;
7625static el_t zel_server_g;
7626static el_t zel_client_g;
7627static httpc_cfg_t zcfg_g;
7628static httpc_status_t zstatus_g;
7629static httpc_t *zhttpc_g;
7630static sb_t zquery_sb_g;
7631
7632static int z_reply_100(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
7633{
7634 SB_1k(buf);
7635
7636 if (sb_read(&buf, fd, 1000) > 0) {
7637 char reply[] = "HTTP/1.1 100 Continue\r\n\r\n"
7638 "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nContent-Length: 6\r\n\r\n"
7639 "Coucou";
7640
7641 IGNORE(xwrite(fd, reply, sizeof(reply) - 1));
7642 }
7643 return 0;
7644}
7645
7646static int z_reply_keep(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
7647{
7648 sb_reset(&zquery_sb_g);
7649 if (sb_read(&zquery_sb_g, fd, BUFSIZ) > 0) {
7650 char reply[] = "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nContent-Length: 6\r\n\r\n"
7651 "Coucou";
7652
7653 IGNORE(xwrite(fd, reply, sizeof(reply) - 1));
7654 }
7655 return 0;
7656}
7657
7658static int z_reply_gzip_empty(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
7659{
7660 SB_1k(buf);
7661
7662 if (sb_read(&buf, fd, 1000) > 0) {
7663 char reply[] = "HTTP/1.1 202 Accepted\r\n"
7664 "Content-Encoding: gzip\r\n"
7665 "Content-Length: 0\r\n"
7666 "\r\n";
7667
7668 IGNORE(xwrite(fd, reply, sizeof(reply) - 1));
7669 }
7670 return 0;
7671}
7672
7673static int z_reply_close_without_content_length(el_t el, int fd, short mask,
7674 data_t data)
7675{
7676 SB_1k(buf);
7677
7678 if (sb_read(&buf, fd, 1000) > 0) {
7679 char reply[] = "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n\r\n"
7680 "Plop";
7681 char s[8192];
7682
7683 IGNORE(xwrite(fd, reply, sizeof(reply) - 1));
7684 fd_set_features(fd, O_NONBLOCK);
7685 for (int i = 0; i < 4096; i++) {
7686 ssize_t len = ssizeof(s);
7687 char *ptr = s;
7688
7689 memset(s, 'a' + (i % 26), sizeof(s));
7690 while (len > 0) {
7691 ssize_t res;
7692
7693 if ((res = write(fd, ptr, len)) <= 0) {
7694 if (res < 0 && !ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
7695 logger_panic(&_G.logger, "write error: %m");
7696 }
7697 el_fd_loop(zhttpc_g->ev, 10, EV_FDLOOP_HANDLE_TIMERS);
7698 continue;
7699 }
7700 ptr += res;
7701 len -= res;
7702 }
7703 }
7704 el_unregister(&zel_client_g);
7705 }
7706 return 0;
7707}
7708
7709static int z_reply_no_content(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
7710{
7711 SB_1k(buf);
7712
7713 if (sb_read(&buf, fd, 1000) > 0) {
7714 char reply[] = "HTTP/1.1 204 No Content\r\n\r\n";
7715
7716 IGNORE(xwrite(fd, reply, sizeof(reply) - 1));
7717 }
7718 return 0;
7719}
7720
7721static int z_accept(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
7722{
7723 int (* query_cb)(el_t, int, short, data_t) = data.ptr;
7724 int client = acceptx(fd, 0);
7725
7726 if (client >= 0) {
7727 zel_client_g = el_fd_register(client, true, POLLIN, query_cb, NULL);
7728 }
7729 return 0;
7730}
7731
7732static int z_query_on_hdrs(httpc_query_t *q)
7733{
7734 code_g = q->qinfo->code;
7735 return 0;
7736}
7737
7738static int z_query_on_data(httpc_query_t *q, pstream_t ps)
7739{
7740 sb_add(&body_g, ps.s, ps_len(&ps));
7741 return 0;
7742}
7743
7744static void z_query_on_done(httpc_query_t *q, httpc_status_t status)
7745{
7746 has_reply_g = true;
7747 zstatus_g = status;
7748}
7749
7750enum z_query_flags {
7751 Z_QUERY_USE_PROXY = (1 << 0),
7752 Z_QUERY_USE_HTTP2 = (1 << 1),
7753};
7754
7755static int z_query_setup(int (* query_cb)(el_t, int, short, el_data_t),
7756 enum z_query_flags flags, lstr_t host, lstr_t uri)
7757{
7758 sockunion_t su;
7759 int server;
7760
7761 zstatus_g = HTTPC_STATUS_ABORT;
7762 has_reply_g = false;
7763 code_g = HTTP_CODE_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR;
7764 sb_init(&body_g);
7765 sb_init(&zquery_sb_g);
7766
7767 Z_ASSERT_N(addr_resolve("test", LSTR("127.0.0.1:1"), &su));
7768 sockunion_setport(&su, 0);
7769
7770 server = listenx(-1, &su, 1, SOCK_STREAM, IPPROTO_TCP, 0);
7771 Z_ASSERT_N(server);
7772 zel_server_g = el_fd_register(server, true, POLLIN, &z_accept, query_cb);
7773
7774 sockunion_setport(&su, getsockport(server, AF_INET));
7775
7776 httpc_cfg_init(&zcfg_g);
7777 zcfg_g.refcnt++;
7778 zcfg_g.use_proxy = (flags & Z_QUERY_USE_PROXY);
7779 if (flags & Z_QUERY_USE_HTTP2) {
7780 zcfg_g.http_mode = HTTP_MODE_USE_HTTP2_ONLY;
7781 }
7782 zhttpc_g = httpc_connect(&su, &zcfg_g, NULL);
7783 Z_ASSERT_P(zhttpc_g);
7784
7785 httpc_query_init(&zquery_g);
7786 httpc_bufferize(&zquery_g, 40 << 20);
7787 zquery_g.on_hdrs = &z_query_on_hdrs;
7788 zquery_g.on_data = &z_query_on_data;
7789 zquery_g.on_done = &z_query_on_done;
7790
7791 httpc_query_attach(&zquery_g, zhttpc_g);
7792 httpc_query_start(&zquery_g, HTTP_METHOD_GET, host, uri);
7793 httpc_query_hdrs_done(&zquery_g, 0, false);
7794 httpc_query_done(&zquery_g);
7795
7796 while (!has_reply_g) {
7797 el_loop_timeout(10);
7798 }
7799 Z_ASSERT_EQ(zstatus_g, HTTPC_STATUS_OK);
7800 Z_HELPER_END;
7801}
7802
7803static void z_query_cleanup(void) {
7804 httpc_query_wipe(&zquery_g);
7805 el_unregister(&zel_server_g);
7806 el_unregister(&zel_client_g);
7807 httpc_cfg_wipe(&zcfg_g);
7808 el_loop_timeout(10);
7809 sb_wipe(&body_g);
7810 sb_wipe(&zquery_sb_g);
7811}
7812
7813Z_GROUP_EXPORT(httpc) {
7814 Z_TEST(unexpected_100_continue, "test behavior when receiving 100") {
7815 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_100, 0,
7816 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/")));
7817
7818 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK , code_g);
7819 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_SB_V(&body_g), LSTR("Coucou"));
7820
7821 z_query_cleanup();
7822 } Z_TEST_END;
7823
7824 Z_TEST(gzip_with_zero_length, "test Content-Encoding: gzip with Content-Length: 0") {
7825 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_gzip_empty, 0,
7826 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/")));
7827
7828 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_ACCEPTED , code_g);
7829 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_SB_V(&body_g), LSTR(""));
7830
7831 z_query_cleanup();
7832 } Z_TEST_END;
7833
7834 Z_TEST(close_with_no_content_length, "test close without Content-Length") {
7835 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_close_without_content_length, 0,
7836 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/")));
7837
7838 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK , code_g);
7839 Z_ASSERT_EQ(body_g.len, 8192 * 4096 + 4);
7840 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_INIT_V(body_g.data, 4), LSTR("Plop"));
7841 sb_skip(&body_g, 4);
7842 for (int i = 0; i < body_g.len; i++) {
7843 Z_ASSERT_EQ(body_g.data[i], 'a' + ((i / 8192) % 26));
7844 }
7845
7846 z_query_cleanup();
7847 } Z_TEST_END;
7848
7849 Z_TEST(url_host_and_uri, "test hosts and URIs") {
7850 /* Normal usage, target separate host and URI */
7851 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_keep, 0,
7852 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/coucou")));
7853 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK , code_g);
7854 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_SB_V(&body_g), LSTR("Coucou"));
7855 Z_ASSERT(lstr_startswith(LSTR_SB_V(&zquery_sb_g),
7856 LSTR("GET /coucou HTTP/1.1\r\n"
7857 "Host: localhost\r\n")));
7858 z_query_cleanup();
7859
7860 /* Proxy that target separate host and URI, URI must be transform to
7861 * absolute */
7862 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_keep, Z_QUERY_USE_PROXY,
7863 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/coucou")));
7864 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK , code_g);
7865 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_SB_V(&body_g), LSTR("Coucou"));
7866 Z_ASSERT(lstr_startswith(LSTR_SB_V(&zquery_sb_g),
7867 LSTR("GET http://localhost/coucou HTTP/1.1\r\n"
7868 "Host: localhost\r\n")));
7869 z_query_cleanup();
7870
7871 /* same thing without leading / */
7872 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_keep, Z_QUERY_USE_PROXY,
7873 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("coucou")));
7874 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK , code_g);
7875 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_SB_V(&body_g), LSTR("Coucou"));
7876 Z_ASSERT(lstr_startswith(LSTR_SB_V(&zquery_sb_g),
7877 LSTR("GET http://localhost/coucou HTTP/1.1\r\n"
7878 "Host: localhost\r\n")));
7879 z_query_cleanup();
7880
7881 /* Proxy with absolute HTTP URL */
7882 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_keep, Z_QUERY_USE_PROXY,
7883 LSTR("localhost"),
7884 LSTR("http://localhost:80/coucou")));
7885 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK , code_g);
7886 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_SB_V(&body_g), LSTR("Coucou"));
7887 Z_ASSERT(lstr_startswith(LSTR_SB_V(&zquery_sb_g),
7888 LSTR("GET http://localhost:80/coucou HTTP/1.1\r\n"
7889 "Host: localhost\r\n")));
7890 z_query_cleanup();
7891
7892 /* Same thing with HTTPS */
7893 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_keep, Z_QUERY_USE_PROXY,
7894 LSTR("localhost"),
7895 LSTR("https://localhost:443/coucou")));
7896 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK , code_g);
7897 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_SB_V(&body_g), LSTR("Coucou"));
7898 Z_ASSERT(lstr_startswith(LSTR_SB_V(&zquery_sb_g),
7899 LSTR("GET https://localhost:443/coucou HTTP/1.1\r\n"
7900 "Host: localhost\r\n")));
7901 z_query_cleanup();
7902 } Z_TEST_END;
7903
7904 Z_TEST(no_content, "test a reply with NO_CONTENT code") {
7905 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_reply_no_content, 0,
7906 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/")));
7907 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_NO_CONTENT, code_g);
7908 z_query_cleanup();
7909 } Z_TEST_END;
7910} Z_GROUP_END;
7911
7912static int
7913z_http2_write_reply(http2_conn_t *w, uint32_t stream_id, int code,
7914 lstr_t headerlines_, lstr_t payload, int payload_repeat)
7915{
7916 t_scope;
7917 pstream_t headerlines = ps_initlstr(&headerlines_);
7918 lstr_t status = t_lstr_fmt("%d", code);
7919 bool eos;
7920 SB_1k(hdrs);
7921
7922 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, LSTR_IMMED_V(":status"), status, &hdrs);
7923 while (!ps_done(&headerlines)) {
7924 lstr_t key;
7925 lstr_t val;
7926
7927 http2_headerlines_get_next_hdr(&headerlines, &key, &val);
7928 http2_conn_pack_single_hdr(w, key, val, &hdrs);
7929 }
7930 eos = (payload.len == 0);
7931 http2_conn_send_headers_block(w, stream_id, ps_initsb(&hdrs), eos);
7932 if (!eos) {
7933 for (int i = payload_repeat + 1; i-- > 0;) {
7934 http2_conn_send_data_block(w, stream_id, ps_initlstr(&payload),
7935 i == 0);
7936 }
7937 }
7938 return 0;
7939}
7940
7941static struct {
7942 int code;
7943 lstr_t headerlines;
7944 lstr_t payload;
7945 int payload_repeat;
7946} z_http2_reply_params_g;
7947
7948static int z_http2_reply_null(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
7949{
7950 SB_1k(buf);
7951 sb_read(&buf, fd, 32 << 10);
7952 return 0;
7953}
7954
7955static int z_http2_reply(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
7956{
7957 SB_1k(buf);
7958
7959 if (sb_read(&buf, fd, 32 << 10) > 0) {
7960 http2_conn_t w;
7961 bool query_reply_written = false;
7962
7963 http2_conn_init(&w);
7964 /* XXX: so flow control does not get in our way. */
7965 w.send_window = HTTP2_LEN_MAX_WINDOW_UPDATE_INCR;
7966 /* Write Server's initial settings */
7967 http2_conn_send_common_hdr(&w, HTTP2_LEN_NO_PAYLOAD,
7968 HTTP2_TYPE_SETTINGS, HTTP2_FLAG_NONE,
7969 HTTP2_ID_NO_STREAM);
7970 fd_set_features(fd, O_NONBLOCK);
7971 while (!ob_is_empty(&w.ob) || !query_reply_written) {
7972 httpc_http2_ctx_t *ctx = zhttpc_g->http2_ctx;
7973 int res;
7974
7975 if (!query_reply_written && ctx && ctx->http2_stream_id) {
7976 uint32_t stream_id = ctx->http2_stream_id;
7977 int code = z_http2_reply_params_g.code;
7978 lstr_t headerlines = z_http2_reply_params_g.headerlines;
7979 lstr_t payload = z_http2_reply_params_g.payload;
7980 int payload_repeat = z_http2_reply_params_g.payload_repeat;
7981
7982 z_http2_write_reply(&w, stream_id, code, headerlines, payload,
7983 payload_repeat);
7984 http2_conn_send_goaway(&w, stream_id, HTTP2_CODE_NO_ERROR,
7985 LSTR_EMPTY_V);
7986 query_reply_written = true;
7987 }
7988 if (!ob_is_empty(&w.ob) && ((res = ob_write(&w.ob, fd)) <= 0)) {
7989 if (res < 0 && !ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
7990 logger_panic(&_G.logger, "write error: %m");
7991 }
7992 }
7993 if (ctx && ctx->conn) {
7994 el_fd_loop(ctx->conn->ev, 10, EV_FDLOOP_HANDLE_TIMERS);
7995 }
7996 sb_reset(&buf);
7997 res = sb_read(&buf, fd, 32 << 10);
7998 if (res < 0 && !ERR_RW_RETRIABLE(errno)) {
7999 logger_panic(&_G.logger, "read error: %m");
8000 }
8001 if (res == 0) {
8002 break;
8003 }
8004 }
8005 http2_conn_wipe(&w);
8006 lstr_wipe(&z_http2_reply_params_g.headerlines);
8007 lstr_wipe(&z_http2_reply_params_g.payload);
8008 shutdown(fd, SHUT_WR);
8009 el_fd_set_hook(el, &z_http2_reply_null);
8010 }
8011 return 0;
8012}
8013
8014static int z_http2_reply_no_content(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
8015{
8016 z_http2_reply_params_g.code = HTTP_CODE_NO_CONTENT;
8017 z_http2_reply_params_g.headerlines = LSTR_EMPTY_V;
8018 z_http2_reply_params_g.payload = LSTR_EMPTY_V;
8019 z_http2_reply_params_g.payload_repeat = 0;
8020
8021 return z_http2_reply(el, fd, mask, data);
8022}
8023
8024static int z_http2_reply_ok(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
8025{
8026 z_http2_reply_params_g.code = HTTP_CODE_OK;
8027 z_http2_reply_params_g.headerlines =
8028 LSTR("x-custom-header-1: value-1\r\n"
8029 "x-custom-header-2: value-2\r\n");
8030 z_http2_reply_params_g.payload = LSTR("Coucou");
8031 z_http2_reply_params_g.payload_repeat = 0;
8032
8033 return z_http2_reply(el, fd, mask, data);
8034}
8035
8036static int z_http2_reply_ok_big(el_t el, int fd, short mask, data_t data)
8037{
8038 sb_t payload;
8039
8040 z_http2_reply_params_g.code = HTTP_CODE_OK;
8041 z_http2_reply_params_g.headerlines =
8042 LSTR("x-custom-header-1: value-1\r\n"
8043 "x-custom-header-2: value-2\r\n");
8044 sb_init(&payload);
8045 while (payload.len < 8192) {
8046 const char *s = "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
8047
8048 sb_add(&payload, s, MIN(8192 - payload.len, (int)strlen(s)));
8049 }
8050 lstr_transfer_sb(&z_http2_reply_params_g.payload, &payload, true);
8051 z_http2_reply_params_g.payload_repeat = 4096 - 1;
8052
8053 return z_http2_reply(el, fd, mask, data);
8054}
8055
8056Z_GROUP_EXPORT(httpc_http2) {
8057 Z_TEST(no_content, "test a reply with NO_CONTENT code") {
8058 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_http2_reply_no_content,
8059 Z_QUERY_USE_HTTP2,
8060 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/")));
8061 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_NO_CONTENT, code_g);
8062 z_query_cleanup();
8063 } Z_TEST_END;
8064
8065 Z_TEST(ok, "test a reply with 200 OK code and a small payload") {
8066 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_http2_reply_ok,
8067 Z_QUERY_USE_HTTP2,
8068 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/")));
8069 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK, code_g);
8070 Z_ASSERT_LSTREQUAL(LSTR_SB_V(&body_g), LSTR("Coucou"));
8071 z_query_cleanup();
8072 } Z_TEST_END;
8073
8074 Z_TEST(ok_big, "test a reply with 200 OK code and a big payload") {
8075 Z_HELPER_RUN(z_query_setup(&z_http2_reply_ok_big, Z_QUERY_USE_HTTP2,
8076 LSTR("localhost"), LSTR("/")));
8077 Z_ASSERT_EQ((http_code_t)HTTP_CODE_OK, code_g);
8078 Z_ASSERT_EQ(body_g.len, 8192 * 4096);
8079 for (int i = 0; i < body_g.len; i++) {
8080 Z_ASSERT_EQ(body_g.data[i], 'a' + (i % 8192) % 26);
8081 }
8082 z_query_cleanup();
8083 } Z_TEST_END;
8084} Z_GROUP_END;
